title: corn bread salad
directions: Mix cornmeal, egg and milk together.
Stir in chilies, cumin, oregano and sage.
Bake at 400° until done. Cool.
In a small bowl, mix mayonnaise, sour cream and dressing mix.
Crumble cornbread in 9-inch square pan.
Layer with beans, corn, tomatoes, green pepper and onion.
Spread mayonnaise mixture on next. Add crumbled bacon next and sprinkle with cheese last. Cover and refrigerate.

title: buttermilk pecan pie
directions: Cream the butter, sugar and vanilla; add eggs one at a time. Add flour, salt and buttermilk to egg mixture; beat until smooth. Put pecans in bottom of crust.
Slowly pour mixture over pecans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (until center is set).

title: corn pudding casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except oleo together.
Melt oleo in baking dish.
Add corn mixture.
DO NOT STIR.
Bake at 350 for 45 minutes.

title: lemon delight
directions: Crumble together and press in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes and cool.

title: stuffed chicken cordon bleu
directions: Flatten chicken between waxed paper to 1/4-inch thick.
Saute mushrooms, onions and garlic in oil, wine and butter until softened.
Add parsley, salt and pepper to taste.
Place 1 to 2 slices Swiss on each chicken breast, then 1 to 2 slices shaved ham. Top with 2 tablespoons Cheddar, then vegetable mix.
Roll chicken tightly and tie in 3 places with kitchen string to secure.
Beat egg(s) with milk.
Mix flour with cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Dip chicken rolls in egg mixture, then flour mixture.
Preheat 1/4-inch deep vegetable oil in large frying pan.
Fry roll-ups 15 minutes or until golden brown, turning constantly.

title: refrigerator pickles
directions: Mix the cucumbers, onions, green peppers and 2 tablespoons salt in tightly covered container.
Let stand in refrigerator at least 2 hours, longer is okay.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Mix and put in bottom of pan.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Mix all together. Roll and chill 12 hours or put in freezer for 3 hours. Slice and bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: spiced nuts
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Fold in nuts until wet.
Mix dry ingredients; fold into wet nuts.
Stir until nuts are well coated.

title: raisin nut clusters
directions: Melt chocolate over low heat. Add nuts and raisins. Mix until lightly coated. Drop small amount from teaspoon onto waxed paper. Chill until firm.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Add brown sugar and cider together in crock-pot or large pot. Wrap spices in piece of cheesecloth and add to cider.
Cook slowly for approximately 4 hours.
Remove spices.
Place orange slices on top of cider.

title: chicken enchiladas supreme(a true mexican delight.  hot!)
directions: In a medium-size saucepan, add garlic and onion to hot oil. Cook until onion is tender, not browned.
Add green chilies to cooking onion along with tomato sauce, salt, pepper and oregano. Simmer 20 minutes.
(Sauce may be pureed in blender if desired.)

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and pepper.
Mix cornmeal, buttermilk, soda, corn, eggs and cayenne pepper together.
Add cooking oil and salt.
Pour 1/2 of cornmeal mixture into a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Then add meat mixture and top with grated cheese.
Top with remaining cornmeal mixture.
Bake in 300° to 325° oven for 45 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Bread should be moist.

title: strawberry magic cake
directions: Spread 10 ounce package of miniature marshmallows in single layer to cover bottom of 9 x 13 x 2-inch greased baking pan. Next, spread 18 ounce box yellow cake mix, prepared by box directions, over top of marshmallows.
Sprinkle jello powder over cake batter.
Drop slightly thawed strawberries by spoonful onto top of mixture.
Drizzle water over all without stirring.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes.

title: cilantro dressing
directions: Puree cilantro, garlic, jalapenos, vinegar, water and salt in a food processor.
Fold mixture into mayonnaise and blend well to combine.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pumpkin drop cookies
directions: Cream together the sugar, pumpkin, eggs, shortening and vanilla.
Set aside.
Sift together the next 7 ingredients.
Add the raisins or nuts.
Gradually add this to the creamed mixture. Drop by spoonful onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 14 dozen.

title: wild rice salad(recipe includes diabetic exchanges)
directions: This tasy dish uses less sugar, salt and fat.

title: grandma's cinnamon rolls
directions: The night before, dissolve the yeast in the warm water. Add 1 cup sugar and the potato water to the mashed potatoes and mix. When the yeast water is cold, add it to the potato mixture and let it set overnight.

title: hot meat balls
directions: Form meat into small balls.
Put all ingredients into pot and cook until meat is done.

title: never fail rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix sugar, shortening, salt and boiling water.
When this mixture is lukewarm, add yeast mixture and eggs.
Beat with mixer.
Add flour. Cover with greased wax paper.
Put in refrigerator. Roll out and let rise as needed. Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.
Dough keeps in refrigerator for several days.

title: tomato sauce
directions: Mix together and refrigerate overnight.
Serve over rice or with rice and black or brown beans.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Put
all
ingredients in
Dutch
oven
type
pan.
Cook slowly on top of stove for
approximately	2
1/2	or 3 hours, turning occasionally.
When meat
is
done, let cool for slicing.
Slice meat thin.	Return sliced meat to pan.
Add 2 or 3 sliced bell peppers plus 1
cup water.	Cook again slowly just until peppers are tender.
Serve on Italian buns.

title: chocolate nut butter cookies
directions: Cream shortening and peanut butter.
Add 2 eggs.
Beat well, blending in dry ingredients, alternately with 1/3 cup milk, blending well after each addition.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Press with fork to flatten.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 9 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Still soft when done.

title: lemonade
directions: Combine sugar and water in saucepan. Boil for 1 minute to make syrup. Cool.

title: cream cheese mints
directions: Combine cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Add food coloring and peppermint.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown
meat; drain well, then make meat layer in bottom of
a 2
quart casserole.
Cover with corn.
Add mashed potatoes.
Frost mashed
potatoes
with diluted ketchup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes until edges bubble.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: Drain fruit well. Combine oranges, pineapple, marshmallows, sour cream and 1 cup coconut, mixing lightly but thoroughly. Garnish with the other cup of coconut and cherries. Chill well.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Sift flour and salt together into a small bowl.
Make a well in the flour and add oil and egg.
Add boiling water and mix well. Chill in refrigerator until ready to use.
Knead in enough flour to roll out with rolling pin.
Divide into 2 or 3 sections, roll out and cut into strips, one section at a time, with kitchen knife.
Drop into boiling stock.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Do not stir.
They may be moved gently with fork.

title: cheesy manicotti
directions: Heat sauce and water together in saucepan to boiling.
Remove from heat and keep warm.
Mix together cheeses and seasonings. Save 1 cup Mozzarella for top.
Spoon mixture into uncooked shells.
Place 1 cup sauce in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Arrange shells in single layer over sauce.
Pour remaining sauce over manicotti.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Add some more Parmesan cheese on top.
Cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 minutes more.

title: beef tenderloin for six
directions: Heat oil; brown meat. Add salt, pepper, bouillon and vegetables. Simmer 2 minutes. Mix sherry, soy sauce and cornstarch.
Add to simmering steak. Stir constantly until thick. Serve with hot cooked noodles or rice.

title: chicken dumplings
directions: Stew chicken until tender and has plenty of broth.
Add butter to season; salt and pepper to taste.
Blend ingredients to make dough.
Roll out on board until thin.
Cut in strips and drop in boiling broth.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add some rich milk to make a gravy and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Do not stir while cooking.

title: bab's beef stroganoff
directions: Cut round steak into thin, bite size strips.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder, as desired.
Coat beef strips with flour.
Brown in large frying pan with 1 to 2 tablespoons cooking oil.
Add onion and brown until tender.
Add mushroom sauce and mushrooms; stir.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add sour cream and heat until warmed.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: chocolate cherry upside down cake
directions: Spread filling in greased 13 x 9 x 2 pan.
Stir together flour, sugar, cocoa, soda and salt.
In a bowl, combine water, oil, vinegar and vanilla.
Add liquids to flour mixture at once. Stir to moisten.
Pour evenly over filling.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Cool ten minutes.
Invert to serving plate and cool.

title: sesame cookies
directions: Cream Crisco, margarine, sugar, eggs, vanilla and anise extracts.
Mix flour with baking powder.
Add liquid mixture to flour mixture.
Stir until it forms a soft dough.
Roll into lengthwise cookie shape.
Roll in milk and sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes on greased cookie sheet.

title: oatmeal drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together in mixer thoroughly.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart on lightly greased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned at 400°, about 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 5 dozen 2 1/2-inch cookies.

title: korean barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Use Tabasco or garlic/pepper sauce to suit your taste.
Use as a marinade.

title: see's fudge candy
directions: Boil milk and sugar on medium heat, stirring all the time. Simmer 5 minutes.
In a separate bowl, mix together marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Pour hot mixture over marshmallows and stir until all has dissolved.
Pour into a buttered pan and let stand at room temperature for 24 hours.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Heat Karo syrup, brown sugar and peanut butter to blend.
Add 2 cups Rice Krispies and 2 cups corn flakes to mixture.
Cool 1 hour and press into jelly roll pan.
Mix together margarine, vanilla pudding, powdered sugar and milk.
Spread on base.
Melt 1 cup chocolate chips with 6 tablespoons margarine and spread on bars.

title: stir and roll biscuits
directions: Place flour, salt and soda in a mixing bowl. Combine oil and buttermilk in a measuring cup. Pour combination into flour mixture and stir quickly until dough clings together. Turn out onto lightly floured board; knead lightly and roll out. Cut with biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet and bake about 10 minutes in a 450° oven. Makes 16 to 20 biscuits.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Mix eggs and salt. Add flour; when mixture gets thick, use hands. Add little bits of flour if mix is sticky to hands. Keep adding flour until mixture is no longer sticky. Take out a chunk (handful of dough or less); roll out. Use additional flour if needed. Let dry, turning rolled out dough. Cut dough when it is almost dry into strips. Place in bowl overnight. Boil chicken broth or beef broth. Cook noodles until done. Serve.

title: potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes and eggs.
While they are cooking, in a large bowl, mix 2 kinds of mayonnaise, mustard, minced onion (optional), salt, pepper, Sweet 'N Low, pickle relish and eggs.
These may be chopped and added.
When they have cooled, skin potatoes.
When they are cool, chop and stir them in.
I sometimes add chopped celery.

title: never fail dumplings
directions: Mix all ingredients together until soft dough is formed. Divide into 3 parts.
Roll out very thin.
Let sheets of dough dry for 15 to 20 minutes.
Cut dough into small strips and drop in boiling chicken broth.
Cook dumplings until tender.
Dumplings are good with any meat stock.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in refrigerator to gel.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix together and spread in serving dish.
Top with shredded cheese, diced tomatoes, peppers and black olives.
Serve at room temperature with tortilla chips.

title: three bean salad
directions: Drain
all beans; rinse well.
Drain again.
Add peppers, celery and onions.
Mix vinegar, cooking oil, sugar, salt and pepper together. Pour over beans, etc.
Let marinate in refrigerator overnight.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Add dry ingredients. Cool dough 3 to 4 hours.
Roll out.
Cut out.
Decorate with sprinkles.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 400°.

title: easy au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook sliced potatoes in water until tender and drain.
In saucepan melt butter, add flour and stir well.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add 4 slices cheese, diced, to milk mixture.
Stir well, then add potatoes and bake at 375° until cheese melts.

title: easy barbecue chicken casserole
directions: Place beans in a 2-quart casserole.
Top with chicken.
Mix together remaining ingredients; pour over chicken and beans. Cover and bake in preheated 325° oven for 1 3/4 hours.
Serves 4.

title: marble pound cake(cold oven)
directions: Cream sugar, margarine and Crisco; add eggs and flour, then add remaining ingredients. Don't beat too much. Leave 1/5 batter and add 2 tablespoons chocolate; swirl around in cake batter. Place in cold oven and set to 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: snack dinner
directions: Assemble.
Everyone compiles their own dinner from what's available in the middle of the table.
One or two cutting boards help.
Eat and eat until you're full!
(It's fast food!)

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Mix all together.
Can be served immediately or prepared ahead of time and refrigerated.

title: tomato salsa
directions: You can use any hot pepper you like instead of jalapenos.

title: carrot cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: pistachio cake
directions: Mix ingredients in a large bowl at medium speed for 2 minutes. Stir in 1/2 cup of chopped nuts.
Pour into a greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until center springs back when lightly touched.
Use either a Bundt or angel food cake pan. Cool 15 minutes before removing from pan.

title: corn meal muffins
directions: Mix corn meal, sugar, soda, egg and enough buttermilk to make soft.
Add flour, salt, baking powder and melted lard.
Stir just enough to mix.
Pour into muffin pan or biscuit pan in hot oven.

title: potato biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix Potato Buds and hot water; let stand until water is absorbed.
Mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; stir into potato mixture.
Stir in milk.
Turn onto well floured surface.
Pat dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with 2-inch biscuit cutter.
Place onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown.
Makes 16 biscuits.

title: easy fluffy icing
directions: Cook milk and flour unti thick, stirring constantly.
Cool completely.
Add granulated sugar gradually.
Beat to mix.
Add flavoring.
Beat on high speed for 10 minutes (no less).

title: milk and honey cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
This will make a stiff batter. Form into balls and roll in powdered sugar.
No baking necessary.

title: waikiki meatballs
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, onion, egg, salt, ginger and milk.
Shape mixture by rounded teaspoonfuls into balls.
Brown and cook meatballs in oil.
Remove meatballs, keep warm.
Pour fat from skillet.

title: zucchini pie
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Pour into an unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Sprinkle with nutmeg and cinnamon.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce to 300° for 30 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite-size chunks.
Mix sour cream with soup.
Mix with chicken chunks.
Blend melted butter with Ritz crackers.
Put on top of chicken.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: recipe for a happy family
directions: Mix well.
Sprinkle with care.
Bake in a moderate oven of everyday life.
Place on a platter of cheerfulness.
Garnish with few tears and lots of laughter.
Serve God, country and your community.

title: oatmeal fruit cookies(low-fat)
directions: Mash bananas.
Add egg whites and dates.
Mix in oats and raisins.
Spoon cookies onto nonstick cookie sheet.
Press cookies flat with spoon.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: frozen cole slaw
directions: Mix all together, except vinegar, sugar and water.
Boil vinegar, sugar and water; cool.
Pour over cabbage mixture.
Stir will.
Place in freezer containers.
Freeze.

title: old fashion vegetable soup(makes 14 cups.)
directions: Brown beef and onion until meat is done. Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients except corn, beans and peas. Simmer 30 minutes or until raw vegetables are tender. Add canned vegetables; continue heating 5 minutes.

title: instant banana pudding
directions: Mix pudding as directed.
Add half Cool Whip.
Layer vanilla wafers, layer bananas and a thin layer of pudding.
Repeat, ending with wafers on top.
Add remaining pudding on top.
Chill before serving.

title: peanut butter delight
directions: Melt margarine in large pot over low heat. Add sugar, salt, cocoa and milk. Mix well. Bring to a boil and boil for 1 minute and 15 seconds. Remove from heat. Add peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal. Mix well. Pour in greased dish.

title: mexi burgers
directions: Make 4 patties from the ground chuck.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook until good and brown.
Place patties in baking dish.
Pour salsa over each patty, as much as desired.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.
When done, place a teaspoon of Cheez Whiz on each, re-cover with foil and place in oven until cheese melts.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Place chicken pieces in a baking dish or aluminum foil.
Mix all ingredients for sauce and heat until margarine and sugar have melted.
Pour sauce over chicken and cover with foil.
Bake 15 minutes at 450° and 1 hour at 300°.

title: bacon wrapped shrimp
directions: Dip shrimp into a mixture of melted butter, chili powder, and garlic. Wrap shrimp in half slices of bacon and fasten with wooden toothpicks. Place on rack in broiler pan and broil 3 inches from source of heat for about 5 minutes. Brush with butter and broil another 5 minutes.

title: passover sweet potato kugel
directions: Mix all ingredients with a spoon.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: clafoutis(from france)
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt and milk.
Add butter and vanilla. Prepare fruit by slicing it and sprinkling with sugar.
Use fresh apricots or fresh cherries.
You can leave pits in cherries. Grease a Pyrex flan dish with butter.
Pour fruit into dish.
Then add the mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
When the cake is almost done, sprinkle with sugar on top and cook for about 15 minutes more.

title: sweet corn fritters
directions: In a medium bowl, beat together egg and milk.
Add flour and mix well.
Stir in corn kernels and salt.
Just before cooking, add baking powder.
Heat about 1 1/2 inches of oil in a deep fryer or frying pan.
Drop batter by spoonfuls into oil and fry on both sides just until crisp and golden, about 1 minute.
Drain on paper towel and serve immediately.
Makes about 14 fritters.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Mix egg whites, sugar, salt, water and syrup in top of double boiler.
Cook over boiling water, beating with an electric mixer until it stands in a peak.
Remove from boiling water.
Add vanilla and continue beating until slightly cool.

title: christmas fruit rolls
directions: Crush fine 1 box of vanilla wafers (save 1/2 cup).
Mix well all ingredients.
Divide into 2 logs.
Roll
in
crumbs. Wrap in foil and refrigerate.

title: homestyle chicken and biscuit dumplings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Shake flour in cooking bag.
Place in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Add gravy mix, garlic powder and water. Squeeze bag to blend.
Place carrots and celery in bag.
Sprinkle chicken with seasonings.
Place on top of vegetables.
Arrange biscuits around chicken.
Close bag with a tie.
Cut 6 (1/2-inch) slits in top of bag.
Bake until chicken is tender, about 50 to 55 minutes.

title: nannie's homemade chocolate
directions: Start by boiling water and salt.
In a large bowl mix flour, sugar and cocoa together; then add to boiling water.
Then add your butter and vanilla.
Mix until smooth.

title: scotch spud cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients; dough will be stiff.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: *Wild strawberry is best if you can get it.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix water and Jell-O until dissolved.
Cool until thick (not completely set).
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add strawberries to Cool Whip and Jell-O mix.
Put into your favorite pie shell.
Graham cracker crust is good.

title: divinity
directions: Stir sugar, Karo and water over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture boils.
Reduce heat and cook, without stirring, until temperature reaches 260° or it drops like pebbles in cold water.

title: best date bars
directions: In a saucepan, combine dates, sugar and water.
Cook, stirring frequently, until very thick.
Stir in nuts; cool.
Meanwhile, sift flour, salt and soda together in a mixing bowl; add oats and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle water over mixture; stir lightly.
Pat half into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Spread with date mixture; cover with remaining oat mixture and pat lightly.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool and cut into bars.
Yields 40 bars.

title: ripe tomato catsup
directions: Mix all together.
Cook slowly; stir often and cook until thick.
Pour into jars and seal.

title: date cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients; cut in shortening with pastry blender. Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Chill well.
Roll 1/8-inch thick on lightly floured surface.
Cut with 2 1/2-inch round cutter. Arrange 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheet.
Place 1/2 teaspoon fruit filling on one side dough.
Fold over like a turnover and press edges together with fork.
Bake in oven at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: kindergarten hot dogs
directions: Cook hot dogs on a stove.
Put them in a bun.
Then eat it.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Mix and bake cake mix according to directions on box; bake cake in an oblong cake pan.
After cake is done and while hot, cut into tiny squares.
Mix sugar and lemonade and pour over cake and down into cuts.
Put cake back into oven for 5 minutes.
Remove and allow to cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Reserve 1 cup broth.
Remove cooked chicken from bone and cut into bite-sized pieces.
Place chicken in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
In medium bowl, combine reserved broth, soups, pimento and water chestnuts.
Add to chicken, mixing well.
Combine butter, flour and milk.
Pour over chicken mixture. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or until casserole is bubbly and crust is golden brown.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly with mixer.
Bake in greased loaf pans at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until brown on top. Yields 3 loaves.

title: caramel corn
directions: Keep popped corn warm.
Mix sugar, syrup and butter in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil and boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat. Add soda, cream of tartar and salt.

title: cherry cheese cake
directions: Beat cheese and add powdered sugar.
Blend together cheese mixture and whipped topping.
Pour into cooled graham cracker crust.
Pour cherry pie filling on top.

title: mushroom chicken quiche
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix rice, 2 of the egg whites and 1/4 teaspoon of the rosemary.
Press onto bottom and sides of lightly greased 10-inch quiche dish or pie plate to form crust.
Bake 10 minutes.
Stir Velveeta Light pasteurized process cheese product and milk in saucepan over low heat until smooth.
Add remaining 3 egg whites, remaining 1/4 teaspoon rosemary, chicken, mushrooms and pepper; mix lightly.
Pour into crust.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until filling is set.
Garnish with fresh rosemary; if desired. Makes 8 servings (190 calories).

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat until frothy the salad oil and eggs.
Add sugar, vanilla and milk; blend until creamy.
If still thick, add a little more milk.
Sift together baking soda, salt, flour and cinnamon.
Add gradually to other mixture.
Fold in apples and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: mamie's million dollar fudge - 1955
directions: Let first four ingredients boil 6 minutes, stirring constantly.
In a large bowl put remaining ingredients.
Pour boiling syrup over ingredients in bowl and heat until chocoalte is all melted.
Pour into buttered pan.
Let cool several hours before cutting.
Store in tin box.

title: summer pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls on cookie sheet to cover pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dill weed.
Cool crust.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust.
Top with vegetables and season to taste.

title: slim-down chicken
directions: Simmer or bake chicken with salsa until done.

title: chicken and wine
directions: Place chicken in glass dish.
Put carrots, celery and onion on top.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts and cut into bite-size pieces.
Place in casserole dish; add sour cream, soup, mushrooms and milk.
Mix well.
Make 1/2 recipe on bag of stuffing.
Put on top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or until bubbly.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: funnel cake
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, sugar, milk and egg.
Mix until smooth.
Heat 1-inch oil in pan.
Holding finger over opening, fill with 1/4 cup batter and then pour into oil, using a circular motion to form a 4-inch spiral.
Fry until golden brown, turning once. Drain on
paper towels.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Serve warm with jelly or preserves, if desired.

title: boiled cookies(tastes like candy)
directions: In a medium saucepan, add the sugar, cocoa, milk and butter. Bring to a boil and boil for 3 minutes; remove from heat. Add the peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Drop by spoonful onto wax paper. Cool completely.

title: deviled ham spread
directions: Place ham, celery, mayonnaise, relish, chili sauce, mustard and hot pepper sauce in a food processor bowl fitted with the metal blade; cover.
Process until blended, scraping sides as needed. Taste and adjust seasonings.

If you don't have a food processor, grind or mince ham and mince celery before combining with mayonnaise, relish, chili sauce, mustard and hot pepper sauce. Spread on cocktail bread or crackers, use to stuff celery or thin with milk and use as a dip with corn chips or raw vegetables. Makes 1 cup.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Slice in 1/8-inch slices; combine with sliced onions and salt.
Let stand for 3 hours.
Drain well, rinse thoroughly and drain again.
In a pot, combine vinegar, sugar, turmeric, mustard seed, celery seed and red pepper; bring to a boil.
Add cucumbers and onions; heat just to simmering.
Do not boil!
Pack in sterilized jars; seal at once.
Makes 7 to 9 jars.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Combine broccoli and onion; cook according to package directions.
Drain and add remaining ingredients; stir well. Pour into greased 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Mix and add beaten egg whites; pour into unbaked crust and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Continue baking at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: carousel rice salad
directions: Combine rice, carrots, celery, sweet pickle, salt and pepper. Toss lightly, then chill.
Blend basil into sour cream.
Serve chilled rice mixture on salad greens.
Top with seasoned sour cream.

title: taco salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except dressing and Fritos. Right before serving, add dressing and Fritos.

title: hamburger, pea and celery casserole
directions: Brown meat until redness disappears.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a casserole dish and add the frozen peas (not cooked or thawed).
Mix milk/cream with mushroom soup.
Add onion to soup mixture.
Place celery on top of frozen peas.
Pour soup mixture over celery.
Add potato chips over the top.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.
(Celery should be crunchy.)

title: fresh vegetable casserole
directions: Season each vegetable individually with salt and pepper and mix all together.
Put into casserole.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top, then plain bread crumbs.
Cover completely with bread crumbs and pour melted butter over casserole.
Bake at 350° until bread crumbs form crust, approximately 1/2 to 3/4 hour.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: corn meal casserole
directions: Cook corn meal.
Turn cooked corn meal into greased 2-quart casserole.
Level top of corn meal with spoon.
Melt butter in skillet and saute mushrooms 3 minutes.
Add tomato sauce and stir. Pour over cooked corn meal.
Sprinkle with cheese and pepper. Bake in oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: curry dip
directions: Mix well and serve with cauliflower, carrots, cucumbers and other raw vegetables.

title: crunchy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave until tender.
Drain water, then spread evenly into a lightly greased casserole dish.
Add cheese chunks and sprinkle crackers on top.
Pour melted butter on top of crackers and bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: mississippi delta's stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Soak cabbage in hot water until pliable.
Carefully peel off leaves and place in boiling water for 5 minutes to soften.
Mix well the meat, rice, salt, pepper, chili powder, tomatoes and onion.
Place 1 tablespoon of meat mixture on each cabbage leaf (cut the large leaves in half).
Wrap and secure with a toothpick. In Dutch oven, arrange cabbage rolls.
Make a second layer if necessary.
Sprinkle each layer liberally with additional salt. Add enough water to the ketchup and reserved tomato juice to make 2 cups liquid.
Pour over cabbage rolls.
Sprinkle brown sugar, lemon juice and bay leaf over rolls.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Cover dish tightly and bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Serves 8.

title: cheese danish
directions: Combine cream cheese, egg yolks, 3/4 cup sugar and vanilla in a bowl.
Mix with mixer on high until creamy, about 3 minutes; set aside.

title: french dressing
directions: Put all ingredients in jar and shake well.
Makes a pint.

title: the best congo bars on the face of the earth
directions: Cream brown sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time. Beat until light.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla; mix.
Add chocolate chips and nuts, if using them.
Spread in large pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spiced apple cider
directions: Dissolve red hots in cider (put in microwave).
Add rest of cider and orange juice.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, leaving enough chips to sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in hot water and buttermilk.
Add sugar and shortening.
Blend in 2 cups flour until elastic.
Add 2 more cups flour.
Roll, cut and dip in hot butter.
Fold as for a pocketbook.
Place in a pan.
Let rise until double in bulk (about 3 hours).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Rub butter on top of hot rolls.

title: mexican omelet roll
directions: Place ham in an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish. Cover and cook on High in microwave for 3 to 4 minutes or until heated through. Cover with foil and allow to stand while fixing the omelet. Place butter, green pepper and onion in a dish (11 3/4 x 7 1/2 x 1 3/4 inches). Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes or until vegetables are tender. Stir together eggs and water. Pour over vegetables. Sprinkle with pimentos. Cover with plastic wrap and cook 8 to 10 minutes on High. Turn dish 4 times while cooking. Remove plastic wrap and loosen bottom and edges of omelet with a rubber spatula. Cover dish with wax paper. Place cookie sheet over paper. Flip omelet out onto cookie sheet. Place ham on small end of omelet in jelly roll fashion. Put seam side down on serving dish. Serve topped with cheese sauce.

title: crab almond dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients, reserving about 1/3 of almonds for top.
Bake at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: soft peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Add rest.
Roll into ball.
Put about 1 cup sugar in a bag and coat ball.
Place on greased pan.
Make with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350°. Sprinkle top with brown sugar before baking.

title: shoo-fly molasses cake
directions: Place the flour, sugar and margarine or butter in a large bowl.
Cream together thoroughly to make crumbs.
Set aside 1 cup of crumbs to sprinkle over top of cake.
Place the molasses, warm water and baking soda in another bowl.
Blend together.
Add liquid mixture to crumbs.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining crumbs over top of cake.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: old time egg custard
directions: Beat eggs well.
Combine with sugar and 1 tablespoon flour. Stir until mixed.
Put in 2 cups milk and stir.
Pour mixture over pie dough.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top and place pats of butter on top. Cook at 400° until firm and golden.

title: cavatelli
directions: In a large skillet, brown ground beef, pork, bacon, mushrooms and onion.
Add tomatoes, bay leaf, garlic, basil, salt and pepper.
Simmer 1 hour, adding water, if necessary.
Add tomato paste and simmer an additional 15 minutes.
Remove bay leaf.
Pour sauce over cooked pasta and top with grated Parmesan cheese.
This is best if prepared the day before, refrigerated overnight and heated up the next day.

title: dumplings for chicken
directions: Cook and debone chicken.
Add poultry seasoning to broth. Bring to a boil.
Mix flour, margarine and milk in bowl.
From dough into balls.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on a floured board and cut into 1-inch squares.
Drop dumplings into broth.
Keep broth boiling.
Cook dumplings 20 minutes on medium heat.
Add chicken. Stir together.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together. Chill. Serve with fresh or frozen fruit.

title: potatoes romanoff
directions: Cook potatoes
until tender.
Peel and shred into large bowl. Add rest
of ingredients, except half cup of cheese and paprika for top.
Pour
into
2-quart buttered dish.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Refrigerate
for	several hours or overnight.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine in dish in oven; add rice.
Pour water over it. Add other ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: diet strawberry pie
directions: Cook ingredients until it begins to boil; let cool. Mix strawberries. Pour in shell. Top with Cool Whip if you like.

title: tamale dip
directions: Mash tamales; combine with chili, Ro-Tel and Velveeta. Microwave on Medium until cheese is melted.
Serve hot with chips.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: In large, skillet, brown ground turkey with onion and green pepper.
Saute over medium heat, stirring occasionally, until meat is cooked.
Drain well.
Stir in Sloppy Joe sauce, salt, pepper, macaroni, corn and Cheddar cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.

title: coleslaw italian style
directions: Lock bowl in place and insert slicer disk.
Slice celery and cabbage; empty bowl as necessary.
Insert steel blade.
Add tuna, capers and olives.
Process, using start-stop until coarsely chopped.
Mix all ingredients by hand.
Add vinegar to taste. Serves 8.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello as directed on package; let cool.
Add pineapple and cottage cheese; add Cool Whip just before it jells.

title: sherry's ono short ribs
directions: Salt and pepper ribs and place into large pot.
Combine other ingredients except green onion and add this sauce to pot.
Bring to rapid boil.
Lower heat to medium.
Simmer for 40 minutes or until soft.
Arrange on platter; garnish with green onions.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar and flour until well blended.
Add milk; mix well. Cook over low heat in heavy saucepan and stir continuously until mixture begins to thicken.
Beat egg yolks until well beaten and add to hot mixture.
Continue to stir until desired consistency. Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and margarine.
In a 9 x 13-inch dish, layer cookies, bananas and cooked mixture, repeating until all cookies, bananas and cooked mixture have been used.

title: turkey wild rice casserole
directions: Combine ingredients and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until heated through.

title: cool whip cookies
directions: Stir all together and drop by teaspoons on baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while warm, if desired.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease bottom of casserole.
Line with slightly crushed potato chips.
Mix the chicken, almonds, chestnuts, pimento, lemon juice, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and soup.
Pour this on top of chips. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Add some of potato chips (crushed) on cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly and cheese melts.

title: thousand island dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients, except eggs.
Blend well.
Add eggs. Chill and serve.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, oil, cinnamon, cloves and nutmeg together.
Add eggs and salt and mix well.
Then add water and pumpkin.
Next add flour and soda.
Mix well and pour into 3 greased and floured 1 pound coffee cans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: oatmeal apple cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Cream butter.
Add sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Finely chop nuts, apples and dates; add to first mixture.
Mix oatmeal, soda, baking powder and cinnamon with flour.
Add to first batter mixture; beat well.
Drop onto oiled cookie sheet in heaping teaspoonfuls.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes. Makes about 3 dozen.

title: eva st. clair's fruit salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add cold water.
Drain fruit, reserving 1 cup liquid.
Fold fruit into gelatin mixture. Pour into a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan or an 11 1/2 x 7 3/8 x 1 1/2-inch glass dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Unmold salad and frost with Fluffy Topping.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Refrigerate until topping sets, about 3 hours.
Makes 90 small servings.

title: lillian's blueberry nut crunch
directions: Lightly grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Spread undrained pineapple over bottom of pan.
Add the layer of blueberries. Sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar.
Sprinkle cake mix over fruit layer.
Drizzle melted butter over cake mix.
Top with a generous amount of pecans (1 to 2 cups) and sprinkle with 1/4 cup sugar for a crunchy glaze.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes. Take out cake and cut down through cake. Return to oven for 10 to 15 minutes until cake mix is done.

title: tortilla roll-ups
directions: Mix sour cream, onion and spices to taste.
Spread thinly on tortillas, leaving a 1-inch border on edge.
Roll up and refrigerate several hours in airtight container.
Toothpicks may be needed to keep tortillas rolled tight.
Slice or keep whole. Dip on hot sauce (picante sauce).

title: egg bread dressing
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and pour in well greased cast-iron skillet.
Bake at 450° until toothpick comes out clean in center. Cool bread; crumble bread in a large bowl.
Add onions and chicken broth until mushy.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and spread dressing in pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 minutes or until slightly browned, but not dried out.

title: party pink applesauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and bring to boil.
Lower heat and simmer until apples are barely tender.
Stir gently a few times while cooking.
Serve with whipped cream for dessert.

title: fresh pear pie
directions: Bake in a double crust for 30 to 40 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Microwave onion, garlic and oil in a 2-quart casserole on High for 2 to 3 minutes until tender.
Stir in chicken, chilies, broth and seasonings.
Microwave on High 4 minutes until thoroughly heated.
Add cream cheese; stir until melted.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto each tortilla.
Roll up.
Place seam side down in an 8-inch microwavable baking dish.
Microwave Velveeta and 1/4 cup tomato in bowl on High for 2 to 3 minutes, stirring after each minute until cheese is melted.
Pour sauce over tortillas.
Top with remaining tomato.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes until heated through, turning dish after 3 minutes.

title: planked carp
directions: Using charcoal briquettes, build a hot, hot fire.
Take 1 French filleted carp, season with salt and pepper.	Lay on a 16-inch long by 2-inch thick oak plank (no substitutions).

title: field's type chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
In a separate bowl, combine the flour, oats, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Mix all together.
Add the chocolate chips and pecans.
Roll into golf ball size balls and flatten slightly.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: rolls with flax seeds
directions: Put the yeast in the water with the syrup and oil.
Stir until the yeast is dissolved.
Mix salt, flax seeds and whole wheat, then add to yeast mixture.
Add most of the white flour (about 2 cups) but not all.
Then add the rest when kneading.
Knead the dough well until firm (about 5 minutes).
Put in a bowl and cover and let rise 30 to 45 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 5 minutes. Let cool.
Spread cream cheese, sour cream, mayonnaise and Ranch mix over rolls.
Add shredded cheese and raw vegetables you desire:
green pepper, celery, broccoli, carrots, radishes, cauliflower, etc.

title: doce de leite
directions: Mix milk and sugar in a large saucepan.
On medium heat, boil them for about 45 minutes.
Be careful because it spills out very easy.
Add baking soda and vanilla.
Mix for 15 minutes more until the color gets brown and the bubbles get bigger.
Use this as a topping for cake or ice cream.

title: bread in a jar
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Wrap a strip of foil around the rim of the jars. Grease inside of jars, but not the rim, set aside.

title: asparagus vinaigrette
directions: Mix vinegar with mustard, herbs, onions and pepper; blend well. Then blend in oil and finally the eggs.
Spoon over slightly chilled or room temperature asparagus.
Serves 6.

title: black bottoms(from debbie's kitchen)
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients.
Add the next 4.
Beat together until smooth, mixture will be thin.

title: broccoli casserole #1
directions: Mix all together except cheese and crackers.
Top with cheese and crackers; dot with butter.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 45 minutes, then cover for 5 minutes.

title: delicious oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add cottage cheese and eggs; mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Mix in oatmeal, raisins, nuts and vanilla until well blended.
Roll dough into balls; dip in sugar.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Let cool and enjoy!

title: applesauce cake
directions: Beat eggs, butter and sugar first, then fold in rest of ingredients.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour cake in.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cherry supreme
directions: Crush graham crackers.
Mix with melted butter.
Press into a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Prepare the Dream Whip.
Add sugar and cream cheese.
Mix well and pour over crust.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Keep in refrigerator.
You could also use blueberry pie filling.

title: lake shore casserole
directions: Cook meat for 1/4 to 1 hour.
Then mix all ingredients together.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Use the broth that you cooked meat in for the liquid.
You can use 1 can mushrooms and 1 can cream of chicken soup.

title: coconut cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening with sugar and flavorings until fluffy.
Add egg yolks.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately in small amounts with milk, beating well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry and fold into batter.
Pour into two greased pans and bake in moderate oven at 375° about 30 minutes.

title: pecan nut tassies
directions: Mix well with blender or hands until soft ball forms.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice, do not peel, the cucumbers.
Wash, peel and slice thin the onions.
Make brine of 9 cups of water to 1 cup salt and pour over cucumbers and onions.
Let stand for 3 hours. Rinse, drain and squeeze out all the water.
Combine the remaining ingredients and stir well.
Heat, but do not boil, for 1 hour.
Pack cucumber and onion slices in jars, pour syrup over them and seal.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar, milk and butter until it forms a soft ball when dropped in cold water, stirring to prevent scorching.
Add peanut butter, marshmallow cream and vanilla.
Mix thoroughly and pour at once into a buttered pan.
Cool and cut.

title: broccoli cheese fondue
directions: Melt Velveeta with cream of mushroom soup over low heat.
Add broccoli after it has been cooked and drained. Heat well and serve in fondue pot. Use for dipping vegetables, toasted bread chunks or pretzels.

title: cheesy hash browns
directions: Mix.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch dish.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat all ingredients well.
Pour into uncooked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Lower oven to 350° for 15 minutes.
Insert knife to test pie.
Clean knife and pie is cooked.

title: sunday chicken
directions: In medium bowl combine soups, butter and rice.
Add chicken. Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Season to taste. Bake at 275° for 2 1/2 hours or until chicken is tender.
Yummy and easy.

title: see's fudge
directions: In a saucepan, bring sugar and milk to a slow boil and boil for 10 minutes. Add marshmallow cream, then remaining ingredients. Beat until mixed.
Pour into buttered pan.
Refrigerate about 2 hours.
Cut into squares.

title: pear mincemeat pie
directions: Combine mincemeat, brown sugar, flour and pecans.
Spoon mixture in prepared pie shell.
Top with strips of pastry in weave fashion.
Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hot shrimp appetizers
directions: Mix together in a bowl butter, cheese spread and shrimp until spreading consistency.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Spread mixture on 12 muffin halves; place on sheet and freeze until firm.
Remove from freezer and cut each half into six wedges.

title: cheewios
directions: Pour butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan, the sprinkle dry cake mix over butter.
Layer over the cake mix in order: Cheerios, marshmallows, chocolate chips and condensed milk.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: cheese sticks
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Empty Bisquick into large bowl.
Stir in milk and beat until smooth. Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Spread evenly in prepared pan.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Cool in pan 10 minutes. Cut into 3 x 3/4-inch strips.
Makes about 3 dozen cheese sticks.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add taco seasoning.
Cut up lettuce in bowl.
Add meat, Western dressing and Thousand Island dressing. When ready to serve, add crushed taco chips.

title: eggnog special
directions: Put eggnog, ice cream, brandy and creme de cacao together. Blend lightly until thick and creamy.
Top with whipped cream and a touch of nutmeg.

title: coconut oatmeal cookies
directions: Toast oats and coconut in oven until golden brown (under broiler for a few seconds). Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs, milk and vanilla, beating well.

title: seashell macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Chill for 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: microwave choco-peanut clusters
directions: Combine morsels in 2-quart casserole.
Microwave on High 3 to 4 minutes until melted, stirring halfway through. Stir in peanuts. Drop by teaspoons onto waxed paper.
Let set until firm (or pop in the refrigerator, if in a hurry) and store in an airtight container.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together the night before serving.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Mix well.
Pour into pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: creamy cucumber dressing
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Keep refrigerated in an airtight container.
May be used as a salad or sandwich dressing or as a sauce for veggies.

title: canned okra
directions: Cook until the color changes and can. When opened to eat, drain, wash good, pour on towel and dry.
Add a little flour, meal, salt and pepper. Deep fry.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef and onion over medium heat until the meat is no longer pink; drain.
Add spaghetti sauce. Cover and simmer until heated through.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: barbara's fresh apple cake
directions: Mix the flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon in one bowl.
In another bowl, mix the oil, eggs and vanilla.
Combine the contents of both bowls and add the apples and nuts.
The dough will be very stiff!
Pour into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.
Let cake cool for 15 minutes, then turn cake out of pan.
Tried and true!

title: apricot bread
directions: Cover apricots with warm water and soak for 30 minutes.
Drain and grease a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Line with wax paper and grease paper.
Mix shortening, sugar and egg.
Stir in the water and orange juice.
Blend flour, liquids, nuts and apricots.
Pour batter into pan and let 20 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 75 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Remove wax paper and cool on rack.

title: baked custard
directions: Combine eggs and salt.
Slowly stir in slightly cooled milk, vanilla and sweetener.
Set 6 (6 ounce) custard cups in shallow pan on oven rack.
Pour hot water 1-inch deep around them.
Pour in custard.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted off center comes out clean.

title: no bake chambord balls
directions: Mix ingredients in order listed.
With damp hands, shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in additional sugar, cocoa or nuts (to coat). Store in airtight cool place.
Makes 36 balls.

title: black bean chili
directions: Cook ground beef, top round, celery and onion in a large pot until vegetables are tender.
Add peppers, cumin and salt. Simmer, uncovered, for 1 hour.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix jello with hot water.
Let set in refrigerator for a few minutes, then add pineapple and let it set.
In a bowl, mix cream cheese and pineapple juice together; add Cool Whip.
Mix together and fold into jello; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chop walnuts and sprinkle over top.
Refrigerate.

title: coney sauce
directions: Heat in skillet over medium flame; add 2 tablespoons oil. Add onion and cook, stirring until soft and translucent, about 5 minutes. Add ground beef; stir and cook until nicely brown. Stir in ketchup, chili powder and mustard. Simmer for 15 minutes, until thick. Season with salt and pepper. Serve on hot dogs.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Thoroughly cream oleo, peanut butter, sugars, egg and vanilla. Sift together dry ingredients; blend into creamed mixture.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place 2 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press five peanut halves atop each or crisscross with fork.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix together.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan that has been greased and floured.
Cover batter with 1/2 cup brown sugar; add 1/2 cup chopped nuts.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: frijoles charros de una gringa
directions: Dice hot dogs, ham and bacon into bite size pieces and put into large pot to cook (low heat).
Add stick of chorizo (may be purchased at jewel or Mexican grocery store).
Stir and cook until everything appears done.
(Bacon may not be brown and crisp but because of the temperature it will be done.)
To this, add diced tomato, onion and hot pepper and cook until onion is transparent. Add cilantro (leaves only), about 1/8 cup.

title: white trash
directions: In a large bowl mix cereal, raisins and peanuts.
Melt together the margarine, peanut butter and chocolate chips.
Pour over the cereal mixture and stir until coated.
Get a large (clean) paper bag.
Pour powdered sugar into bag.
Pour the cereal mixtures into bag and shake until well coated.
Can be made ahead of time and stored in airtight container.
Great for parties or showers.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spread evenly in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place chicken pieces on top and brush with melted butter.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325° to 350°.

title: quick chicken primavera
directions: Melt margarine in large skillet.
Add chicken and garlic. Cook and stir until chicken is no longer pink.
Add milk and pasta accents.
Cover and simmer 4 to 8 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: whole wheat dog biscuit
directions: Combine flour, wheat germ, garlic and salt in a large bowl. Cut in margarine.
Stir in beaten egg, molasses and milk.
Add enough water to mixture can be shaped into a ball.
Roll dough onto a floured board to a thickness of 1/2-inch.
Cut into shapes and place on a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and let cool.
Makes about 30 biscuits.

title: impossible pie
directions: Mix all in blender until thick.
Pour in large pie pan that has been well greased.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes its own crust.

title: jan bassett's egg nog(georgetown university)
directions: Separate egg whites from yolks.
Beat the yolks and add 1/2 cup of sugar to them.
(Save the egg whites for later.)
Mix half and half, brandy and rum into egg yolk mixture.
Set aside to "absorb" the liquor for about 12 hours.
Before you are ready to serve, beat the egg whites until fluffy and add the 1/4 cup of sugar.
Once these are beaten, they go on top of the egg yolk mixture.
Yields about 2 quarts.

title: caldereta
directions: Marinate beef in mixture of vinegar, peppercorns and garlic for 1 to 2 hours.
Drain vinegar.
Brown meat on all sides in hot oil; set aside.

title: mexican apple pie
directions: Combine sugar and water in a small saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until sugar is melted.
Set aside. Place butter in a 13 x 9-inch baking dish. Set aside. Combine apples and 2 teaspoons cinnamon, stirring to coat.
Place about 1/2 cup apple mixture down center of each tortilla.
Roll up and place, seam side down, in baking dish.
Pour sugar mixture over top of tortillas and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Uncover and bake 25 to 30 minutes longer.
Let stand 10 minutes. Serve warm with whipped cream sprinkled with additional cinnamon, if desired.

title: graham cracker pudding
directions: Heat milk and stir in marshmallows.
Stir carefully until dissolved.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour into a lightly greased pan and let cool.

title: sausage balls
directions: Have sausage and cheese at room temperature.
Combine and mix well.
Add paprika and biscuit mix; mix well.
Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
May be baked and frozen.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients reserving enough pecans to cover the ball.
Shape into ball.
Roll in finely chopped pecans.

title: crock-pot hamburger vegetable casserole
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Place vegetables in crock-pot in order given, seasoning each layer with salt and pepper.
Add ground beef.
Mix soup and 1 soup can of water in bowl.
Pour over ground beef.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours.
Yields 6 servings.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, celery, onions, dressing, salt and pepper. Toss well and chill until shortly before serving time, then add mayonnaise, blended with mustard and lemon juice.
Should be quite moist.
Serves 6.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Grate cheese.
Crumble sausage.
Add Bisquick mix.
Mix all together. Roll into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: soybean muffins
directions: Mix and sift dry ingredients.
Combine milk, beaten egg and shortening.
Gradually add to the flour mixture, stirring only enough to moisten.
Do not beat as batter should not be smooth. Fill greased muffin pans 2/3 full and bake in a 425° oven for about 15 minutes.
Chopped nuts may be added, if desired.

title: rotel cheese enchiladas
directions: Soften flour tortillas.
Fry ground meat.
Melt Velveeta cheese with Ro-Tel tomatoes.
Drain meat.
Add 3/4 cup water and enchiladas seasoning; simmer.

title: chess squares
directions: Mix cake mix, 1 egg and margarine.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and bake on cookie sheet 20 minutes at 350°.
Spread marshmallow cream on top while hot.
Mix powdered sugar, stick of butter (melted), and 1/3 cup cocoa.
Add vanilla and milk to make it spreadable.
Spread on top and add nuts.

title: bierocks
directions: Melt butter in milk.
Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Combine milk, dissolved yeast, sugar and salt with flour.
Use enough flour to make a fairly stiff dough.
Meanwhile, brown hamburger, salt and pepper to taste.
Drain.
Boil cabbage and onion in 1/2 cup water, just enough to soften.
Mix with hamburger.
Roll dough.
Cut into squares.
Fill each square with hamburger mixture and top with a piece of cheese.
Pull up sides and pinch together. Bake at 350° for 18 minutes.

title: leona's potatoes
directions: Layer ingredients; top with corn flakes.
Bake in a 9 x 13 -inch pan
at
for
minutes.
Best if fixed night before and refrigerated.

title: kindergarten banana bread(room 3, 1993 to 1994 voted number 3)
directions: Mash bananas (save).
Mix flour, soda and wheat germ.
Melt butter or margarine in pan.
Add eggs and apple juice concentrate. Fold in flour mixture and bananas.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 hour or put in cupcake papers and bake.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: dump cake
directions: Pour 2 cans pie filling in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle cake mix over pie filling.
Pour melted margarine on top.
Cook one hour at 350°.

title: emily's peanut butter rice krispie treats
directions: Bring sugar and Karo to a boil.
Boil 30 seconds.
Remove from heat and add Rice Krispies.
Press into lightly greased pan with wax paper.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In separate bowl, combine sugar, oil and eggs (beaten).
Combine flour mixture into sugar mixture.
Add bananas and mix.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes until fork comes out clean.

title: treasure toffee cake
directions: Combine cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar.
Combine remaining ingredients except nuts, candy and melted butter.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat at medium speed for three minutes.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Mix thoroughly the first 10 ingredients and refrigerate 2 hours.
Shape into balls and slowly brown in large skillet with oil.
Remove meatballs and keep warm.
Blend flour with paprika and 1/2 teaspoon salt into oil in skillet.
Cook over low heat, stirring until mixture is smooth and bubbly.
Remove from heat; stir in water.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Reduce heat and stir in sour cream until smooth. Add meatballs and heat thoroughly.

title: corn dogs
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Stir in cornmeal.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal. Mix egg and milk and stir into cornmeal mixture until blended. Insert wooden skewer into each hot dog.
Coat evenly with batter. Fry in deep heated oil (375°) until brown.
Drain on paper towels. Serve with catsup and mustard.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into a 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan or your favorite jello mold, sprayed lightly with cooking spray.
Cover and chill until firm.
Unmold on lettuce lined plate.
Serves 12.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolks, one at a time. Alternate milk with flour.
Add flavorings.
Beat egg whites and fold into batter.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs, milk and vanilla; beat until smooth. Sift all dry ingredients and add to mixture. Chill 10 minutes or more. Roll. Bake at 325° until brown.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes and cut in thin slices.
Put a layer in a buttered baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and flour.
Dot with butter.
Repeat, having no more than 3 layers.
Add milk until it can be seen through top layer.
Sprinkle top layer with salt, pepper and flour.
Dot with butter.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350° or until potatoes are brown on top.
If desired, sprinkle each layer with 1 teaspoon minced onion.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook zucchini and onion in a little water until almost tender, about 7 to 8 minutes.
Beat eggs, Beau Monde seasoning and dill together in a mixing bowl.
Add crumbs. Add drained zucchini and onion.
Add sour cream.
Melt butter and stir into the vegetable mixture.
Pour into a greased, shallow casserole dish.
Top with cheese and bake 30 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: crusty bread pudding with cinnamon sauce
directions: Tear bread in pieces and place in buttered shallow casserole. Mix together the eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and milk; pour over bread.
Dot with butter and sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake in pan of water at 400° for 10 minutes, then at 350° for 20 minutes or until puffed and brown.

title: stroganoff superb
directions: Cut meat into bite-size pieces.
In skillet cook and stir mushrooms and onion in butter until onion is tender; remove onion and mushrooms.
In same skillet brown meat lightly on both sides. Set aside 3/4 cup of bouillon and add remainder of bouillon, catsup, garlic and salt to skillet; stir to mix.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Blend reserved bouillon and the flour; stir into meat mixture.
Add mushrooms and onion.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in sour cream and heat.
Do not let it boil.
Serve over white rice.

title: christmas souffle
directions: Cook sausage and drain.
Cube bread.
Combine sausage and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a well greased, buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cover and refrigerate overnight. Cook 1 hour at 350°.

title: chili beef stew
directions: Brown stew beef, salt and pepper in butter.
Remove.

title: rabbit's apple cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and vanilla.
Add diced apples with skins, walnuts and raisins.
Grease, but do not flour, a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.
Does not need icing.

title: spicy stuffed mushrooms
directions: Remove stems from mushrooms; finely chop enough stems to measure 1/2 cup. Crumble sausage in large skillet; add chopped mushroom stems and onion. Cook until sausage is browned, stirring frequently. Drain excess fat. Stir in ketchup, bread crumbs and parsley. Fill each mushroom cap with sausage mixture. Place in 3-quart baking dish. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 12 to 15 minutes. Makes about 30 stuffed mushrooms.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Add ginger ale just before serving.

title: oriental chicken
directions: Fry the chicken in oil.
Use salt and pepper to season.
Brown the chicken, then add broth, soy sauce and brown sugar.
Cover and simmer over low heat 35 to 40 minutes.
Remove chicken and add cornstarch, sugar and cold water mixture to pan; stir until thick. Return chicken to pan.
Add green peppers, celery, onions and mandarin oranges, about 10 minutes before serving.
This is especially good over rice or Chinese noodles.

title: fruit salad
directions: Into large mixing bowl, combine the first 3 ingredients. Empty thawed strawberries on top of that, then sprinkle powdered pudding over all. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight. Stir in sliced bananas before serving.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Use to spread on Ritz crackers.

title: marble cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Add baking powder, vanilla, sugar and flour; mix.
Add milk slowly while mixing; mix well.
Take a small amount of batter (1 cup) and put into a small bowl.
Combine with approximately 3 tablespoons of instant chocolate Quik; mix well.
Pour 1/2 white batter into a greased and floured Bundt pan; pour chocolate batter on top, then pour remaining white batter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until it springs back.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: Cook fettucini according to package directions; drain.
Heat margarine and garlic in skillet on medium until garlic is lightly browned.
Add crab or substitute, evaporated skim milk and pepper. Heat about 3 minutes, or until mixture begins to bubble; stir occasionally.
Add Parmesan cheese; stir for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Toss seafood sauce with fettucini.
Serve immediately with additional Parmesan, if desired.
Makes four 1-cup servings.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Cook noodles until tender in salted boiling water.
Drain. Add corned beef, cheese, onions and soup mixed with milk.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and top with buttered crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: coffee cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into a greased and floured 8 or 9-inch pan. Sprinkle heavily with sugar.
This gives a crusty top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Best served when served warm.

title: hamburger hash
directions: Brown ground beef with onion.
Add chili powder, tomatoes and salt to meat.
Heat to boiling.
Place macaroni in casserole dish. Sprinkle green pepper over macaroni.
Pour in meat sauce mixture and mix well.
Bake, covered, for 20 minutes at 400°.
Uncover and stir.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven to melt.

title: chicken-vegetable pie
directions: Cook chicken; remove from bone.
Place in greased pan. Combine Veg-All and the 3 cans of soup.
Pour soup and Veg-All mixture over chicken.
Mix flour, milk and margarine; pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: frosty fizz punch
directions: Boil cranberries in 4 cups water until popped (approximately 10 minutes).
Stain through a fine sieve.
Add sugar, mix well and chill.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Mix thawed lemonade and Eagle Brand milk well.
Fold in Cool Whip and mix well.
Put in pie shells and chill.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease the baking dish.
Peel, core and section apples.
Put the apple sections in baking dish with 1/4 cup water in dish.
Put sugar, flour and cinnamon in a mixing bowl. Fill the measuring cup with water to the 1/2 cup mark; drop teaspoons of butter into the cup until the water rises to the 1 cup mark.
Pour off the water into the sink.
Drop the 1/2 cup butter into the bowl with dry ingredients.
Mix everything by hand.
Pack the mix firmly over the apple sections.
Bake 50 minutes.
Serve with cream or ice cream.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: hot dog cheesies
directions: Cook hot dogs.
Spread one slice of buttered bread with mustard, top with cheese slice.
Fold over to make triangle and hold with toothpick.
Brush with melted butter.
Place under broiler 4 to 5-inches for 2 minutes.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar, salt, egg yolks and milk.
Cook until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from stove and add margarine and vanilla.
Stir until margarine melts.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large bowl.
Add eggs, milk, oil and vanilla.
Beat at medium speed 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer; stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch or 3 (8-inch) layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.
Frost with buttercream frosting on cocoa can.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs, one at a time beating after each addition.
Mix flour, salt and soda.
Add alternately with the buttermilk.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place 1/2 of potatoes and onion in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Put soup, milk and pepper in blender for about 1 minute.
Pour 1/2 over first layer of potatoes and onion.
Alternate rest of ingredients.
Sprinkle with paprika and add 1 tablespoon of butter or margarine on top.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour, then uncover and bake for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients. Add melted butter to stuffing mix and line bottom of 9 x 13 dish or pan with this mixture.
Pour squash mixture over stuffing mixture. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly. Freezes well.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream eggs, oil and sugar.
Add flour, salt, soda, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Put in 2 bread loaf pans and bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: green vegetable salad
directions: In a large bowl, mix together the first 7 ingredients.
In a saucepan mix together the rest of the ingredients.
Cook over heat until mixture boils.
Cool completely before pouring over vegetable mixture.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain the broccoli.
Mix the next 4 ingredients together and add the drained broccoli.
Pour into casserole and top with grated cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Let stand to cool for a few minutes to set.

title: orange delight
directions: Drain unsweetened pineapple; mix well with cottage cheese, jello and pudding.
Lime jello may be substituted for orange.
Add Cool Whip.

title: anise candy
directions: Boil sugar, syrup, water and cream of tartar to 295° on candy thermometer.
Remove from heat and add anise and food coloring. Pour on greased cookie sheet.

title: cold tortillas
directions: Mix all ingredients and spread on flour tortillas.
Roll up like a jelly roll.
Slice 1-inch slanted, not straight across. Serve with picante sauce to dip in.

title: frosted banana bars(low-fat)
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Spray square 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Beat sugar, sour cream, margarine and egg whites in large bowl on low speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl occasionally.
Beat in bananas and vanilla on low speed 30 seconds.
Beat in flour, salt and baking soda on medium speed for 1 minute, scraping bowl occasionally.
Stir in nuts.

title: candy sweet potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes for 45 minutes.
Cool and skin.
Slice potatoes; set aside.
Mix in saucepan:
butter (melt first), sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and lemon juice.
Strain to make sauce; then dip potatoes in mixture.
Coat both sides 2 minutes.
Remove to platter.

title: cauliflower and broccoli
directions: Add cubed cheese, if desired.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill overnight.

title: veal rollatine
directions: Cut the veal into 8 slices.
Place them between sheets of wax paper and pound thin.
Sprinkle lightly with flour, shaking off any excess.
Spread the floured slices on a working surface. Brush one side with about 1/3 of the butter.
Chop garlic and parsley together.
Put the salt, pepper, garlic, parsley, Prosciutto, half of the cheese and 2 tablespoons of the butter in a bowl and mix well.
Spread 1 teaspoon of the mixture down the center of each veal slice.
Roll up each piece of veal and pin with a food pick.
Heat olive oil and remaining butter in a skillet.
Add the veal rolls and brown well on all sides.
Add the tomato, cover and cook slowly for about 25 minutes.
Serve in platter and sprinkle with remaining cheese and sauce.
Serves 4.

title: jennifer's lasagna
directions: In large skillet, brown meat.
Add onion and remaining spices; cook until brown.
Drain off grease.
Add canned tomatoes; cook or simmer for 45 minutes.
Drop noodles in boiling salted water; cook for 15 minutes.
Rinse and drain.
Place layer of noodles in large greased casserole dish.
Top with layer of meat sauce.
Top this with about 1/2 of each kind of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Put small amount of meat sauce on top for color.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Allow to set 10 to 15 minutes before cutting.

title: punch
directions: Any flavor Kool-Aid works well. You can also drop some sherbet into punch.

title: punch
directions: I use Sweet 'N Low in a lot of my cooking.

Did you know that 1/3 cup sugar equals 4 packets or 1 1/2 teaspoons bulk or 2 teaspoons liquid sugar substitute; 1/2 cup sugar equals 6 packets or 2 teaspoons bulk or 1 tablespoon sugar substitute; 1 cup sugar equals 12 packets or 4 teaspoons bulk or 2 tablespoons liquid sugar substitute.

title: brunswick stew
directions: Boil beef in water until done.
Remove from water.
Grind onions and potatoes; also grind beef.
Mix altogether in the water that beef was cooked in and cook all ingredients until done.

title: hot corn bread
directions: Follow directions on box.
Add picante sauce and cheeses. Bake as directed.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients; add other ingredients in order and mix thoroughly.
Bake in layer cake pans which have been greased and coated with flour.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: bobsled blueberry muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix flour, 1/3 cup sugar and baking powder in large bowl.
Beat egg in small bowl; add milk, oil and peel. Add to flour mixture, mixing just until moistened.
Fold in cream cheese and blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin pan, filling each cup 2/3 full.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Mix juice and 3 tablespoons sugar.
Brush on muffins; cool.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: shrimp rice
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Saute bell pepper and onions. Combine other ingredients with pepper and onion.
Place in dish and bake at 350° until rice is done.

title: swan coach house veggie slaw
directions: In a very large bowl, combine cabbage, carrots, squash, zucchini and red onion. Set aside.

title: croghan baloney
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate 24 hours.
Take out and mix well again.
Form into 2-inch diameter rolls (choose your own length).
Bake on a rack over a cookie sheet or broiler pan at 300° for 1 1/4 hours to allow fat to drip.

title: beef imperial
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper.
Pound meat cubes with mixture.
Brown meat in shortening.
Add water; cook until tender. Stir in soup and catsup.
Put into 2-quart casserole.
Top with Potato Puffs.

title: cole slaw
directions: Put in large mixing bowl by layers and set aside.

title: key lime cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients; beat 2 to 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 3 round, greased and floured cake pans.
Bake at 350 degrees approximately 25 minutes.

title: fruited acorn squash
directions: Cut squash in half and remove seeds.
Place squash, cut side down, in a jelly roll pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut each squash half into 2 pieces.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Mix ingredients.
Put in the oven at 450° for 1 hour.

title: hot and dill garlic pickles
directions: Bring vinegar, sugar and salt to a full boil.
Pour over cucumbers in packed jars.
In each jar place 1 garlic bulb, 1 dill and 1 hot pepper.
Seal at once.

title: baked potato salad
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and seasoning.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan, sprayed with Pam.
Top with bacon and if using, the olives. Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Cook broccoli and onion; drain.
Combine with cheese and undiluted soup.
Fold in cooked rice.
Bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 20 to 30 minutes.

title: texas chili soup
directions: Rinse, drain and chop the green chilies.
In 3-quart slow-cooker, combine all ingredients and 2 cups water.
Cover and cook on low for 4 hours or on high for 2 hours, until onions are tender.
Ladle evenly into 6 soup bowls.

title: pineapple cream cheese
directions: Blend all ingredients together.
Spread on bread.

title: seven-minute frosting
directions: In top of double boiler, combine egg whites, sugar, salt, water and syrup.
Put over boiling water and beat with electric mixer for 7 minutes until mixture will stand in stiff peaks.
Stir in vanilla.
Spread over layers.

title: overnight eggs
directions: Alternate bread and cheese in layers in buttered casserole dish.
Beat eggs, milk, dry mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: vinegar and oil dressing(16 ounces)
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender and blend at high speed for about 15 seconds.

title: ham and vegetable soup
directions: Place ham bone, chopped onion, minced garlic and salt and pepper in large stock pot and cover with water.
Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours until meat falls from bone.
Remove bone and meat from stock.
Allow meat to cool, then remove all fat, gristle and return only lean ham meat to soup stock.
Add tomatoes to stock and simmer approximately 1/2 hour.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer approximately 30 minutes to 1 hour.
May adjust garlic and other seasonings to taste.
May adjust choice of vegetables to taste.

title: polish pigeons (stuffed cabbage)
directions: Cook rice until done.
Mix egg, rice and hamburg.
Remove heart from cabbage and place cabbage in a pot of hot water.
Heat cabbage until leaves are pliable.
Remove from heat, cool slightly.

title: kelley's spaghetti(feeds 6 people)
directions: In large saucepan, combine sauce and tomatoes and sausage and let simmer on very low heat.
Brown hamburger, then put into sauce; stir.
Using grease from meat, saute mushrooms until soft. Put into sauce; stir.
Using same grease, saute onion, garlic cloves and parsley until soft.
Put into sauce; stir.
Cover sauce and keep simmering.
Stir occasionally.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole. Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 300°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries and pineapple.
Blend cream cheese with some cherry juice until smooth.
Add cherries and pineapple to cheese mixture.
Beat cream until stiff, adding 1/4 cup sugar.
Fold into first mixture.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over top.
Refrigerate overnight before serving.

title: sundae topping for ice cream
directions: Mix butter, light brown sugar, corn syrup, white marshmallows and Butter Buds in a saucepan over low heat.
Keep stirring until marshmallows melt and mixture comes to a boil.
Cook for about 1 minute.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli by directions on box.
Put in casserole dish. Slice cheese; add to broccoli.
Crumble crackers on top of cheese. Melt butter and pour on crackers.
Bake at 350° to 375° until cheese is bubbly.

title: spinach dip
directions: Cut out a large hole in the middle of the bread.
Thaw out spinach and squeeze out all water.
Mix mayonnaise, soup mix and sour cream together with spinach.
Put dip in the center of the bread.
Cut up pieces of the center of the bread and arrange around for dipping.
