title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Beat butter and shortening at medium speed about 2 minutes or until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat lightly.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan 10 to 15 minutes; remove from pan and let cool completely.

title: massa's restaurant's seafood gumbo
directions: *This mixture of ground sassafras and thyme thickens and gives a distinctive Creole flavor.

title: salisbury steaks
directions: Measure cornflakes before crumbling.
Add milk until flakes are soft.
Add to remaining ingredients and mix up in oblong patties.
Flour patties and brown in oil on both sides.
Lay in baking dish.
Add 1 can water to soup and pour over patties.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: sara's chop suey
directions: Roll cut-up steak in flour, salt and pepper.
Brown meat over medium heat.
Cut up onion and add to meat until onion is done. Add water.
Stir in soup and soy sauce, also 1/2 can of water.
Let simmer 10 minutes.
Add chop suey veggies and let simmer until hot. Serve over rice.

title: orange julius
directions: Put ingredients in blender.
Puree until ice cubes are dissolved.
Serve immediately.

title: corn salad
directions: Drain corn; chop peppers (cut seeds out if desired).
Add mayo, sour cream and chilies.
Add garlic salt to taste.
Stir. Add grated Cheddar cheese (enough to thicken).
Stir, then chill for 2 hours before serving.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan.
Mix in flour.
Add chicken broth and milk; cook until becomes a smooth sauce.
Add chicken to sauce and season with salt.
Heat mixture thoroughly and serve over rice, toast or biscuits.

title: baked apple butter
directions: Cook apples until mushy.
Strain apples into roasting pan. Add sugar, cinnamon to taste.
Bake in 350° to 375° oven until thick and dark.
Stir occasionally.

title: shrimp and brown rice salad
directions: Bring water to a boil in a medium saucepan; add rice and return to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and cook, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until water is absorbed, stirring occasionally. Spoon the rice into a colander and rinse under cold running water. Set aside.

title: cheese bites
directions: Cream the butter, then mix all ingredients.
Roll in balls and press with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: chocolate layer pie
directions: Cream until smooth.
Press into oblong dish.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour, soda and salt; set aside.
In large mixing bowl, cream the butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs.
Add flour mixture to creamed mixture.
Add chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes, just until edges turn brown.
Cool on cookie sheet for 5 minutes.
Remove and cool completely.

title: four bean salad
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix sugar, vinegar, oil and seasonings together.
Whisk "dressing" until sugar is melted and oil is well blended.
Pour over bean mixture. Mix well and refrigerate.
This recipe should be made 24 hours prior to eating.
If using frozen beans, use 1 cup of each bean type.
Makes approximately 9 cups, serves 12.

title: beef with sour cream
directions: Remove any fat and bone from meat.
Cut into small strips. Dredge in flour.
Using large skillet, quickly brown meat in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add onions, broth, thyme and liquid from the mushrooms.
Cover and simmer for 45 minutes or until meat is tender.
Add mushrooms and beans.
Cover and cook for 5 to 7 minutes.
Stir in sour cream.
Heat, but do not boil.
Add Gravy Master.
Serve over hot rice.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Remove from oven and cool.
Add brown sugar and spread in bottom of pan.
Spread ice cream over chex and add thin layer of chex on top.

title: watermelon sherbet
directions: In small saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over milk.
Stir over low heat until dissolved.
Place all ingredients in blender and blend on high speed for 30 seconds.
Pour into 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Cover and freeze overnight.

title: rumaki (polynesian appetizer)
directions: Cook chicken livers in butter and soy sauce.
Wrap chestnut half and piece of chicken liver with 1/2 slice of bacon.
Secure with food pick.
Marinate 1 hour in soy sauce.
Broil until bacon is crisp (about 15 minutes).
Turn once.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Cream oil, sugar, vanilla and eggs. Add flour, cinnamon, salt, soda, pecans and apples. Bake in tube pan at 300° for 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: fruit punch(serves 50)
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients in large container.
Place one cup of juice mixture into blender.
Add 5 bananas and blend.
Mix all together and pour into 5-quart container and freeze at least 24 hours.
Defrost in punch bowl at least 2 hours.

title: rick's jello salad
directions: Cream the cream cheese.
Dissolve jello in water.
Add to cream cheese.
Whip until smooth.
Let partially gel.
Mix remaining ingredients and allow to fully set.
Decorate with red cherries.

title: fat-free cheese cake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sour cream, sugar and vanilla and beat until well blended and smooth.
Add egg whites and beat on low until well blended.
Spray a 9-inch cake or pie pan with Pam. Sprinkle pan with graham cracker crumbs.
Pour cream cheese mixture into pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Let cool on rack and then refrigerate.
When chilled, cover cake with fruit pie filling or fresh fruit.
Serves 10.
Enjoy!

title: jingle bell salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup hot water.
Add strawberries; stir. Add pineapple and diced banana.
Pour half of mixture into an 8 x 8 x 2-inch dish.
Refrigerate until jello sets.
Spread sour cream on top.
Add remaining mixture.
Refrigerate for several hours. Cut into squares and serve.

title: caesar salad
directions: Rub bowl with garlic.
Allow a few pieces of garlic to remain in the bowl.
Mix oil, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper in the bowl.
Tear romaine lettuce into bite size pieces.
Toss the lettuce with the ingredients in the bowl.
Squeeze the lemon over the salad.
Toss.
Sprinkle with croutons and cheese.
Toss.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix together and bake in 2-quart baking dish 1 hour at 350°.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Slowly cook onion in oleo until tender.
Add all other ingredients.
Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour in freezer.
Add milk (whole or 2%) to fill line.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Combine cracker crumbs and 1/4 cup oleo together.
Saute onions and 2 tablespoons of oleo until tender, but not browned. Put onions into the pie shell.
Combine next 4 ingredients; mix well and pour over the onions.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve immediately in pie shaped servings.

title: yam casserole
directions: Combine flour, brown sugar, oats and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine.
Mix 1 cup of this mixture with yams and cranberries. Spread remaining mixture on top.
Bake 35 minutes at 350°.
Top with marshmallows and broil.

title: rice casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Mash tomatoes. Mix all ingredients, except cheese in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle top with cheese. Bake for 5 more minutes.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish.

title: bar-b-que chicken sauce
directions: Mix together and baste chicken.

title: chicken lasagna
directions: Melt margarine in medium saucepan. Add flour and stir 1 minute.
Do not brown. Add stock and milk. Stir until mixture comes to a boil.
Add garlic, salt, pepper and mushrooms. Continue to cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream and mayonnaise. Spray a 13 x 9-inch baking pan with Pam.
Layer half the noodles, half the chicken, half the sauce and half the cheese. Repeat layers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until bubbly.
Let rest 5 minutes before serving.

title: sweet lemon chicken
directions: Combine flour and salt.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture and brown in hot oil in large skillet.
Combine lemonade, water, sugar, catsup and vinegar.
Stir well and pour over chicken. Bring to a boil and reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 45 to 50 minutes until tender.
Remove chicken to serving platter and keep warm.
Measure pan drippings and add enough water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Combine cornstarch and 1 tablespoon cold water. Stirring until smooth, add cornstarch mixture to pan drippings and return to skillet to cook, stirring constantly until smooth and thick.
Serve over chicken with rice.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs and add all other ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into a well-greased 10-inch skillet or pan and bake at 400° for 30 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: barrack special
directions: Cook macaroni & cheese as directed on box. Add chicken, salsa and black olives. Place in a large greased casserole dish. Bake at 350 degrees until bubbly in middle. Use tortilla chips and additional olives to garnish.

title: tabouli(middle eastern salad)
directions: Pour boiling water over cracked wheat.
Cover and let stand for 20 minutes.
Add parsley, mint, onion, tomato and cucumbers; toss.
Combine lemon juice and olive oil.
Add to mixture.
Chill and serve on bed of lettuce.

title: fruit punch
directions: Combine juices, stir in ginger ale and add sherbet.

title: french corn bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl combine pancake mix, sugar, oleo, eggs, milk, baking powder and corn meal..
Mix and pour into 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: vanilla squares
directions: Combine ingredients and pour on cookie sheet. Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: camper's cocoa
directions: *May substitute 2 cups Nestle Quik for cocoa powder.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar and salt.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Pour in pie shell.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: chicken penne with veggies
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions. Meanwhile, pound chicken flat. In a bowl, combine Parmesan cheese and seasoning blend. Dip chicken in mixture; coat both sides evenly. Heat olive oil in a large pan over medium heat; add chicken. Cover and cook 3 minutes. Turn over and cook additional 2 minutes or until no longer pink in center. Cut into strips and set aside. Add tomatoes and veggies into the pan; simmer 2 minutes. Add cooked pasta and toss. Top with chicken strips. Sprinkle additional Seasoning blend and Parmesan cheese, if desired.

title: chicken-eggplant casserole
directions: Cut eggplant from shell.
Cook onion in butter.
Add to chicken, eggplant and tomatoes.
Cook 15 minutes over surface burner; then add egg and salt.
Fill shell with mixture (or put in dish).
Cover with buttered cracker crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: cheese and macaroni
directions: Boil noodles with cooking oil for about 30 minutes.
Mix boiled noodles, milk, flour, salt and 12 ounces grated cheese.
Stir well. Pour in a glass cooking dish.
Add 4 ounces of grated cheese on top of mixture.
Bake for about 30 minutes.
Serve hot!

title: ginny's drop sugar cookies
directions: Blend together the sugar, shortening and eggs.
Mix together flour, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
Mix together the dry ingredients and wet ingredients.
Alternate buttermilk with dry ingredients.
Drop onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with granulated sugar.
Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; drain.
Add mushroom soup and Cheez Whiz.
Stir in croutons.
Put in casserole dish.
Spread some Cheez Whiz on top.
Bake at
350° for 20 minutes or in microwave for 8 minutes.

title: chicken mexicana
directions: Mix soups, tomatoes, onion, chili powder and broth; heat thoroughly.
In large casserole dish, layer ingredients: chips (broken into pieces), chicken, soup mixture, then cheese.
Repeat, ending with cheese on top.
Bake at 400° about 30 minutes or until mixture is bubbly.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs.
Add cream of tartar, baking soda and flavoring, then flour.
Cover and chill dough 2 hours or overnight.
Make small balls.
Dip into cinnamon and sugar or sprinkles to match the holidays.
Place one dozen on each cookie sheet ungreased.
Will puff up and flatten when cool.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 10 dozen.

title: crispy herbed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.

Rinse chicken under cold running water. Pat dry. In a lightly greased shallow roasting pan, place chicken in a single layer. In a small bowl, combine flour, basil, thyme, salt, oregano, tarragon, paprika and pepper.
Sprinkle 2 tablespoons herb seasoned flour mixture on chicken.
Pour warm water down side of pan. Do not pour on chicken. Bake for 40 to 50 minutes or until tender, basting with pan juices occasionally.

title: pumpkin pecan bread
directions: Cream butter, sugars, eggs and pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients in bowl.
Add to creamed mixture.
Blend well.
Spoon into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 10 minutes or until wooden pick comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool on wire racks.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients, blending mixture as added.
Stir zucchini, nuts and raisins.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Pour mixture and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: old-fashioned strawberry shortcake
directions: Add extra teaspoons shortening and 1 1/2 teaspoons sugar to dry ingredients in the recipe of baking powder biscuit dough.
After mixing biscuit dough, turn it out on lightly floured board.
Put flour on your hands and knead dough lightly.
Roll dought into one large circle about 1 1/2-inches thick.
Bake as usual for biscuits. Meanwhile, wash, hull, crush berries.
Mix with sugar and let stand in warm place.
When shortcake is done, split and butter.
Put 1/2 the berries between the layers and put 1/2 on top.
If you have heavy cream, serve in pitcher at table.
Otherwise, whip the cream.
tags: recipe of baking powder biscuit dough

title: pineapple grapeade
directions: In pitcher, combine ingredients; mix well.
Chill. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: corned beef and cabbage
directions: In heavy pan, put oil.
Add cut up celery, green pepper and onion.
Saute about 5 minutes.
Add cut shredded cabbage.
Cook until tender.
Add can of corned beef.
Stir well.
Cook 2 minutes.
Add tomatoes.
Cook about 2 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: fruited honey chicken
directions: Marinate chicken in fruit juices and onion for 1 hour. Reserve marinade.
Brown both sides of all pieces in oil.
Place in a covered casserole and cover with marinade, plus the apple, raisin, apricots, prunes and honey.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Baste often.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Mix cookie mix according to directions.
Pat out cookie dough in bottom of deep dish pizza pan.
Sprinkle pecans over crust and bake.
Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar to spreading consistency.
Spread over crust.
Next, spread strawberry pie filling.
Slice and layer bananas.
Arrange pineapple rings over banana layer.
Put cherry in middle of each pineapple ring.
Chill until set, about 30 minutes.

title: hamburger and corn casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour in 2-quart greased casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk.
Cook over medium heat until it starts bubbling all over.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove from heat and add vanilla, cocoa, peanut butter and oats.
Mix real good.
Drop on wax paper.

title: broccoli casserole ii
directions: Cook onions and
celery
in oleo until tender, about 15 minutes. Remove from heat
and add remaining ingredients.
Mix together well and pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: french toast
directions: Break eggs into a dish and beat them well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat butter and oil in a frying pan.
It should be hot but not smoking.
Dip slices of bread in egg.
Let any extra egg drain back into dish.
Fry the bread slices on both sides until they are crisp and golden brown.
Eat French toast while it is hot with sugar sprinkled on top.
Yummy!

title: butterball biscuits
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Melt 1/2 cup butter.
Put 1 teaspoon into each of 12 pan cups.
Save the rest for later.
Sift and measure flour, baking powder and salt.
Add 1/3 cup softened butter.
Cut into flour mixture with pastry blender until pea size.
Stir in 3/4 cup milk with a fork.
Fill each muffin cup almost to top with dough.
Bake in preheated oven for 10 minutes. Spoon melted butter over each biscuit.
Bake 10 minutes more. "Serve piping hot with butter, jam or honey."

title: traditional cornbread dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Lightly grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish or pan.
Melt butter in skillet.
Saute celery and onion until tender (about 3 minutes).

title: chess cake
directions: Mix cake mix with the stick of butter (softened) and 2 eggs. Crumble in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and vanilla.
Spread on top of cake mix.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fruit cake
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in a pan and simmer for 20 minutes. Cool.
Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix the flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and cloves.
Mix all together.
Add nuts and red and green maraschino cherries. Grease and flour angel food cake pan. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Bring butter, Crisco, cocoa and water to boil in 2-quart pan. In large bowl combine sugar and regular flour.
Pour hot mixture over flour and beat well.
Add beaten eggs, soda, buttermilk and vanilla.

title: burrito pizza
directions: Place taco shell on microwave safe plate. Spread with refried beans and salsa. Sprinkle with cheese and top with second tortilla. Microwave on high for 1 1/4 minutes. Cut into wedges. Serve with additional salsa and shredded lettuce, if desired. makes 1 serving. Repeat for each serving.

title: spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and crumble in small pieces.
Add green pepper and celery to bacon drippings; saute.
Combine in baking dish the remaining ingredients.
Cheese is optional (American or Cheddar) sprinkled over top (grated cheese, 1 cup or more).
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake in greased and floured 8 x 8-inch pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chocolate oatrage snack bars
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate, for approximately 3 minutes or until well blended.
Spread in 8 x 8-inch microwave-safe dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Cook on High for 4 minutes and rotate dish.
Cook 4 to 5 minutes longer until top appears dry or bottom is even colored.
Cover with remaining bits and let stand 10 minutes.
Spread bits and cool completely.

title: butter coffee cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, pudding mix, oil and water.
Add the eggs, one at a time, vanilla and butter extract or flavoring.
Beat 6 to 8 minutes at high speed.
Mix the nuts, sugar and cinnamon. Sprinkle a little on the bottom of a well-greased Bundt pan.
Pour in the batter, layering it with the rest of the nut mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Cool 8 minutes.
Turn out of pan.

title: shrimp salad
directions: In extra large salad bowl:
Chop peppers, celery and eggs.
Add boiled and drained packages of tiny shell salad macaroni, small frozen shrimp, mayonnaise and sour cream.
To season, add generous amounts of celery salt, onion powder, pepper and a dash of garlic powder.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve cold.
Makes 1 large bowl of salad.

title: sour cream blueberry pie
directions: Stem berries and gently rinse.
Pat dry and set aside.
In a mixing bowl, blend together beaten eggs and sugar.
Fold in sour cream until mixed.
Fold in berries.
Pour mixture into pie shell; bake in preheated 325° oven for approximately 60 minutes, until pie is firm.
Serves 6.

title: apple crisp
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Grease square pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches. Place apple slices in pan.
Mix remaining ingredients thoroughly. Sprinkle over apples.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serve with ice cream or whipped cream.

title: chicken mozzarella
directions: Brush bottom of rectangular pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) with oil. Mix Parmesan cheese, Bisquick, seasoning, paprika and pepper; coat chicken.
Arrange, skin side down.
Bake 45 minutes at 425°. Divide chili sauce among breast halves.
Sprinkle with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake until melted.
Sprinkle with parsley, if desired.

title: best-ever chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Cream together the margarine and shortening.
Add sugar and eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and add vanilla.
Add alternately with milk to creamed mixture. Bake in tube or Bundt pan at 325° for about 80 minutes.
Cool. Frost with Fudge Icing.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Mix and pour over cake.
Bake at 350° (325° for glass pan) for approximately 40 to 50 minutes.

title: egg custard
directions: Beat sugar and cream together until smooth (not whipped).
Add eggs and 1 cup milk; beat until eggs are blended.
Add vanilla and 1/2 cup milk; mix.
Add melted margarine.
Pour into unbaked shell.
Bake at 375° until center does not shake and top is brown.

title: seasoned pretzels
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Break pretzels into bite-sized pieces in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Melt butter and pour on pretzels.
Sprinkle onion soup over pretzels and mix well.
Season with garlic salt and garlic powder as wanted.
Stir every 1/2 hour and add more spices, if needed.
Bake for 2 hours.
Great for a new and different snack.

title: marbled pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Combine gingersnap and graham cracker crumbs with powdered sugar and butter.
Toss to mix.
Press evenly onto bottom of 8-inch spring-form pan.
Bake at 350° for 5 minutes.
Cool.
In mixer bowl, beat cream cheese until smooth.
Gradually beat in sugar and beat until light.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Transfer 1 cup mixture to separate bowl and blend in pumpkin, cinnamon, ginger, nutmeg and liqueur.
Pour half of pumpkin mixture into prepared crust.
Top with half of cream cheese mixture.
Repeat layers using remaining pumpkin and cream cheese mixtures.
Using table knife, cut through layers with uplifting motion in 4 to 5 places to create marble effect.
Place on bake sheet and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Without opening oven door, let cake stand in turned-off oven 1 hour.
Remove from oven and cool, then chill.
Yields about 12 servings.

title: homemade bread
directions: Scald milk. Add sugar, salt and shortening. Set aside. Dissolve yeast in water. Stir in milk mixture. Add 3 cups flour. Beat until smooth. Add other 3 cups of flour. Turn dough out on floured board. Knead. Place in greased bowl; brush with melted shortening. Cover with clean towel; let rise in warm place until double in bulk, about 35 minutes. Punch down and divide in 2 parts. Shape into loaves and place in greased bread pans. Cover. Let rise until double. Bake in 350° oven for about 50 minutes or until golden brown.

title: noodle stroganoff
directions: Brown ground chuck with onions in large skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain.
Stir in next four ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Stir in noodles.
Simmer covered for 10 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in sour cream.
Do not boil after sour cream is added.

title: cinnamon applesauce jello or salad
directions: In a small bowl, add 1/2 cup boiling water to red hots.
Stir and let melt.
In a large bowl, add 2 cups boiling water to jello. Stir until dissolved and add cinnamon candy liquid.

title: florida orange bread
directions: Remove orange rind from oranges and cut into slivers.
Combine sugar and water with rind in pan.
Stir until sugar dissolves. Cook for 5 minutes.
Mixture should measure 1 1/2 cups.
Add butter and stir until melted.
Add orange juice and eggs.
Mix dry ingredients with orange juice mixture in a large bowl.
Batter will be lumpy.
Bake in greased loaf pan 1 hour and 15 minutes at 325° or in 4 small pans 45 minutes.

title: banana punch
directions: Dissolve sugar in water.
Add juices and bananas and stir well.
Pour banana mixture into milk cartons or other containers and freeze.
Remove from freezer 2 hours before serving.
Add lemon-lime drink.
Yields 6 dozen servings.

title: sour cream-raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a large loaf pan.
In a large bowl, stir together the sour cream and baking soda.
Set aside for 5 minutes.
Add the melted butter, sugar, eggs and raisins and whisk until blended.
Set aside.
In another bowl, stir together flour, baking powder, cinnamon and salt.
Add to sour cream; mix until blended.
Spread evenly in prepared pan. Stir together the cinnamon, brown sugar and walnuts.
Sprinkle over batter.
Bake for 65 to 75 minutes.
Cool 15 minutes.

title: cranberry chutney
directions: Combine water and honey in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Add cranberries and cook 5 minutes.
Add orange, berries, ginger and raisins.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add toasted nuts.
Pour into serving bowl and refrigerate.
Serving Size:
10. Preparation Time:

title: homemade pretzels
directions: Dissolve the yeast in warm water.
Next add salt and sugar. Blend in flour.
Knead dough until smooth.
Cut into small pieces. Roll in ropes and twist into shapes.
Place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Brush the pretzels with a beaten egg.
Finally, sprinkle with coarse salt.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple dip
directions: Mix cream cheese, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add cocktail peanuts.
Serve with apple slices that have been dipped in orange juice to keep color.

title: charlie's enchilada casserole
directions: For the topping, set aside sour cream, 1/2 cup of the grated cheese and 1/3 of the Doritos bag.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Stir with spoon and put in freezer container.
Freeze in hand cranked freezer.
Makes a gallon of ice cream.
Recipe may be tripled.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Blend together all ingredients.

title: senate restaurant bean soup
directions: Day 1:
Soak beans in a large bowl covered with water to a depth of 4 to 5-inches.
Let soak overnight.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown sausage, onion, green pepper and garlic; drain.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer uncovered 20 minutes.

title: mock sour cream
directions: Blend in blender.
One tablespoon equals 10 calories.

title: fruit and chicken salad
directions: Coarsely chop the chicken or turkey and the walnuts.
Cut the grapes in half.
Drain the pineapple and the oranges.
Combine all the ingredients together and chill before serving.

title: chicken fettuccine
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions; drain. In medium size skillet; cook and stir chicken and mushrooms until heated.
Add cream and heat (do not boil).
Toss together hot fettuccine, cream mixture, cheese, salt and pepper.
Serve immediately on warm platter.
Makes 6 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all but cornflakes and melted margarine.
Place in a large casserole dish.
Mix cornflakes with margarine and cover potatoes.
Bake covered for 1 hour at 325°.

title: mom's old time egg custard
directions: Line a 9-inch pan with crust.
Put in refrigerator.
Scald milk.
Blend eggs with salt and sugar.
Slowly pour milk into egg mixture, stirring well.
Add vanilla.
Pour into pan; dot with butter and sprinkle nutmeg over top.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until lightly firm.

title: simple doughnuts
directions: Mix ingredients; roll out on floured surface and cut with doughnut cutter.
Let rise 15 minutes; fry in deep, hot fat (375°) until brown.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Mix together; pour into crust.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: caramel pecan dream bars
directions: Mix well and press into a 9 x 13 pan.

title: chili
directions: Cook hamburger and onion together; drain off grease.
Heat your tomato sauce, chili beans, chili powder and water together, then add your hamburger and onions.
Let simmer for about 1 hour on low heat.
Cook spaghetti, then wash it off in cold water.
Add it last.

title: perfect white rice
directions: Bring water, butter and salt to a rolling boil.
Add rice; stir well.
Bring back to a rolling boil.
Cover and turn off. Don't peek for 12 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: jubilee jumbles cookies
directions: Mix thoroughly shortening and the 2 sugars and eggs.
Stir in the evaporated milk and vanilla, then stir in dry ingredients. Chill dough if too soft.
Drop by teaspoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: big red cake
directions: Make cake using directions on box.
Bake in a 13 x 9-inch sheet pan.
Cool 30 minutes.
Punch holes in cake.

title: avocado dip
directions: Mix ingredients in blender (spread in shallow dish) and refrigerate for 2 hours.
Before serving, top with tomatoes, salad olives, green onions and Cheddar cheese.
Serve with corn chips.

title: chinese salad
directions: Combine shrimp, oranges and onion in glass bowl.
Mix remaining ingredients, except lettuce leaves.
Pour over shrimp mixture and toss.
Refrigerate, covered, 2 to 4 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lamb chops deluxe
directions: Trim lamb chops; brown on both sides in hot olive oil.
Remove from skillet; pour off fat, leaving 3 tablespoons.
Add onion; cook until transparent.
Mix in flour, then apple juice, stirring constantly.
When boiling, lower heat.
Add soy sauce, sugar, chicken stock and mint.
Return chops to skillet; cover and cook very gently for 30 minutes, or until lamb chops are tender.

title: turkey-vegetable pasta salad
directions: Toss all ingredients.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate rum cake
directions: Mix first seven ingredients well.
Add chocolate chips and chopped nuts.
Stir well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Dust with powdered sugar.

title: sweet potato cobbler
directions: In a large saucepan, combine 1 to 2 cups water, salt, nutmeg, sugar and diced potatoes.
Bring to a boil; cover, reduce heat and simmer about 15 to 20 minutes or until potatoes are fork-tender. Pour mixture into a lightly greased 9 or 10-inch pan.

title: granny's chewy chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine flour, salt and soda in a small bowl.
In large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Gradually add flour mixture.
Stir in chocolate morsels and pecans.
Drop by teaspoonful (two inches apart) on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes about 8 dozen cookies.

title: stroganoff
directions: Cut steak into thin strips; dust with flour and pepper.
In large skillet, brown meat in butter.
Add sliced mushrooms, onion and garlic; brown lightly.
Stir in beef broth.
Cover, cook about 1 hour or until meat is tender, stirring now and then.
Gradually stir in sour cream.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.
Serve over cooked noodles.

title: super skillet pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt margarine in super skillet and brush on sides.
Sprinkle brown sugar in melted margarine.
Place pineapple rings, then cherries in middle of pineapple rings and sprinkle pecans on top. Add drained crushed pineapple.
Mix yellow cake mix, according to directions, except add pineapple juice in place of liquid the cake recipe calls for.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or a few minutes over, according to your oven.
Let cool for 15 minutes.
Place a large plate over skillet and dump.

title: fudgey chocolate torte
directions: Melt butter, stir in cocoa and 3/4 c. sugar.
Blend.
Cool 5 minutes.
Blend in almonds and flour.
Beat in egg yolks, one at a time.
Stir in water.
In bowl, beat egg whites until foamy. Gradually add remaining sugar, beating until soft peaks form. Fold chocolate mixture into egg whites.	Pour into greased and floured 9 inch layer pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove cake from pan and invert.
Use raspberry sauce or chocolate glaze. Garnish with raspberries and green leaves.

title: seafood fettucini
directions: In large pan, melt butter.
Stir in flour.
Gradually add half and half.
Stir until thickened.
Add Parmesan; cook and stir until smooth.
Fold in crab flakes.
Heat 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally.
Serve over fettucini.

title: apple snow-topping for gingerbread
directions: Place the egg white, sugar and grated apple all in a bowl; beat until it is the consistency of whipped cream.

title: soup bean casserole
directions: Fry ground beef in skillet with chopped onion, salt and pepper.
When beef is brown, add tomatoes and celery soup.
Mix well.
Then add soup beans to mixture.
Mix your own corn bread mix.
Put all the mixture in a baking dish.
Pour corn bread mix over beef mixture.
Bake at 375° until bread is done and brown.

title: make ahead spaghetti
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Combine cream cheese, cottage cheese and sour cream in food processor.
Blend until smooth. Fold in onions and green peppers.

title: cool whip pie
directions: Mix the Kool-Aid with the sweetened condensed milk.
Mix it with the Cool Whip.
Put it on the ready crust.
Put it in the refrigerator or freezer.
If refrigerator, an hour; if the freezer, a few minutes.

title: mom king's lemon cake
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in boiling water and cool.
Mix cake mix and oil and mix well.
Add lemon extract and eggs, beating well after each.
Add cool jello and mix well.
Bake in Bundt pan for 40 to 50 minutes at 325°.
Make holes in warm cake with fork for sauce.

title: candy cookie
directions: Mix together margarine and powdered sugar.
Add rest of ingredients.
Make 2 rolls.
Chill 4 hours.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Cut cookies 1/4-inch thick.

title: divinity
directions: Beat egg whites stiff. Mix Karo syrup and water; heat to soft-ball stage. Pour half of this syrup into beaten egg whites slowly. Heat rest of syrup to hard-ball stage and pour slowly into egg whites.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: cottage cheese potato salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Combine melted margarine and 1/4 cup fruit sweetener and spread evenly in 9-inch square or round pan.
Drain pineapple, reserving 1/4 cup juice.
Arrange pineapple rings in pan.
Arrange nuts around pineapple.
In a large bowl, combine 1/2 cup fruit sweetener and margarine.
Blend in slightly beaten eggs and vanilla.
Add reserved pineapple juice and milk.

title: bread pudding
directions: Melt margarine in a casserole dish.
Mix sugar, milk, eggs, vanilla and salt together.
Pour into casserole with margarine. Mix bread crumbs in and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until knife comes out clean.

title: peanut butter scratch sauce
directions: In a saucepan on low heat, melt butter.
Gradually stir in brown sugar, then milk.
Add peanut butter and cook, stirring constantly, until blended.
Serve warm.
Makes 2 1/2 cups.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time. Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Add sifted ingredients alternating with milk, then add vanilla flavoring.
Cook at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: beef 'n rice
directions: Remove labels from cans; send to school.
Put meat in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Pour soups over top.
Cover with foil; bake in slow oven (250° to 300°) or crock-pot for 3 hours.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: angel food dessert
directions: Bake angel food cake according to package directions.
Allow to cool.
Cut top off of cake and tunnel out middle.
Mix jello and boiling water.
Add strawberries to jello.
Add pieces of cake from tunnel.
Stir together and pour into tunnel.
Replace top of cake.
Frost top and sides with Cool Whip.
Chill.

title: banana nut bread(1 loaf)
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Add rolled oats.
Cream margarine and brown sugar.
Add bananas and orange extract, then eggs and walnuts.
Gradually add dry ingredients and stir just until blended.
Pour into well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until tested done.

title: cajun fish
directions: Mix 1/2 part mustard and 1/2 part Louisiana hot sauce together in a large bowl.
Mix 1/2 part cornmeal and 1/2 part cracker meal together in a large cake pan.
Add Tony Cachere Creole seasoning and black pepper to the meal mix per your taste preference, and mix together.
Roll fish into meal until they are completely covered by the meal.
Remember to sift meal frequently to remove lumps in meal.
Fry fish in peanut oil.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add unbeaten eggs.
Beat well. Add pineapple and vanilla.
Add flour, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix very little.
Drop by teaspoons onto a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes about 25 cookies.

title: ganni's sweet & sour slaw
directions: Coarsely grate cabbage by hand.
Add pepper and onion.	Bring first 6 ingredients to a boil.
Pour over vegetables.
Toss and chill.
Best if made a day ahead.

title: gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in egg and molasses.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Sift flour, salt, cloves, ginger and cinnamon together.
Add buttermilk and flour mixture alternately to creamed mixture, beating well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until tests done.

title: potato salad
directions: Peel potatoes and boil until well done, so they will be thick enough to mash.
Mash until smooth;
add salt, pepper and salad dressing and stir well.
Chop boiled eggs and fold in.
Serve warm or cold.

title: jello salad
directions: Drain crushed pineapple juice in bowl; mix together with sugar and boil.
Remove from heat.
Add Jell-O.
Take pineapple juice, cream cheese and Dream Whip (4 packages).
Mix Dream Whip according to box, then add juice and creamed cheese.
Mix well.
Fold in Jell-O mixture, then fold in 2 cups cold water.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.

title: prune cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Mix oil, sugar, eggs and prunes.
Add to flour, allspice and cinnamon.
Beat together.
Add nuts.
Cook in tube or Bundt pan for 1 hour.

title: angel food delight
directions: Mix egg yolks, sugar and lemon juice; cook until custard consistency.
Add milk; then dissolve gelatin in cold water and add to custard.
Beat egg whites and 1 cup sugar until stiff. Fold into custard.
Break up angel food cake into chunks and fill buttered glass dish with a layer of cake, then a layer of custard alternating until all is used.
Chill overnight.
Cut in squares and serve topped with whipped cream.

title: cheese wedges
directions: In small bowl thoroughly combine cheese, margarine and if desired hot sauce; spread each pita half with half of cheese mixture, covering entire surface of pita.
Set pita halves on baking sheet and broil until cheese is melted and lightly browned, 2 to 3 minutes.
Cut each half into 4 equal wedges and serve hot. Makes 2 servings, 4 wedges each.

title: rabbit chili
directions: Boil
rabbit
until almost done.
Take off the bone and grind or chop fine.
Brown rabbit, beef and onions until done. Drain fat, if any.
Add seasoning mix; stir until well blended on
low heat.
Add sauce, water and beans.	Salt and pepper to taste.
Add sugar.
Simmer
to
15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: sante fe chicken wings
directions: Cut wings at joints; discard wing tips.
In large recloseable plastic food bag, combine 2/3 cup picante sauce, ketchup, honey, cumin, chili powder and garlic.
Mix well.
Add chicken wings to marinade; seal bag and turn several times to coat.
Place bag in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Refrigerate, turning bag occasionally, at least 2 hours.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Mix rhubarb and sugar and let set 12 hours (or overnight). Mixture will make own liquid.
Bring to a boil.
Boil 5 minutes. While hot, stir in jello to dissolve.
Put in jars.
Seal with paraffin.

title: creamy vanilla frosting
directions: Combine flour, milk and vanilla in saucepan and cook until thickened, stirring frequently. Cool.

title: scrumptious rhubarb pie(here is another good rhubarb pie recipe.)
directions: In a large bowl, blend dry ingredients.
Add eggs and mix well.
Stir in rhubarb.
Place in unbaked pie shell and bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: lemonade cake
directions: Dissolve 1 small pkg. of lemon jello in 3/4 c. hot water and set aside.
Beat together the eggs and Wesson oil.
Add the cake mix and lemon flavoring and beat well.
Add jello mixture and mix well.
Bake in a tube pan at 300° for 1 hour.
While cake is baking, mix the frozen lemonade with the sugar.
When cake is done, run a knife around the edges to loose cake from pan, then pour lemonade over and down sides of cake.
Keep in pan until well cooled.

title: barbecued cocktail franks
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients, except frankfurters.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently.
Reduce heat. Add franks; simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with toothpicks.
Makes 32 appetizers.

title: coconut pie
directions: Melt oleo.
Beat eggs well.
Mix all ingredients well.
Pour in pie crust.
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: crescent triangles
directions: Separate rolls into triangles.
Combine cream cheese, egg yolk, flavoring, jam and sugar.
Place a tablespoon in center of each triangle.
Pull points of triangle together and pinch to seal.
Place on greased baking sheet and bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 375°.

title: play time dough
directions: Fill coffee mug with bottled water.
If you care for an exotic taste, use tap water.
Place full mug in microwave and microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Add 1 teabag (I prefer Lipton) and flavor to taste.

title: five bean casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Drain beans and put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole.
Brown sausage in skillet over medium heat. Remove sausage and drain grease, reserving a small amount in skillet.
Return skillet to heat and add onions and celery; cook, stirring occasionally.
When onions are transparent, add undiluted soup, mustard, sugar and chili powder.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Stir sausage and skillet mixture into beans.
Spread tomato paste over top and place bacon strips on top.
Bake 1 1/2 hours and serve hot.
Great at barbecues.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Spread into pie size plate and bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove and top with onions or scallions and tomato.
Serve while hot with crackers.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat salad oil and sugar together.
Add eggs and vanilla. Beat again; add chopped apples.
(Do not beat again after adding apples.)
Add flour, stir,
add baking soda, salt and cinnamon. Stir again.
Add 1 cup nuts; stir.
(Dough will be very thick.) Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle top with granulated sugar.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool.
May be served with whipped cream.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Break broccoli florets apart.
Cook and crumble bacon.
Whisk sugar, vinegar and mayonnaise together for dressing.
Combine broccoli, raisins, bacon and onion.
Add dressing just before serving.
Sprinkle with shredded carrot for color.

title: crumby chicken
directions: Mix bread crumbs, cheese, garlic salt and pepper in a bowl. Dip each piece of chicken in margarine, then roll in bread crumb mixture.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mincemeat
directions: Cook meat.
Drain.
Grind meat and apples in food grinder or blender.
If using a blender, alternate meat and apples and add cider.
When all ground, add remaining ingredients.
Cook again until raisins swell.
Cool and freeze in containers.
Use approximately 2 cups for one pie.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place boneless chicken on bottom of a pan.
Spread frozen vegetables over chicken.
Spread both cans of soup over vegetables.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.
Bake at 340° for 3/4 hour.

title: spinach with hot bacon dressing
directions: Wash spinach, discarding stems.
Pat dry on paper towel.
Tear into bowl.
Add onions and sprinkle with pepper; chill.
Slowly fry bacon until crisp-cooked.
Add vinegar, lemon juice, sugar and salt.
Pour over spinach.
Garnish on top with red onion, mushrooms and egg.
Serve Parmesan cheese on the side.
Serves 8 to 12 people.

title: cafe pecan pumpkin pie
directions: Makes 2 pies.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Line two 9-inch pie pans with wax paper.

title: fudge pie
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a 2-quart saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk and chocolates.
Stirring constantly,
cook over medium heat until mix thickens and bubbles.
Reduce heat.
Cook and stir for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Separate egg yolks from whites.
Beat yolks slightly.
Gradually stir 1 cup of hot filling into yolks.
Return this to hot filling in saucepan. Stirring, bring this to a gentle boil; remove from heat.
Stir in butter and vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and bake in a 350° oven for 15 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: ceviche
directions: Marinate fish in lime juice and Worcestershire for 24 hours in refrigerator.
Add other ingredients.
Marinate entire salad 24 hours before serving.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Mix in bananas, flour, soda and salt.
Grease pan; cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta.
Rinse with cold water and drain.
Let cool. Combine ingredients and then toss with Italian dressing and Parmesan cheese.
Cover and chill several hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: daddy's tater wedges
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Place wedges in the mixture and refrigerate overnight.
(Make sure potatoes are covered with batter or they will turn black.)
Cover with lid or plastic wrap. Drop wedges in heated oil for about 5 to 6 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cheese dip for nachos
directions: Stir all ingredients together and melt in slow cooker.
Serve warm with tortilla chips.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Beat together cream cheese and sugar.
Fold in pineapple, strawberries, bananas and Cool Whip.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix first 3 items and add the other ingredients in the order given.
Mix with water and turn on floured board and knead until smooth and pliant.
Put in a greased bowl and turn so it will be oiled on both sides.
Cover and put in a warm place until double in size.
Punch down; roll out and cut as desired.
Let rise again.
Bake in 450° oven.
Refrigerate the rest.
Take out the amount you need each day.
Keep covered.

title: snowballs
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
In double broiler, melt chips and wax.
Form into balls and chill. Stick toothpicks in balls and dip into chocolate wax mixture.
Watermelon scoop makes good balls.

title: v-8 juice
directions: Wash tomatoes; remove stems.
Cut into quarters (do not peel). Put through blender on liquify, adding carrots, celery and mangoes (can use other vegetables you may like).
After each blending, put through a sieve or strainer.
Pour into large kettle; bring to boil at least 20 minutes.
Skim top, then add salt, onion powder, celery salt, Worcestershire sauce, Tabasco sauce (optional) and sugar. Simmer to thickness, about 1/2 hour, and taste you desire.
Put in jars and seal.
Makes 10 or 12 quarts.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil noodles until soft; drain.
In a mixing bowl, whip eggs. Add package of powdered cheese from box, milk, grated cheese and noodles.
Pour into baking dish.
Sprinkle pepper and pats of butter on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: toasted butter pecan cake
directions: Toast pecans in 1/4 cup butter at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Stir frequently.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cream 1 cup butter.
Gradually add sugar, creaming well.
Blend in eggs; beat well after each addition.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients.
Blend well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and 1 1/3 cups pecans.
Turn into three 8 or 9-inch round layer pans, greased and floured on bottoms.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool and spread frosting between layers and on top.

title: ratatouille
directions: Quarter the eggplant; cut into 1/4-inch slices and cut the peppers in half.
Clean them out.
Cut into strips; quarter the tomatoes.
Heat up the olive oil in a pressure cooker; put in the sliced onions and put in the other ingredients.
Spice with salt and pepper; put on the lid.
Let cook for approximately 5 minutes. Stir in the pressed garlic and the parsley.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat sugar, eggs, margarine and vanilla with an electric mixer on high speed for about 15 minutes, until smooth. Melt 1 stick of margarine and mix with graham cracker crumbs. Press into a 9 x 13 pan. Spread mixture on top of graham cracker crumbs. Spread sliced bananas over top of mixture and drained crushed pineapple over bananas. Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts on top. Decorate with cherry halves. Chill.

title: mandarin orange salad *
directions: Mix Jell-O in boiling water and stir until dissolved.
Add pineapple and mandarin oranges, juice and all.
Add marshmallows and mix well. Pour into dish (11 x 7-inch).
Refrigerate.
When firm, spread Cool Whip over top, followed by cheese.
Serves 12.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Add sugar to apples.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix well with spoon.
Bake 45 minutes in a 350° oven in square pan.
Cool 10 minutes.

title: sauerkraut slaw
directions: Toss all ingredients together and let stand for 2 days in refrigerator.
Keeps well for two weeks.

title: easy barbecue sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic in margarine until tender. Add other ingredients and bring to a boil. Brush on any kind of meat during cooking.

title: camp stew
directions: Brown ground beef in butter; add soup and water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover; cook slowly for 15 minutes.
Serve with thick slices of garlic toast.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: chicken tortilla soup
directions: In a large saucepan, place 1 tablespoon oil and heat it on medium heat until it is hot.
Add the green onions and garlic and saute them for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add the cooked rice, chicken, chile peppers and chicken broth.
Cover and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add the lime juice, cilantro, salt and pepper.
Line soup bowls with tortilla chips.
Place cheese, tomatoes and avocado in center. Serve and add soup to bowls.

title: white christmas pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water, mix together in saucepan, sugar, flour, salt and milk.
Cook over low heat, stirring until boils. Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in gelatin.
Cool.
When partially set, beat with rotary beater until smooth.
Blend in vanilla and almond.
Gently fold in cream, whipped until stiff and carefully fold all in meringue of egg whites beaten stiff with sugar and cream of tartar.
Last, fold in 1 c. of coconut.
Pile into cooled baked pie shell.
Sprinkle with moist shredded coconut. Chill until set, about 2 hours.
Serve cold.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Cream together	margarine,
shortening	and
sugar; add eggs one at a time.
Beat
after each addition. Sift flour and baking powder
together. Add milk and flour alternately to the batter. Add
flavorings
and beat well.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: overnight coffee cake
directions: Put frozen rolls into a Bundt pan.
If using regular rolls cut up, fill the pan 1/2 full only.
Mix brown sugar and pudding mix together and sprinkle over the top of the rolls.
Pour melted butter over rolls/pudding mixture.
Let sit overnight where the dough can unthaw and raise.
(oven) In the morning bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Turn upside down on serving platter with sides.

title: peggy's mexican casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and 1/2 of chips. Place in 9 x 12-inch pan.
Top with cheese and remaining chips. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: cocoa frosting
directions: Bring margarine, milk and cocoa to a boil.
Remove from heat. Add confectioners sugar.
Beat until smooth.
Pour frosting over cake and garnish with nuts.

title: frozen grape dessert
directions: Clean grapes and divide into individual serving dishes. Freeze grapes in dishes until ready to serve.
Mix brandy and honey and drizzle over top of frozen grapes.

title: fettucine sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add cream (do not let boil).
Add Mozzarella cheese and stir until melted.
Add Parmesan and stir.
Pour over fettucini noodles and serve.

title: fried streaked salt pork with cream gravy
directions: Fry pork on medium heat until crisp.
Remove from pan and place on paper towel to absorb excess fat.
Leave 2 to 3 tablespoons of fat in pan.
Add flour to pan and stir until flour browns.
Add water, milk and pepper.
Stir until it boils and gravy thickens. Serve with hot biscuits and eggs for a delicious country breakfast.

title: crabmeat muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine crabmeat, cheese, lemon juice, garlic powder and margarine.

Mix until soft enough to spread. Turn oven on to 375° (broiler mode). Arrange muffins on cookie sheet and spread an even amount over each muffin half. Cut muffins into quarters. Cook muffins until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: sausage brunch
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan well.
Spread croutons in pan. Layer grated cheese over croutons.
Brown and drain the sausage (with salt and pepper to taste).
Layer sausage over cheese.
Beat well the eggs with the milk and dry mustard.
Pour over sausage. Refrigerate overnight.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: play dough
directions: Mix dry ingredients in a small saucepan.
Add oil and water. Cook on medium heat until mixture pulls away from side of pan. Add flavoring.
Pour on wax paper and knead food color into dough. Not edible.

title: mother's pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into an uncooked pie shell. Bake at 350° until firm.

title: strawberry pop cake
directions: Dissolve Jell-O and boiling water.
Add strawberry pop. Set aside.
Bake the yellow cake mix according to directions. Cool 10 minutes.
Punch
with
a fork all over so mixture can penetrate cake.
Pour
Jell-O
mixture over top.
Refrigerate overnight. Set
aside	and
make topping by mixing well until thick 1 package of vanilla	pudding and 1 1/2 cups milk.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over cake and refrigerate.

title: cheryl's mushroom barley soup
directions: Saute mushrooms, onions and green pepper in butter.
Blend in flour.
Cook until browned.
Slowly add milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add barley, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and parsley.
Bring to boil, then simmer, covered, for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar, baking soda and salt together.
Add eggs and fruit cocktail.
Mix well together.
Pour in greased 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: caramel parfait
directions: Place unopened can of milk in pan deep enough to cover can completely with water.
Bring to rolling boil.
Reduce heat to slow boil.
Add hot water to keep can covered.
Boil 3 hours. Remove from heat and cool.
Do not open can until completely cool.
Melt butter in large skillet; add coconut and pecans.
Cook to golden brown on medium heat, stirring constantly.
Set aside and cool.
Layer Parfait in glasses, vanilla wafer crumbs, caramel milk. pecans and coconut.
Top with Cool Whip.

title: gooey butter cake
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and beat 2 minutes.
Grease a large pan.
Pat dough on side of pan.
Beat powdered sugar, eggs and cream cheese.
Pour in middle of cake mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana punch
directions: Make syrup from sugar and water.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool.
Mix lemon juice and mashed bananas.
Pour both mixtures into punch bowl.
Add pineapple and orange juice.
Add sherbet just before serving.

title: molasses sugar cookies
directions: Melt
margarine;
let
cool.
Add
sugar,
molasses and eggs; beat
until
smooth.
Sift all dry ingredients together and mix with first mixture.
Chill until firm, then roll into balls.
Dip in	sugar.	Bake
in
a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes;
shorter time for softer cookies, longer time for harder cookies. Experiment with the times.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Prepare pudding using 3 cups of milk.
Then fold in Cool Whip.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine 3/4 cup of sugar with the cinnamon.
Put mixture in a paper bag.
Quarter the biscuits and shake in the mixture.
Place 1 can of biscuits in ungreased Bundt pan.
Add a layer of pecans and raisins.
Repeat 3 times.
Melt oleo and add 1 cup of sugar. Bring to a full boil.
Pour over the biscuit mixture.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in a 325° oven.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef chunks that have been dipped in flour in small amount of oil or margarine.
Add 2 cans soup and 1 can water. Cover and cook on low for about 2 1/2 hours.
Stir occasionally to avoid sticking.
Gravy will be thick and delicious.
Great with mashed potatoes or thick noodles.
Serves about 6.

title: ham loaf
directions: Soak bread crumbs in
milk
and
salt.
Add to meat and form a loaf. In a
saucepan
warm
cup tomato juice and 3 tablespoons brown sugar.
Pour
over loaf.
Bake at 275° until heated through, then 300° until done.

title: rockfish imperial(stuffed with crab)
directions: Remove skin from fillets in lengthwise manner; slit the tops, forming pouches.
Butter fillets and lightly salt and pepper. Set aside.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften.
Cream with a mixer.
Add Cool Whip and cream together.
Add other ingredients and fold together. This is good enough to be a dessert as well as a salad.

title: creole spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti in salted water and drain.
Chop vegetable protein food.
Saute onion and pepper in oil for a few minutes. Add vegetable protein food and brown.
Add tomatoes, spaghetti, salt and seasoning; cover and cook 15 to 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spinach salad with warm beet dressing
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Place bread on baking tray and toast, tossing occasionally, until crisp and golden, about 10 to 15 minutes. Set aside to cool. Place beets in saucepan and cover with cold water. Bring to a boil and cook until tender, about 30 minutes. Drain. Cool until able to handle, then peel and cut into 1/2-inch cubes. Set aside.

title: russian tea cakes
directions: In large bowl, combine first 4 ingredients on low speed of mixer about 1 minute; blend well.
Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup and level off.
Gradually add flour at low speed until just combined.
Stir in nuts.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls; place about 1 inch apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until firm to the touch, not brown (do not overbake).
While warm, roll in powdered sugar.
Cool.
Re-roll in powdered sugar before serving.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: buckeyes
directions: Put peanut butter, margarine and sugar into large bowl and blend together with hands.
Roll into balls and place on wax paper covered cookie sheet.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin together in double boiler.
Insert toothpick in each ball and dip in chocolate mixture.

title: chicken a la' orange
directions: Combine Stove Top with 3/4 cup orange juice.
Let stand.
Stir occasionally until liquid is absorbed (about 5 minutes).
Top each cutlet with stuffing.
Roll up and secure with toothpicks.
Roll lightly in flour.
Saute chicken rolls in oil and lightly brown in skillet.
Slowly add remaining orange juice and simmer for 7 minutes.
Add your vegetables and simmer another 3 minutes.

title: angel food cake squares
directions: Cut angel food cake into squares.
Dip each square in mixture of oleo, orange juice and powdered sugar.
Then roll in graham crackers and nuts.
Lay on wax paper until set.
Store in cool place.

title: chocolate crunch candy
directions: Combine milk powder and cocoa in a food processor or blender. Process or blend to a fine powder.
Stir into liquid fructose and water.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Slightly crush the chow mein noodles and fold them into the chocolate mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool to room temperature.

title: brisket
directions: Cover brisket with onion, salt and pepper.
Bake in a 450° oven for 1 hour.
Then add beef consomme and water.
Cover with foil tightly.
Turn oven down to 250° and cook for 2 hours.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut each biscuit into 4 pieces.
Melt butter.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and brown sugar in separate bowl.
Dip each piece of biscuit in butter, then in sugar mixture.
Layer in Bundt pan. Add nuts occasionally to pan on top of biscuits.
Top with extra sugar mixture and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Great for breakfast!

title: my favorite salad
directions: Combine dry jello, cottage cheese and pineapple.
Carefully stir in mandarin oranges.
Fold in whipped topping and refrigerate until serving time.
Easy and delicious.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Mix blueberries, sugar, butter and vanilla and spread in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex baking dish.
Mix the yellow cake mix with the pineapple and its juice.
Spread over the blueberries.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until browned.

title: zucchini marmalade
directions: Grate zucchini on small side of grater.
Chop fruit peels into small pieces.
Combine all ingredients except the box of pectin. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer for 30 minutes.
Add pectin and stirring constantly, boil for 7 minutes.
Reduce heat to low and keep warm while preparing into hot canning jars.
Makes 5 pints.

title: cheese and macaroni
directions: Cook thin spaghetti for about 15 minutes until done.
Drain. Pour into dish.
Combine a can of Carnation milk and grated Old English cheese and simmer until cheese is melted.
Pour over noodles and bake until melted thoroughly.
Delicious!

title: romas pink angel ring
directions: Dissolve jello and salt in boiling water; add berries and stir until thawed.
Chill until nearly all set.
Whip until fluffy, then fold in whipped cream.
Pour 1/3 of mixture in tube pan or ring mold.
Follow with 1/2 the cake (from which brown crumbs have been brushed), torn into pieces.
Add another third of the raspberry mixture, then remainder of cake and then the rest of the raspberry mixture.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and garnish with whipped cream (or frost it).
I double this to fill my Bundt pan.
Strawberries can be substituted.

title: toni holdroyd's apricot casserole
directions: Place in casserole:
Layer of apricots and some juice, layer of Ritz cheese crackers.
Continue until casserole is full.
Pour over this, mixture of melted butter, lemon juice and brown sugar. Cook on 350° until hot through and through.

title: maui onion spread
directions: Bake at 350° until bubbly (at least 30 minutes or more). Serve with favorite crackers.

title: spicy green beans
directions: Saute the onion in the margarine for about 5 minutes.
Add the herbs, spices and beer.
Bring to a boil and boil briskly for 3 minutes.
Add the beans and cook, uncovered, for about 15 to 20 minutes or until the liquid has almost evaporated.
Sprinkle with parsley and serve.

title: bread and butter pickles or zucchini
directions: Soak pickles or zucchini and onion slices in salt, topped with ice, overnight.
Drain and add remaining ingredients.
Cook 20 minutes.
Put in jar and seal.

title: onion casserole
directions: Saute peppers, onions and butter until soft.
Mix in pimento. Place 1/2 in greased 9 x 9-inch pan or similar round dish. Cover with 1/2 cup Swiss cheese and 1/2 cup crushed crackers.
Put in other half of onions and peppers.
Cover with 1/2 cup Swiss.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast and cut in chunks.
Mix all ingredients together.
Put in casserole and top with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed eggplant(serves 4)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Remove stalks from eggplant.
Put in large pan; cover with water.
Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Drain.
Cut in halves lengthwise.
Scoop out flesh and chop.
Place eggplant shells in a shallow, ovenproof dish.

title: mama's chocolate pie
directions: Mix dry ingredients in saucepan.
Beat egg yolks lightly.
Add milk, heating slow.
Gradually add to dry ingredients.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Put in baked pie shell.

title: orange sauce(wonderful on chicken or duck)
directions: Cook over low heat until thick and clear.

title: corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients except pimiento into a large enamel or stainless steel pan.
Cook over high heat and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 20 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in pimiento and pack into pint jars.
Seal immediately.
Yield:
3 pints.

title: brownies
directions: Variations:
Butterscotch Brownies:
Omit chocolate and substitute 1 cup brown sugar for the white sugar.
For added flavor, add 1/2 cup butterscotch bits.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Grind cheese and pimentos together. Mix with enough Miracle Whip for spreading consistency.

title: lemon dripple cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs one at a time, beating after each egg.
Alternate adding flour and buttermilk to which soda has been added.
Bake 1 hour and 12 minutes at 325°.

title: blueberry delight
directions: Mix jello with boiling water, then add cold water and rest of the ingredients.
Let congeal.

title: grandma ree's symphony of sloppy joes
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add remaining ingredients after draining grease and simmer on low heat for 30 minutes.
You can omit beef and use as a barbecue sauce.
Great with shredded pork.

title: apple cake
directions: In a well-buttered pan, place chopped apples into 1-inch deep. Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Dot with butter.
Mix ingredients together.
Mix into crumbles and spread over apples. Bake until golden brown in medium oven at 350°.
Serve warm or cold with ice cream, whipped cream, sauce or plain.

title: cran-apple sauce
directions: In a large saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes or until apples are tender.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Puree mixture in food processor.
Cover and refrigerate.
Yields 4 cups.

title: pina colada cake
directions: When using vanilla pudding, increase water to 3/4 cup and add 1 cup coconut to batter.
Blend cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, water, rum and oil in large mixing bowl.
Beat 4 minutes at medium speed of mixer.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Do not underbake.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes; remove and cool on racks.
Fill and frost with Pina Colada Frosting.

title: icing variation
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Blend well until spreading consistency.

title: mom's caramel cake frosting
directions: Cook together all ingredients except margarine and cook to soft ball stage.
Do not
beat until cooled.
Add margarine while cooling.
If frosting hardens
too quickly, add a little more milk.

title: five cup salad
directions: Mix together orange, grapes, coconut, miniature marshmallows and pineapple chunks.
Add English walnuts, if desired. Mix well with
Miracle Whip salad dressing and whip cream.

title: mexican salad
directions: Layer ingredients as listed in recipe.
Add the Fritos and dressing just before serving to keep the Fritos "crunchy".

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs and
1 1/2 sticks margarine in a 14 x 9 x 2 inch pan for crust.
Beat eggs, sugar and 1 1/2 sticks margarine for no less than 15 minutes. (Do not melt the margarine.)
Spread egg and sugar mixture over crust.
Cover with sliced bananas.
Arrange in layers the pineapple, cool whip and pecans.
Top with cherries and sprinkle with pecans.

title: cajun beef and rice
directions: Brown ground beef in skillet; drain.
Add the rice and sauce mix, water and chilies.
Cook over medium heat for 10 to 12 minutes.
Turn off heat; top with cheese.

title: chicken spaghetti rotel
directions: Cook chicken, butter, salt, and pepper until done.
Skin and debone chicken;
Chop in small pieces.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth then add other ingredients.
Cut cheese in small pieces, add to mixture, let melt.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Put in freezer. Add milk to freezing line.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or 12-cup Bundt pan.
Beat butter and cream cheese together in mixing bowl until well blended.
Add sugar to mixture and cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in vanilla.
Sift flour and salt together; blend into creamed mixture.
Spoon batter into pan.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool in pan 5 minutes.
Dust with confectioners sugar, if desired.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cut cabbage into six slices and cook in boiling, salted water for about 10 minutes or until tender-crisp.

title: lemon broiled fish
directions: Combine margarine and lemon juice.
In medium bowl combine bread crumbs, parsley and 1/4 cup of lemon mixture.
Dip fish into paprika mixture; broil until flakes with fork.
Top with bread crumb mixture.
Return to broiler; heat through.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes 4 servings.

title: candy yams
directions: Drain 1/2 juice out of can of yams.
Add sugar and oleo and cook until water is thick or very little water left.
Then add vanilla the last 10 minutes.
Cook on medium heat for 20 to 25 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and brown under broiler.

title: basic egg beaters
directions: In a blender, grind sunflower and sesame seeds with short burst at high speed.
Combine with remaining ingredients.
Place in a tightly covered jar and store in the refrigerator.

title: hot fudge topping
directions: Combine all of the ingredients in a medium sized saucepan. Cook over medium heat until it reaches boiling point.
Reduce heat to medium-high.
Stirring frequently, cook until soft ball stage. Serve over vanilla ice cream and enjoy!!

title: barley casserole
directions: Heat 2 tablespoons butter and saute in it briefly.
Transfer barley to heavy casserole.
Heat 2 more tablespoons butter and saute onion in it.
Add to barley.
Saute mushrooms in remaining butter and add to barley mixture.
Stir in hot consomme and salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, covered, stirring occasionally in 325° oven until barley is tender and has absorbed the consomme, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Makes about 6 servings.

title: southwestern gravy
directions: Whisk together oil and flour in large skillet. Cook over medium heat, whisking constantly, until brown, about 20 minutes. Add onions; cook 5 minutes. Stir in 2 cups hot water, tomatoes, tomato paste, tomatoes and chilies, Worcestershire sauce, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.

title: chili rellenos casserole
directions: Spray a 2-quart casserole with Pam.
Alternate layers of half of green chilies, Jack cheese, remaining chilies and Cheddar cheese.

title: italian meatballs
directions: Have ready a frying pan with enough oil to cover the bottom. Mix together thoroughly all ingredients.
Keep hands wet with cold water as you form the meat mixture into balls the size you desire. Heat oil in frypan on medium.
Place meatballs in oil and brown.
As meatballs are done, add to spaghetti sauce and simmer on low for 30 minutes.
Enjoy and think of me.

title: wild plum jelly pie
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Add eggs and mix.
Add jelly and vanilla; mix well.
Add melted butter and mix well.
Pour into unbaked crust.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until firm like a custard.

title: shrimp-rice-bean salad
directions: Cook rice, following package directions.
Drain and rinse. Place in medium-sized bowl.
Bring 4 cups water to boil in medium saucepan.
Add shrimp.
Simmer, uncovered, for 3 minutes or until shrimp is cooked through.
Drain.
Add along with beans to rice. Cool to room temperature.

title: stuffed chicken in pastry
directions: Saute sliced mushrooms and garlic in pan.
Pound chicken breasts flat 1/4-inch thick.
Mix mushrooms with cream cheese. Spread over pounded chicken breasts.
Roll breast, placing seam side down on pastry.
Cover entire breast with pastry.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover loosely with foil.
Bake at 350° in oven for 25 or 30 minutes.
Uncover the foil from pan.
Place in oven for 10 or 15 more minutes or until golden brown.

title: cornflake chicken
directions: Lightly grease bottom of baking dish.
Dip chicken in beaten eggs.
Roll chicken in cornflakes (both sides).
Line them in the baking dish.
Cover the chicken with creamy Italian dressing. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cover with foil for only the first 30 minutes.
Serve over rice or with noodles.

title: christmas eggnog
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a bowl or blender. Mix until smooth. Store in refrig. until time to serve. Pour into punch bowl and sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: original girl scout cookies
directions: Cream softened butter and sugar in large bowl.
Add eggs, milk and vanilla; mix well.
In separate bowl, mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add slowly to creamed mixture, mixing well after each addition.
Refrigerate for at least 2 hours.
When ready to bake, spoon out enough to roll out on pastry board, leaving rest in refrigerator.
Roll to 1/8-inch thickness and cut with cookie cutters.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Cool on wire rack. Let cookie sheet cool before putting fresh dough on it.

title: swiss eggplant
directions: Saute zucchini, eggplant and onion in oil and butter.
Add fresh vegetables, dill, mint and rest of ingredients.
Lay 4 slices of Swiss cheese on top.
Cover and cook on low until tender.

title: chicken-vegetable soup
directions: Combine all and bring to a boil, then simmer for 15 minutes. Yield: 7 cups, 81 calories and 2 grams of fat per cup.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Put butter in a bowl and pour boiling water over it.
Stir in sugar and salt.
Let stand until lukewarm.
Add eggs and yeast mixture.
Mix in flour, a cup at a time, until dough is stiff.
Knead it and turn into a greased bowl to rise until doubled.
Punch dough down and shape into balls to fill greased tins.
Cover and let rise again.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix spinach, eggs, bacon and bean sprouts in a large bowl. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over salad.

title: "jiffy" peanut clusters
directions: Mix in a saucepan all ingredients.
Cook and stir to a full boil.
Lower heat and keep stirring while mixture boils slowly 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in all at once 1 cup peanuts. Beat until candy starts to thicken.
Drop from teaspoon onto waxed paper to form clusters.
Using butterscotch makes delicious pralines.

title: strawberry jello cake
directions: Mix cake mix and gelatin in large mixing bowl.
In small bowl, combine, oil, water, eggs and strawberries.
Mix well, and add to dry mixture.
Blend to moisten, then beat well for 3 minutes. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes, until toothpick inserted in the center comes out clean.

title: koulourakia(greek coffee cookie)
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy in electric beater.
Beat in eggs and flavoring.
Add half the sifted dry ingredients and mix well.
Add water to mixture, together with remaining flour.
Knead slightly.
Pinch off pieces of dough and roll into pencil-thin strips, about 6 inches long.
Fold in half and twist into a rope. Place 1-inch apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: maybelle's yummy balls
directions: Mix all ingredients, except soup, well with hands. Shape into balls about size of golf ball. Pile into well oiled casserole. Pour soup mixture over meat balls.
Cover casserole.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour.

title: corn fritters
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Add eggs and milk; stir in corn.
Heat vegetable oil in pan or deep fryer.
Drop 1/8 cup batter into hot oil.
Do not crowd batter.
Fry 1 to 2 minutes on each side until brown.
Transfer fritters to tray lined with paper towels.
Serve warm.

title: diet chicken breasts
directions: Skin chicken breasts; sprinkle with salt and paprika.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Drain liquid from mushrooms into saucepan.
Add chicken bouillon cube; heat and stir until dissolved.
To the liquid, add mushrooms, Sauterne, onion, curry or oregano and pepper.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Uncover and bake 20 minutes longer. Serve with juice.
Serves 4.

title: cucumber lime mold
directions: Pour boiling water on gelatin in small bowl; stir until gelatin is dissolved.
Stir in mayonnaise with fork until smooth. Refrigerate until slightly thickened, but not set, about 20 minutes.
Stir in cucumber and onion; pour into 4 ounce mold or 6 ounce custard cup.
Refrigerate until firm, at least 2 hours. Unmold on spinach leaves.

title: sour cream raisin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook until thick.
Pour into a baked pie shell and top with meringue and nut meats, if desired.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Shape into ball.
Roll in chopped nuts.

title: buttermilk-less biscuits
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Mix milk and vinegar together and let stand until thickened (1 or 2 minutes).
Add oil. Stir dry mixture and liquid mixture together with a fork.
Make biscuits.
Cook in a 350° oven until done, about 30 to 35 minutes. Makes about 8 big biscuits.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine the apples, sugar, flour and cinnamon; toss to mix well.
Add the soda and salt.
Beat the eggs, vanilla and oil. The secret of this cake is to mix well and slowly so the flavor of the apples has a chance to soak in before baking.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and pour in your batter.
Flatten down with a spoon. The batter will be thick.
Bake in a 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread(hot)
directions: Mix all ingredients with milk (sweet or butter).
Bake at 425° for 30 minutes.

title: barbecued pork chops
directions: Mix sugar, salt, ginger, soy sauce, ketchup and peaches.
Line the pan with foil.
Lay pork chops in pan. Cover with sauce evenly.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Cover and chill. Serve with sliced fruit.

title: orange fluff salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add orange juice, crushed pineapple and part of the orange slices.
Save some slices for top.
Let set.

title: brown sugar ham steaks
