directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in a skillet until syrupy.
Add lemon juice.
Cook steaks in the mixture, covered, until thoroughly heated.
Drizzle pan drippings over steaks and serve.

title: date dainties
directions: When you have leftover dough from pies, roll the dough and cut into small circles.
Fill a pitted date with brown sugar.
Place pitted dates, sugar side down, on pastry circles. Wrap dough around date and place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: maine lobster stew
directions: Melt 3 tablespoons butter in a heavy saucepan and add lobster meat.
Simmer until both lobster and butter turn very red, about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add milk and cream.
Heat almost to boiling, but do not boil.
Chill for at least 2 hours.
Reheat stew in a double boiler.
Sprinkle with paprika and add remaining 1 tablespoon butter and pepper.
Serve with oyster crackers and pickles.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Set aside. Combine sugar, vinegar and oil in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring often.
Reduce heat and simmer until sugar dissolves.
Cool.
Pour sugar mixture over vegetables. Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Yields 8 cups.

title: oriental rice
directions: Drain water chestnuts and slice thin.
Saute lightly in small amount of butter in frying pan.
Combine in casserole soup, water, mushrooms and rice.
Add water chestnuts.
Stir and add 1/4 pound of butter, cut up into small pieces.
Bake 1 hour at 325°. Serves 6 to 8.

title: drunken meat balls
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Form into small meat balls.
Heat water, catsup and the beer in a saucepan. Carefully drop meat balls into the liquid.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve in a chafing dish.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cook onion in butter until tender.
Blend in flour and add milk.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add cheese and stir until melted.
Place layer of egg slices in a 10 x 6 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Cover with half of the cheese sauce, then half the chips and half the bacon.
Repeat layers.
Bake in a 350° preheated oven for about 30 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: baked pork chops with gravy
directions: Season pork chops and sprinkle with diced green onions and put in foil-lined baking pan.
Then add cream of mushroom soups after heated.
Put in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours or until chops are tender.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Saute onion in oleo, add brown sugar and bread and mix with tomatoes.
Add salt and pepper.
Bake 350°
for l hour.

title: buttermilk refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large mixing bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Stir in melted shortening.

title: virginia's blueberry cheese cake
directions: Mix cracker crumbs with oleo.
Whip Dream Whip and milk until stiff.
Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Combine Dream Whip mixture and cream cheese mixture together.
Take 1/2 of crumbs and pat good in a dish.
Add 1/2 of cream cheese.
Pour berries over cream cheese.
Add remaining cream cheese.
Top with remaining crumbs and chill.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Turn into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 350°. Remove cover and bake 30 minutes longer.
Makes 6 large servings.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Combine peanut butter, sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat at medium speed until creamy.
Add egg; beat until blended. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Add creamy mixture at low speed, just until blended.
Drop by teaspoon on ungreased pan. Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: pecan spread
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and milk, mixing until well blended.
Stir in dried beef, green pepper, onion flakes and seasonings; mix well.
Fold in sour cream.
Spoon into an 8-inch pie plate or small baking dish.
Heat and crisp pecans in melted butter and salt.
Sprinkle over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.

title: cornbread dressing for 25
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper in margarine until soft. Mix bread crumbs with all spices, salt and baking powder.
Beat eggs in mixer until light and foamy.
Add milk to eggs.
Mix together dry ingredients and sauteed vegetables.
Add milk-egg mixture.
Add broth until dressing is soupy.
Pour into baking pan and dribble melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; cut in Crisco.
Mix cranberries, orange peel, orange juice and egg.
Mix dry with wet.
Fold in nuts and cranberries.
Pour into loaf pans, 4 x 8-inch, 5 x 9-inch or 3 1/2 x 7 1/2-inches.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: breakfast treat
directions: Remove	crust
from
bread.
Butter
each
slice on one side. Layer bread, ham and cheese; end with bread; layer in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Beat eggs and milk.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Pour
over	bread, cheese and ham.	Cover with foil and refrigerate
overnight.
Bake
hour
and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna until almost tender.
While cooking, brown hamburger in saucepan; drain and add spaghetti sauce, green peppers and onion.
Heat thoroughly, then simmer on low until noodles are done.
Drain.
Put a tiny amount of sauce in bottom of baking dish so noodles don't stick.
Layer noodles, sauce and cheese.
Repeat until noodles are gone.
Bake in microwave 8 minutes or in oven at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: apple-banana shake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar. Add eggs and beat until fluffy. Add cocoa and red food color to mixture. Stir

together salt and flour and add to mixture alternately with milk. Add soda, vinegar and vanilla. Pour into greased and floured cake pans and bake at 325° for approximately 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean. Makes 3 layers.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush Oreos.
Put 1/2 of cookies on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Cream sugar and cream cheese first and then add milk, pudding and vanilla.
Spread over cookies in dish and add remaining Oreos.
Top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: holiday punch
directions: Heat juice.
Dissolve candy in juice.
Store in refrigerator. Heat as needed.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, egg, milk, stuffing mix, salt and pepper. Roll mixture into balls.
Brown meatballs and remove excess grease. Place meatballs in a baking dish.
Set aside.
Mix pineapple juice, molasses, barbecue sauce and flour.
Cook over low heat until mixture starts to thicken.
Pour over meatballs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: walnut caramel triangles
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Cut in margarine or butter until crumbly.
Press firmly on bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes or until lightly browned around edges.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Cube bread and place half of it in a well buttered 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
In a separate bowl, mix meat, Miracle Whip, celery, onion and pepper. Spread mixture over bread and put rest of bread on top.
Beat eggs slightly and add milk, salt and pepper to taste.
Pour over mixture. Cover with foil and place in refrigerator several hours or overnight.
Take foil off and bake in a 325° oven for 15 minutes. Remove foil and spread mushroom soup over the top, then grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: gourmet fava salad
directions: Drain and rinse fava beans.
Place in bowl.
Cut onion into strips; mix with beans.
Add oil, oregano and salt.

title: spinach stuffed sole fillets
directions: Melt butter in saucepan; stir in flour, salt and paprika. Gradually add the half and half.
Cook and stir over medium heat until thickened.
Add 1/2 cup of cheese, lemon peel and juice and stir until cheese melts.
Add 1/3 cup cheese sauce to cooked spinach and green onion.
Stir to blend.
Place some spinach mixture on each fish fillet and roll up.
Place seam side down in shallow baking dish.
Spoon remaining cheese sauce over fish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes until fish flakes easily with a fork.
Garnish with additional slices of green onion.
Serve fish rolls with rice and top with remaining cheese sauce.
Serves 6.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all ingredients reserving 3/4 cup nuts.
Shape into ball. Roll in the remaining nuts.
Chill until firm.

title: decorator frosting
directions: Measure all ingredients into large bowl.
Beat at normal speed for 3 minutes, then on high speed for 2 minutes.
Add more sugar to thicken or more water to thin.
Makes 3 1/4 cups.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Melt butter; stir in chopped pretzels and 1/2 cup sugar. Place in oven and bake for 3 to 5 minutes.
Cream 1/3 cup sugar and cream cheese.
Add crushed pineapple and baked ingredients (when cooled) together.
Combine Cool Whip and pecans with mixture and place in bowl.
Cool in refrigerator.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients; place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Freezes well.

title: clam dip
directions: Soften cream cheese; add the drained clams and picante sauce. Mix thoroughly.
Chill.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: two cheese broccoli
directions: Beat together first 5 ingredients.
Add broccoli.
Pour the mixture into greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: fruity punch
directions: Combine 2 cups of the water and 1 1/2 cups sugar in a medium saucepan. Bring to a boil. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Cool, then stir in 6 cups water and fruit juices. Freeze 8 hours (at least), stirring twice during freezing process.
Remove from freezer 30 minutes before serving, breaking into small pieces. Stir in ginger ale and serve. Makes 5 quarts.

title: french onion soup
directions: In large covered saucepan, cook onions in butter over low heat for about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Then add beef consomme and water until it boils.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer for about 30 minutes.
Place toast in each bowl and then pour hot soup over toast.
Lay cheese across top of bowl and place in a 350° oven for about 5 minutes.

title: wrapped chicken breasts
directions: Arrange dried beef in bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch pan. Pound chicken breasts with meat pounder and roll up and wrap in 1 slice of bacon.
Secure with toothpick and place over dried beef. Top with sliced mushrooms.
Combine sour cream and soup and pour over chicken.

title: chicken macaroni casserole
directions: Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350° in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: honey candy rolls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Add more peanuts if desired. Crush the peanuts first.
Roll in bite size balls and chill.
May be rolled in sunflower seeds or coconut.

title: mom's butter tarts
directions: Mix all ingredients (except tart shells) and pour into unbaked tart shells.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until shells are golden brown.

title: red lobster biscuits
directions: Mix all together and spoon onto cookie sheet.
Brush top with garlic powder before and after baking.
Bake on 425° until slightly brown.

title: aunt hazel's texas hot wiener sauce
directions: Combine all in 5-quart Dutch oven.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Serve on hot dogs.

title: cranberry marble salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Stir in pineapple.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in cranberry sauce.
Spoon into 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Spoon sour cream atop.
Chill until firm.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: poor man's pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: pineapple slaw
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix until coated with mayonnaise. Chill and serve on lettuce.
Yields 1 serving.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, butter, oil and vanilla.
Set aside. Mix together the flour, soda, salt, cream of tartar, then add this to sugar mixture.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll into balls, size of walnuts.
Flatten with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake on cookie sheet at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: easy stroganoff
directions: Cook oil,
beef and onion until onion is tender.
Drain off excess fat.
Add bouillon and Worcestershire sauce.
Bring to a boil,
reduce
heat
and simmer, covered, for 1 hour, or until meat
is
tender.
Add
mushrooms with liquid.
Combine sour cream
and	flour;	blend
into
meat mixture.
Continue cooking, stirring
occasionally, until thickened.
Serve over hot noodles. Serves 6.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Roll into small balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 30 minutes at 325°.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen.

title: pralines
directions: Boil to soft boil stage on candy thermometer.
Add the pecans and stir. Drop by spoonful on waxed paper. (This recipe can be cooked in the microwave.)

title: spinach lasagna(healthy recipe)
directions: Combine spinach, Ricotta, salt, pepper and nutmeg; mix well. Spoon 1/3 into baking dish.
Cover with 1/3 of the tomatoes and 1/3 of the Mozzarella; repeat twice.
Sprinkle with Parmesan. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.
Serve as is or put under broiler, about 4 inches from
heat source for 2 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Makes 2 luncheon servings.

title: chicken crunch
directions: Mix together in order given.
Pour into casserole.
Top with 1/2 cup sliced almonds.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: spritz cookies
directions: Cream the butter.
Add sugar and egg and mix well.
Add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Lay out dough and cut into shapes.
Add food coloring for color.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: hot dip
directions: Beat ingredients with mixer.
Put into Pyrex dish, sprinkle with chopped nuts.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve on crackers.

title: easy fantasy fudge
directions: Mix margarine, sugar and milk in a heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Stir constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes on medium heat.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased pan.
Do not refrigerate.
Make on a clear day.

title: sawdust salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water and then add cold water.
When starts to thicken, add crushed pineapple, drained, bananas and marshmallows.
Let set.
Mix pineapple juice, sugar, flour and egg; boil until thick and cool.
Put on jello.
Mix Cool Whip and cream cheese.
Spread on top of pudding.
Top with grated sharp cheese.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Beat the eggs in a 2 or 3-quart casserole dish.
Add milk to beaten eggs and mix together.
Add macaroni and cheese to milk and stir all ingredients together.
Put butter or margarine on top and bake at 375° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: cocoa apple cake
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, margarine and water until fluffy. Sift together flour, cocoa, soda, cinnamon and allspice.
Add to creamed mixture and mix well.
Fold in nuts, chocolate, apples and vanilla until evenly distributed.
Spoon into greased and floured 10-inch loose bottom tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 70 minutes until cake tests done.
Makes 1 cake.
Yields 10 servings.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Combine all ingredients except almonds in a saucepan and cook until cranberries pop open, about 10 minutes. Skim the foam from the surface; add the almonds and cool.
Makes about 4 cups.
Great gift idea!

title: grandmother pearson's world famous pumpkin bread
directions: Add oil to sugar and blend.
Stir in beaten eggs and pumpkin. Sift together and add flour, salt, baking powder, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and baking soda.

title: boston baked beans
directions: Put beans into a deep kettle.
Cover with water; bring to a boil and boil for 2 minutes.
Remove from heat; let stand 1 hour. Return to heat; cook for 5 minutes, or until skin splits.
Drain; reserve the water.
Cover the salt pork with boiling water; let stand for 5 minutes.
Drain the water; save it to put in beans. Cut salt pork.
Put the beans in the bean pot.
Press the pork into the beans.
Mix salt, molasses and mustard.
Add 1 cup of the reserved water; bring to a boil.
Pour this mixture over the beans and pork.
Add enough water to cover beans.
Cover pot.
Bake at 250° for 6 to 8 hours.

title: pottsfield pickles
directions: Add spices, sugar and vinegar.
Cook until thick.
Process in jars for 10 minutes.

title: spicy baked corn
directions: Melt oleo in a large baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients in a bowl and pour into the baking dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tomato aspic
directions: Sprinkle
gelatine on 1/2 cup of tomato juice.
Place on low heat, stir until gelatine dissolves.
Remove from heat and add remaining
tomato
juice and seasonings.
Pour into a 2 cup mold or
individual
molds, chill until firm.
Unmold on salad plate, garnish
with
cucumbers
and
black olives.
Enjoy, 33 calories per serving.

title: southern spiced tea
directions: When water boils, put in cinnamon and boil 10 minutes.
Add tea and let stand for 5 minutes.
Make a syrup by boiling sugar, 1 cup water and cloves.
When mixture thickens, add to tea and juices.
Add 1 cup cold water.
Serve cold with ice cubes or serve hot.

title: easy jello salad
directions: Combine cottage cheese, oranges, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Sprinkle dry Jell-O over mixture and stir thoroughly.
Can be used immediately or refrigerate and use when desired.

title: honey barbecue chicken
directions: Place chicken, skin side down, in an ungreased 13 X 9 X 2 baking dish. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Combine the remaining ingredients; pour over chicken. Bake, uncovered, at 375 degrees for 30 minutes. Turn chicken and bake 20 minutes longer or until chicken juices run clear, basting occasionally. Yield: 8 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Saute onions and peppers.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Place the ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon jelly filling
directions: In saucepan, heat orange juice, butter and lemon juice. Add sugar and
flour.
Let this boil well, then cool.
Add egg beaten with sugar;
return
to heat and cook until thick.
Add marshmallows and cook
until thick.
Use to spread on cake for filling.

title: ultimate chocolate malt
directions: In blender container combine milk, chocolate syrup and malted milk powder.
Cover; blend 10 seconds.
Add ice cream; cover and blend until smooth.
Pour into glasses and serve immediately. Makes 3 3/4 cups.

title: snow cake
directions: In a large
bowl
of
your electric mixer, whip the egg whites until
frothy.
With
mixer at highest speed, gradually add the sugar
and beat until mixture will stand in stiff, but not dry, peaks.
Then
beat	in
the
salt
and vanilla.
Sift flour; measure,
then
sift again with baking powder into the egg whites, folding
until
well blended.
Fold in melted and cooled butter until
evenly
blended
and turn mixture into a tube-type cake pan
that
is
well-greased
and
dusted
with powdered sugar. Bake
at
for
one
hour
or until cake bounces back	when touched lightly.
Remove from pan and cool. Dust well with powdered sugar before serving.

title: bourbon pennies
directions: Combine all in saucepan or crock-pot.
Bring to boil.
Cover. Lower heat and simmer 1 hour.
To serve, place in ovenproof dish over candle warmer or keep in crock-pot.
Yields about 10 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
Mix squash, 1/2 bread crumbs, salt and pepper.
Add sugar, onion, margarine, eggs and milk.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cover with remaining bread crumbs and cheese.
Bake until cheese is bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.
Equals 1 serving vegetable, 1/2 bread, 1 fat serving, 1/4 milk, 2 protein, 1/2 egg and 1 1/2 ounces cheese.

title: pickled okra
directions: Clean and wash okra.
Rinse well and place in a large colander to drain.
Pack okra in vertical order into pint or 1/2 pint jars, adding 1 or 2 hot peppers, raw onion and garlic as desired. Sprinkle mustard seed in each jar.
Make brine of water, vinegar and salt, adding pickling spice, if desired.
Heat to boiling. Pour over raw okra and seasonings.
Seal and let stand 3 to 4 weeks.

title: sausage balls
directions: Let sausage and cheese get soft.
Mix well with Bisquick. Form into small balls.
Place in pan.
Bake until brown, about 30 minutes at 400°.

title: casserole espanol
directions: In large skillet, brown sausage, breaking it into small chunks.
Remove sausage with slotted spoon; set aside.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon fat.
Add onion and garlic; saute until onion is tender.
Stir in beans, sausage, water and 1/2 chili powder.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water for 8 to 10 minutes; drain.
As macaroni is cooking, grate cheese.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Layer macaroni and cheese; dot with butter. Pour milk over top.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: fish and rice for four
directions: In 12 x 8 x 2-inch glass baking dish, combine rice, carrots, celery, 1 tablespoon butter, bouillon, lemon peel and poultry seasoning; stir in boiling water.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Remove from oven; stir.
Arrange fish over rice. Sprinkle with lemon juice, paprika and salt to taste and dot with remaining butter.
Bake, covered, for 25 minutes or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Garnish with lemon wedges and parsley.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix oleo, molasses, sugar and eggs; beat well. Add dry ingredients; mix until all ingredients are moistened. If dough is not stiff enough, add more flour (dough gets firmer when cold). Refrigerate the dough several hours or overnight. Make into small balls and roll in granulated sugar. Do not flatten. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes in 375° oven. Store in airtight container. They freeze real well.

title: savory pot roast
directions: In a heavy pan or skillet in hot oil, brown roast on all sides.
Spoon off fat.
Stir in mushroom soup, onion soup mix and 1 cup of water; reduce heat to low and cover.
Simmer 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Turn occasionally.
Add vegetables.
Cover and cook 40 minutes or until roast and vegetables are fork-tender. Remove roast and vegetables onto platter.
Over medium heat, cook sauce until slightly thick.
In a cup, stir together the flour and 1/4 cup of water until smooth.
Gradually stir into sauce mixture, stirring constantly until thick.
Serve with roast.
Serves 8.

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Combine 2 cups flour, yeast and 1 1/4 teaspoons sugar substitute in a large bowl.
Combine milk, 1/3 cup margarine and salt in a small saucepan; heat until mixture reaches 120° to 130°. Add liquid mixture to flour mixture.
Add eggs and beat at low speed of an electric mixer 30 seconds.
Increase speed to high and beat 3 minutes.
Gradually add remaining 2 cups flour, stirring to make a stiff dough.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Saute onion and pepper.
Mix all ingredients, except for cheese.
Pour into microwavable dish.
Sprinkle cheese on top. Microwave until cheese has melted.

title: fish in white gravy
directions: Saute in oil the onions and garlic, then add flour, onion tops and parsley.
Cook on low heat for a few minutes.
Add about 1/2 cup water; simmer until almost done.
Add fish and cook on a low fire until fish is done.
Season to taste.

title: fumi salad
directions: Toast the almonds and sesame seed.
Mix cabbage and onion in large bowl.
At last minute, add sesame seed, almonds and crushed Top Ramen (uncooked).
Pour the dressing over top and toss together.

title: hamburger baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Add beans, ketchup, vinegar, Worcestershire sauce and sugar.
Stir together.
Bake at 375° for 1/2 hour or until liquid has cooked out some.

title: layered lettuce salad
directions: Layer lettuce, green peppers, celery, onions and peas.
Spread with mayonnaise and sprinkle with sugar.
Top with the Cheddar cheese and then crumble the bacon on top.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or overnight.

title: fried rice
directions: Put rice, soup, bouillon and onion in casserole dish and add meat, if desired.
Mix well.
Cook at 350° until rice is done.

title: raspberry bread and butter pudding
directions: Spread butter on bread.
Fit 6 slices, buttered side down, in an 11 x 7-inch glass baking dish.
Sprinkle 1 cup berries on top. Layer with remaining bread, buttered side down, and berries. Whisk eggs with sugar, then milk in bowl.
Pour over bread, pressing gently.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Preheat oven to 350°. Place baking dish in larger pan in oven.
Pour boiling water in larger pan to come to within 1-inch up sides of dish.
Bake 50 minutes or until center is set.
Cool on wire rack.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli-rice delight
directions: Saute onions and celery in butter; drain.
Cook rice and broccoli.
Mix drained broccoli, onions and celery, then soups and cheese.
Line buttered dish with half the rice; pour in vegetable mixture.
Cover with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in pumpkin.
Sift flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, cloves, salt, baking powder and soda together.
Add to pumpkin mixture.
Pour into 2 (5 x 9-inch) loaf pans.
Bake for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: white chocolate salties
directions: Combine chocolate and shortening in a double boiler on low heat; melt chocolate.
Pour into a large mixing bowl.
Stir in pretzel sticks and peanuts.
Spread into a buttered 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Chill until set.
Break in pieces.

title: boiled custard
directions: Scald milk. Beat eggs well.
Mix sugar, salt and cornstarch to eggs.
Stir constantly while adding the hot milk. Cook in double boiler, stirring until the mixture thickens and coats a spoon. Cool and add flavoring.
Chill overnight. It is better real cold. Will keep well 2 or 3 days.

title: sausage and broccoli lasagne
directions: In skillet, cook sausage and onion.
Drain off fat.
Stir in sauce and seasonings.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Cook broccoli until tender; drain well.
Cook noodles.
Combine eggs, cottage cheese, Parmesan cheese and broccoli.
Layer 1/2 noodles and 1/2 cottage cheese mixture.
Top with 1/2 Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers except cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Uncover.
Add cheese and bake 10 minutes more.
Let set 10 minutes.

title: broccoli and cheese casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix in broccoli.
Pour in casserole dish and cover.
Cook for 30 minutes in oven at 350°. Remove cover and cook another 15 minutes.
Serve.

title: onion dip
directions: Chop onion and pepper very fine.
Add all other ingredients. Serve with your favorite chips.

title: collard greens
directions: Add water, neck bones, black pepper and salt to large pot. Let cook on medium flames.

title: guacamole
directions: Combine ingredients in order given. Stir briefly after adding each ingredient.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.
Good served with taco salad or taco chips.

title: candy crunches
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels over boiling water.
Add peanut butter.
Stir in chow mein noodles.
Add salted nuts.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper; put into refrigerator.

title: corn pone pie
directions: Combine meat, onions, sugar
and chili powder and saute until meat changes color.
Add
tomatoes and pintos and simmer for 15 minutes.
While
this cooks, mix cornbread:
corn meal, flour, sugar, salt, baking
powder, egg, milk and cooking oil. Mix well. Put meat mixture
in
a greased casserole, then put cornbread over and cook at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: *maryland crab cakes(olney inn)
directions: Combine all ingredients, except egg whites.
Beat egg whites and fold in.
Shape into 2 1/2 to 3-inch cakes.
Saute in melted butter over low heat until browned.

title: cajun beans
directions: Cook beans, onion, bell pepper and sausage.
When done, add beef bouillon cubes.

title: peanut butter squares(tastes like reese's peanut butter cups)
directions: Melt margarine. Add graham cracker crumbs, peanut butter and confectioners sugar.
Mix well and spread in 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: potato chip oven-fried chicken
directions: Combine crushed potato chips (can use different flavors if desired), garlic and pepper.
Dip chicken in melted butter.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place chicken, skin side up, in greased pan. Be sure pieces do not touch each other.
Sprinkle with remaining butter and crumbs.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour without turning. Makes 4 servings.

title: chat 'n chew bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Press firmly into 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown at 450°.
Cool thoroughly.
Cut into bars.

title: one step lasagna
directions: Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer 1/3 each of noodles, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat twice.
Pour water around the sides of the pan; cover tightly with foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Remove foil and bake 15 minutes or longer, until noodles are tender.
Let stand 20 minutes before serving.
Serves 6.

title: lite cheesecake
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, 2 tablespoons sugar and enough melted margarine to hold the crumb mixture together.
Press mixture into bottom and sides of spring-form pan.
Place pan in freezer.
Mix cream cheese, sugar, and cornstarch in mixer.
Add egg and egg whites, then sour cream.
Pour into spring-form pan. Place pan in preheated oven of 375°.
Bake for 10 minutes; turn oven to 300°.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Turn oven to 225°.
Bake for 85 minutes.
Turn oven off.
Leave in oven for 45 minutes.
Take out of oven.
Cool completely, then refrigerate.

title: pineapple sour cream cake
directions: Combine pudding and pineapple with juice and beat.
Add sour cream and sugar.
Beat slowly for 1 minute.
Pour in shell and chill for 3 hours.

title: meat loaf italiano
directions: Mix beef, 1 1/4 cups bread crumbs, egg, salt, onion powder, Italian seasoning, garlic powder and black pepper.
Add tomato sauce and mix well.
Shape into loaf and place on jelly roll pan. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pineapple muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar and pecans in a large
bowl.
Add egg, pineapple, milk, margarine and vanilla. Stir
until
just
moist.
Put
in	muffin	tins.
Makes approximately 18 muffins.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chef henri's rice and chilies(8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 2-quart casserole. In hot butter in large skillet, saute onion until golden (about 5 minutes).
Remove from heat; stir in hot rice, sour cream, cottage cheese, bay leaf, salt and pepper.
Toss lightly to mix well. Layer half the rice mixture in bottom of casserole.
Layer half the chilies; sprinkle with half of cheese.
Repeat.
Bake, uncovered, 25 minutes or until bubbly and hot.
Sprinkle with chopped parsley.

title: chocolate chip fruit bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and bananas.
Sift flour and soda together.
Stir into butter mixture.
Fold nuts, chips and cherries into batter.
Divide batter into two greased 9 x 5-inch or four 7 1/2 x 3 3/4 x 2 1/4-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° until toothpick is clean and bread starts to pull away, 9-inch pan for 60 to 65 minutes; 7 1/2-inch pan for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: no egg ice cream
directions: Mix first three ingredients together.
Add milk to fill freezer.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Filling: Separate yolks from egg whites. Mix yolks with 1 1/2 cans condensed milk and beat with fork. Add lemon juice and stir well. Pour in crust. Top with meringue or Cool Whip.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute peppers and onions in butter.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, soup and cheese, stirring often and cook over medium heat.
Add cleaned, raw shrimp.
Cook until shrimp are pink, about 7 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: big biscuits
directions: Melt margarine in iron frying pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: boiled raisin cookies
directions: Boil the raisins in water.
Set aside to cool. Cream the shortening and add sugars.
Add eggs one at a time. Combine flour with dry ingredients.
Add to mixture. Add oatmeal and mix.
Add raisins, water and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Stir cream cheese until smooth.
Mix well with hot Jell-O. Add pineapple, 7-Up, vanilla flavoring and sugar.
Refrigerate until firm in shallow pan.
Cut in squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until thick, stirring all the time. Pour over cooked, diced potatoes with chopped onion.
Add mayonnaise.
(Lightly salt potatoes before pouring on dressing.)

title: slush
directions: Mix well; put in freezer.
Stir occasionally until slushy (to keep sugar from settling).
To serve, put 3 tablespoons of slush in a large glass and fill with 7-Up.
If using small glasses, use 2 tablespoons of slush.

title: pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt the 2 tablespoons butter in bottom of 9 or 10-inch cake pan.
Add 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
Spread evenly. Drain the crushed pineapple, reserving 3/4 cup of syrup.
Spread drained pineapple on top of sugar mixture and set aside.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Place 1 1/2 cups flour, yeast and sugar in a large bowl.
Mix well.
Heat liquids and butter to hot (110° to 120°).
Pour into flour mixture and beat at medium speed for 3 minutes.
Stir in remaining flour.
Let rise until double.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp scampi
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add garlic and shrimp.
Saute for 3 minutes and add Italian salad dressing.
Stir until mixed well and shrimp turn pink.
Remove from heat and serve over hot cooked rice.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat soup over low heat.
Add cheese, milk and margarine. Next, add chicken, peppers, onion and sour cream.
In a frying pan, pour enough oil to cover the bottom, then dip tortillas until soft.
Put in layers and pour sauce over each.
Top with cheese. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: quick made dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake in iron skillet.
When ready for use, crumble and mix with turkey or chicken broth.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: turkey and sausage wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to package directions.
Set aside.
Brown sausage in large skillet over medium heat about 10 minutes, stirring until sausage crumbles and is no longer pink.
Add onion and red bell pepper to sausage mixture, and saute 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Drain.
Return sausage mixture to skillet over medium-high heat, and add mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Saute 3 minutes or until mushrooms are tender.

title: sweet and tangy kielbasa with shells
directions: Simmer kielbasa in 1/2 cup water (covered) for 20 minutes. Cook shells and drain. Drain and slice kielbasa. Set aside.
Cook bacon and drain. Reserve 3 tablespoons drippings.
Crumble bacon and set aside.

Cook mushrooms in drippings for 2 minutes. Stir in sugar, flour and pepper. Add the 3/4 cup water and vinegar. Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly. Add kielbasa, shells, bacon and parsley. Toss together.

title: easy miniature rolls
directions: Combine butter and flour; stir in sour cream.
Drop by tablespoons into greased miniature muffin tins.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Yields 36 rolls.

title: broccoli chicken casserole
directions: Place broccoli in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add chicken. Layer cheese.
Add mixed soup and mayonnaise.
Pour over top. Place sliced chestnuts on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle onion rings on top.
Bake 15 minutes longer.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Boil sugar, salt, butter and milk 6 minutes and stir constantly.
Mix chocolates, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Pour boiling syrup over chocolate mixture and mix until all of the chocolate melts.
Pour into very lightly greased pan and let stand a few hours before cutting.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Combine chicken, onions, cloves, salt, pepper and water in a large pot.
Cover and cook on low heat for 30 to 40 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken and cool quickly, saving broth. Bone chicken and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Cook spaghetti as package directs; drain and set aside.
Mix soup, sour cream, Cheddar cheese, sherry and peppers in a saucepan.
Stir over low heat until heated, but do not boil!
Cook mushrooms in chicken broth about 10 minutes.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: In medium saucepan, combine cornstarch, salt, dry mustard and pepper.
Stir in milk until smooth.
Add butter, stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil over medium to high heat.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove from heat.

title: tarragon-mustard chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch pieces.
Saute onion and garlic, then add chicken and cook chicken over medium heat until white. Add carrots and cook for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally. Season with pepper and thyme.
Add mustard and stir until incorporated. Sprinkle flour over mixture and stir in while continuing to cook for 3 to 4 minutes.
Add broth and wine. Simmer for about 10 minutes.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine melted margarine and graham crackers.
Put in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.

title: ham and rice so nice
directions: Place rice in bottom of greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Layer broccoli, ham, mushrooms and cheese over rice.
Combine soup, mayonnaise and mustard.
Mix well.
Pour over ham; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Makes 8 servings.

title: praline-peach cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Spray rectangular pan, 13 x 9 x 2-inches, with cooking spray. Stir together graham cracker crumbs, pecans, brown sugar and butter in medium bowl. Press evenly in bottom of pan. Arrange peaches over crust. Sprinkle with cinnamon-sugar. Stir together Bisquick mix, sugar and milk in medium bowl. Pour over peaches. Bake 55 to 65 minutes or until edges are deep golden brown and center is slightly brown. Serve warm. Store covered in refrigerator. Makes 12 servings.

title: 90 day pickles
directions: Wash cukes and pack in gallon jars.
Add to each jar: pickling spice, alum and salt.
Cover this with vinegar and let sit for 90 days.
After 90 days, remove from jars and pour out vinegar. Rinse off and slice real thin.
Add 1 cup sugar to every 2 cups cukes and set overnight.
Stir as often as you can.
Put in any container and pour juice over the cukes.
Containers do not have to be sterilized or sealed.

title: raspberry muffins
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix beaten egg, milk and melted fat.
Add to dry ingredients.
Add raspberries. Bake at 425° until slightly browned.

title: pecan turtles candy
directions: Put 3 pieces of pecan halves together to form cluster for each piece of candy.
Put one Kraft caramel on top of each cluster of nuts.
Put in oven on low temperature until caramel is soft enough to spread over nuts.
Do not get caramel too hot or too soft to spread.
Melt Hershey's Kisses in double boiler and then spread over top of each piece of candy.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Crush pretzels (not too fine).
Press into 9 x 13 pan.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together cream cheese, sugar and Cool Whip.
Put on pretzel mixture.
Mix Jell-O with water.
Stir in berries.
Let stand 10 minutes and pour on top of the cream cheese mixture.

title: chicken in white wine
directions: Brown chicken in oleo;
remove chicken from pan and put in chopped onions, carrots
and
celery.
Brown lightly.
In a large skillet or pot,
combine
chicken and vegetables.
Add 1 to 1 1/2 cups of water;
pour
in wine.
Cook, covered, at low temperature for 30 minutes.
Add
mushrooms
and simmer for 25 minutes.
(If a lot of liquid
is
left
in
pot, add 2 tablespoons of cornstarch, stirring constantly.) Serve over rice.

title: ranch beans
directions: Brown beef, bacon and onions in a pan.
Pour into pot with remaining ingredients.
Simmer one hour.
I leave out the liquid smoke.
I also bake mine in a slow oven in a bean pot.

title: grandma's orange-carrot cake
directions: Combine molasses, applesauce, eggs and orange juice.
Mix well.
Stir in flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well. Stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 9-inch round pans or one 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: crescent cheese cake
directions: Grease an 8 x 11-inch or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread first tube of rolls in pan pinching together at seams.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and egg yolk until light and fluffy.
Spread over rolls. Cover mixture with second tube of crescent rolls, pinching seams together as done with bottom layer.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Great for breakfast, brunch or anytime!
Delicious!
Serves 8 at 114 calories or 12 servings at 76 calories.

title: pilgrim corn casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients. Place in a buttered 2 quart casserole dish. Bake in a preheated 350F oven for 1 hour.

title: dark fruit cake
directions: Chop fruit and nuts.
Raisins don't need chopping and mixed fruit is already chopped.
Flour all fruit, raisins and nuts with 1 cup of flour.
Before you flour it, save back a few pieces of cherries, pineapple, dates, figs and unchopped nut halves to decorate cake.
Set floured mixture aside.
Cream margarine and sugar; while still beating add eggs, one at a time and then mix in milk, extracts and spices.
Add the remaining 2 cups flour and beat well.
Using a large pan, mix floured ingredients with batter using hands to mix well.

title: cream cake
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Put baking powder in flour; add alternately with cream.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: swedish hash
directions: Brown meat and onions.
Drain.
Add all ingredients.
Pour into a greased casserole dish and bake until rice is done.
Bake at 350° or microwave on High for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: raisin bars
directions: Melt shortening.
Add sugar and mix well.
Add egg and mix again.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Blend dry ingredients into sugar and egg mixture.
Add vanilla and raisins and mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch pan or double recipe and pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
You can ice these bars with a thin powdered sugar icing.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: country limas
directions: Soak beans overnight or cover with water 2-inches above beans and bring to boiling.
Boil them for 3 to 4 minutes, then let them sit for an hour.
Drain the water and refill to 2 to 3-inches above beans.
Add all other ingredients, except potatoes.
Bring to boil, then simmer for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes and cook until potatoes are done.

title: pork chops with amber rice
directions: Brown pork chops. Place 1 1/3 cups Minute rice in oblong baking dish. Pour orange juice over rice. Place in chops. Pour chicken with rice soup over rice and chops. Brown in oven at 350°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Mix all ingredients and top with crackers.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: mary's glorious pound cake
directions: Mix butter and sugar. Add eggs, flour, whipping cream and flavorings.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Frost, if desired.

title: cheese-rice crispy crackers
directions: Mix cheese and margarine.
Add flour and mix well.
Add rice cereal and mix well.
Shape into small balls and place on a greased cookie sheet.
Flatten each ball with a fork and bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: party ham and cheese rolls
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Spread on opened dinner rolls.
Add ham and cheese; top with dinner roll.
Cover with foil and heat in a 350° oven until cheese melts, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chili dip
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, microwave chili and cheese on High until melted.
Stir occasionally while cooking.
Remove and add hamburger.
Serve hot with nacho chips.

title: quick and easy lasagna
directions: Brown beef. Add spaghetti sauce, water, salt and sugar. Boil several minutes. In 9 x 13 pan, layer 1/3 sauce, 1/2 uncooked noodles, 1 cup cottage cheese and 1/3 of cheese. Repeat layers, ending with the sauce and cheese. Cover with foil and bake at 350° for at least 1 hour to 1 hour and 30 minutes. Remove from oven. Remove foil and let stand for 10 minutes.

title: creole crabmeat-potato puff
directions: Peel skin from potatoes; cut into small cubes.
Place potatoes in medium-size pot; fill with water and place on medium heat for 1/2 hour.
Stir potatoes, with butter, cream, garlic powder, onion, parsley, green onions and cheese.
Mix crabmeat into potato mixture lightly.
Place mixture in baking pan sprinkle generously with paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Serves 8.

title: broccoli with cheese sauce
directions: To Prepare:
Trim off large leaves; remove tough ends of stems.
Wash.
If stems are thicker than 1 inch, make lengthwise gashes in each stem.

title: stagecoach's hush puppies
directions: Put water and oleo in a pot and bring to a good boil.
Put other ingredients together in a mixing bowl while water is boiling.
Pour dry ingredients into pot, stirring constantly. Turn heat off as soon as dry ingredients have been added. Stir and mix well.
Hand roll into hush puppies while hot. Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Make a mixture of flour, cornmeal, salt and pepper.
Slice tomatoes in 1/4-inch slices.
Coat each slice with the batter mixture.
Fry in skillet with small amount of oil.
Brown on one side, then the other, turning only once.
When they are tender, they are ready to serve.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix zucchini and sugar; let set a few minutes until sugar dissolves. Mix the rest of the ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to one hour. Makes one large loaf or two small.

title: german apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch Bundt pan.
Preheat oven to 350°. Slice apples thin and toss with 5 tablespoons sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Set aside.
Mix together flour, sugar, salt, eggs, oil, vanilla, orange juice, baking powder and soda.
Blend on low for 1 minute, then at medium beat for 3 minutes.

title: slush
directions: Mix together and freeze. Remove from freezer one hour before serving.

title: breakfast quiche
directions: Prepare a pie shell and set aside.
Brown sausage and onion; drain fat.
Add 2 tablespoons of flour and mix.
Spread this mixture in unbaked pie shell.
Mix eggs, milk and cheese together and pour over sausage.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes.
Let stand 5 or 10 minutes.
Then serve.

title: hidden valley ranch crackers
directions: Combine mix with oil, add spices, pour over crackers and mix well.
Place on a cookie sheet and bake 15-20 minutes at 250°. Stir occasionally.

title: vegetable lasagna(makes 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 7 1/2 x 12 x 2-inch pan; set aside.
In boiling water, cook lasagna noodles according to package directions; drain.
Meanwhile, in a large saucepan, cook carrots, onion and garlic in oil.
Stir in spaghetti sauce, water, oregano and salt.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Stir in zucchini and cook, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: fay's special
directions: Slice off 1 roll of cookie dough and line 9 x 12-inch pan. Mix other ingredients and spread on cookie dough.
Slice other cookie dough and lay on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: mexican salad
directions: Dissolve lemon jello in 1 c. hot water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Mix;
place in oblong pan and place in refrigerator until set.

title: al's piggly wiggly broccoli salad
directions: Mix vegetables, cheese and bacon. In another bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar.
Mix well.
Pour over vegetable mixture.
Mix well.
Serve immediately.
Makes 10 to 12 servings. Can be made 24 hours in advance.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Beat margarine, oil and sugar until creamy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; mix well.
Sift flour and soda together.
Alternately add buttermilk.
Add vanilla, coconut and chopped nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Grease and flour three 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When cool, frost with cream cheese frosting. Freezes well.

title: o'harry bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
In a medium mixing bowl, cream butter or margarine and sugars.
Beat in corn syrup and vanilla.
Stir in oats.
Moisten hands to prevent sticking.
Pat mixture over bottom of pan.
Bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes or until bubbly and brown.
Cool slightly.
Melt chocolate with peanut butter on low setting.
Stir to blend.
Spread over baked layer; chill.
Loosen sides and turn out.
Cut into 3 x 1-inch bars.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: coconut delight cake
directions: Cook cake mix as directed on box.
Poke holes in cake (fork, toothpick, etc.).
Blend evaporated milk and cream of coconut together.
Pour on top of cake.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle on coconut, as desired.

title: eggplant with chickpeas
directions: Fry onion until lightly golden.
Add eggplant and chickpeas, stirring lightly, until eggplant is tender.
Add tomatoes or diluted tomato paste and seasoning, blending for a few minutes until done.
Serve warm or cold.

title: pizza cups
directions: Brown beef with onion and pepper.
Drain.
Stir in tomato paste.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Spray muffin pan with nonstick spray. Flatten biscuits and put in muffin cups.
Pour meat mixture in each cup.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 400° for 12 minutes or until brown.

title: pecan pie
directions: Add ingredients together and beat until well mixed.
Add pecans to mixture and pour into pie crust.
Bake until pie is set and pie crust is browned.
Use a 375° oven and bake for 40 to 50 minutes.
Enjoy.
I use a deep dish pie crust.

title: turkey (or chicken) casserole
directions: Cook broccoli; put in baking dish.
Top with layer of turkey and add salt and pepper.
Add mushroom soup, mixed with salad dressing.
Add grated cheese and toast cubes on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: raisin nut bread
directions: Boil raisins in the water and let cool.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: dilled potato salad(makes 6 servings.)
directions: In a large salad bowl, combine mayonnaise, yogurt and seasonings.
Fold in potatoes, peas and onions.
Cover and chill. Contains 135 calories per serving.

title: orange slice cookies
directions: In large mixing bowl, cream together sugars and shortening until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Stir into creamed mixture. Stir in candy and coconut.
Using about 1 tablespoon mixture for each, roll into 1-inch balls.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove. Cool on wire rack.
Makes 6 dozen or more.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Fold in egg whites lastly.
Pour in buttered dish.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until firm.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Beat eggs until light. Add sugar gradually until thick; then add remaining ingredients. Makes 1 gallon.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine eggs, milk, salt, flour and sugar.
Mix.
Add corn. Pour into baking dish and pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken in 1 can broth and a little water.
After boiled and when ready
for dumplings, add bouillon cubes and drop biscuit dough into broth.
Thicken as desired with cornstarch.

title: chocolate cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, sugars and eggs until light and fluffy.
Mix all dry ingredients together and then add to creamed mixture a little at a time.
Add vanilla.
Bake on an ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes, until they look a little cracked.
Do not overbake!

title: pumpkin-pecan cheesecake
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Pulverize the pecans and crackers.
Add brown sugar and blend well with fingers.
Add butter, tossing with a fork.
Press crumbs in bottom and halfway up side of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Bake for 10 minutes.
Remove and cool.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix in order.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken vegetable casserole
directions: Remove chicken from bones and put in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Next spread vegetables over chicken.
Mix soup and milk together.
Pour over chicken and vegetables.
Make stuffing according to directions on package and sprinkle on top.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: butter pecan pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and beat on low for 2 minutes. Bake in Bundt pan for 45 to 60 minutes (depends on your oven) at 350°.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out dough into large rectangle on lightly floured surface. Brush with egg and milk wash.
Place remaining ingredients of your choice down the middle 1/3 of rectangle.
Fold up outer third (sides) of rectangle over the center.
Brush top with egg and milk wash.
Sprinkle with Parmesan, oregano and parsley.
Bake at 350° on greased cookie sheet for 20 minutes.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: florentine stuffed pasta shells
directions: Mix above ingredients together.
Stuff cooked jumbo pasta shells with mixture. Cover bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with marinara sauce (spaghetti sauce).
Place shells in pan.
Cover with remaining sauce and shredded Mozzarella.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fruit medley
directions: Empty
ingredients
into
large
bowl (do not drain any cans). Mix
instant pudding and let set.	(If liquid is still too thin, add another small box of instant pudding.) Chill and serve with most
any
dish and/or meal.
(Can be added to for larger bowl or taken away for smaller amount.)

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix and pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: orange delight - jello
directions: Blend orange Jell-O with boiling water.
Refrigerate until consistency of egg whites.
Blend in Cool Whip; add oranges and pineapple.
Pour into flat pan.
Sprinkle top with chopped nuts. Refrigerate again until it becomes stiffer.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Boil butter, onion and water.
Add
broccoli
and cook 3 minutes.
Add rice and let stand 5 minutes.
Add Cheez Whiz and soup; mix well and pour into 13 x 9-inch dish.
Cook 35 minutes at 325°.
Serves 10 to 15.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Spread hamburger in bottom of greased loaf pan or casserole. Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Add green beans.
Pour mushroom soup over beans.
Add frozen Tater Tots.
Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.

title: big bean pot
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a Dutch oven or large roaster, saute bacon and onions; drain.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Bake uncovered at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes, until hot and bubbly. Serves 16.

title: noels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine.
Beat egg slightly. Combine sugar, flour, soda, nuts and dates.
Stir into eggs, margarine and vanilla.
Bake 20 minutes.
Dust bottom side with powdered sugar.

title: butterscotch smoothies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips in double boiler until smooth.
Stir in peanut chips or remove from stove and add peanut butter.
Pour into round buttered cake pan or tiny cupcake cups.
Let cool.

title: carrot bake
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Arrange carrots in ungreased rectangular baking dish, 12 x 7 x 2-inches.
Layer cauliflowerets over carrots.
Dot with margarine.
Sprinkle with salt and nutmeg. Cover and bake until vegetables are tender, 50 to 55 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese; garnish with parsley.

title: victoria sponge cake
directions: Sieve the flour.
Take out the butter from the refrigerator 1 hour in advance.
Cream the butter and sugar very well. When mixture is light and creamy, add the eggs, one at a time, beating each time thoroughly.
If the mixture curdles while adding eggs, add a little flour before adding the next egg.
Fold in the flour and add milk until the mixture forms a dropping consistency.
Add vanilla essence.
Grease and dust two 7-inch diameter tins.
Pour 1/2 the mixture into each of the two tins.
Bake in a hot oven at 400° for 20 minutes.
Cool the cake.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup, water and a small lump of butter. Cook mixture until peanuts pop.
Stir in soda.
Spread in ungreased pan.
When cold, break into pieces.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together and stir.
Chill before serving.

title: pumpkin and cream cheese roll-up
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Line with wax paper.
Grease and flour the wax paper.

title: easy chicken or pork picada
directions: Saute meat; sprinkle with taco seasoning.
Add rest of ingredients (salsa and preserves) to pan and simmer with a little added water for 45 minutes.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water until mixture spins a thread.
Then add raw peanuts.
Cook until golden brown.
Add butter, vanilla, salt and baking soda.
Mix and pour out onto a large cookie sheet that has been previously buttered.
Let cool and break into pieces.

title: bread pudding
directions: Cut buttered bread into finger width pieces or cubes.
Arrange in layers in buttered baking dish (for variation, sprinkle each layer with slices Brazil nuts or raisins and cinnamon).
Beat eggs slightly; add sugar, salt, vanilla and milk.
Mix well and pour over bread.
Bake in slow oven (325°) for 1 hour.
Serves 6.

title: raspberry fluff
directions: Mix Jell-O according to instructions on box, except before the cold water, add ice cream and berries.
Then add cold water.
Mix and pour into a large dish and freeze.
Thaw some before eating to soften.
Very refreshing.

title: easy chicken divan
directions: Cook broccoli and drain. Arrange broccoli in greased 11 1/2 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish. Place the chicken on top. Combine soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder; pour over chicken. Sprinkle with cheese. Combine breadcrumbs and butter; sprinkle all over. Bake in preheated 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated. Trim with pimento strips if desired. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: fresh apple bread
directions: Beat eggs and
sugar, add all remaining ingredients.
Mix until well blended.
Grease 2 loaf pans and pour batter.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: pork cutlets with maple-mustard sauce
directions: Place pork cutlets between sheets of plastic wrap and pound to a 1/3-inch thickness. Sprinkle with half of sage, salt and pepper. Melt butter in a 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Add pork and cook until cooked through and brown on both sides, about 2 minutes per side. Remove pork to a plate, leaving drippings in skillet. Add broth, syrup, mustard and remaining sage to the skillet. Boil until syrupy, about 3 minutes. Reduce heat to low. Return pork to skillet, and cook until just heated through, about 2 minutes. Serve glazed with the sauce.

title: blarney stone salad
directions: Add boiling water to lime Jell-O.
When Jell-O is starting to set, add crushed pineapple.
Pour over first mixture.
Chill until set.

title: yam, apple, nut stuffing
directions: Bake potatoes until soft (in 450° oven), about 1 hour.
Peel and mash.
Add butter and mix well.
Peel, core and thinly slice apples.
In a saucepan, place apples, sugar and water and cook, covered, until tender.

title: million dollar rice salad
directions: Cream the cheese, mayonnaise and sugar.
Add pineapple, marshmallows, rice and cherries.
Last fold in the cream, which has been whipped good, and nuts.
Place in dish and chill.

title: fry bread
directions: In large mixing bowl, put warm water, then add to the water the yeast, sugar, salt and shortening.
Mix well, then stir flour into the mixture until the dough turns into elastic, not sticky. Keep adding flour if you need more than the 5 cups; grease your dough.
Let rise.
Fry in hot grease until lightly browned.
Drain on paper towels.

title: chinese meatballs(appetizer)
directions: Mix and form into meatballs.
Bake on cookie sheet in a 275° oven for 30 minutes.

title: chicken divan
directions: Layer broccoli in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay chicken on top of broccoli.
Combine the next 5 ingredients and pour over chicken. Sprinkle cheese over chicken mixture.
Mix bread crumbs and melted butter.
Sprinkle over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes until hot.
Let stand a few minutes and serve over rice.

title: mom's chicken dumplings
directions: Mix broth, salt and baking powder.
Add enough flour to make dough stiff dough to roll out.
Slice into strips.
Drop strips into boiling broth.
Simmer.
(I let the chicken cool, remove it from the bones, then return it to the broth.)

title: mystery mocha
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.

Melt chocolate and butter slowly over low heat. Add to first mixture, then add milk and vanilla. Stir with wire whisk. Pour into greased 9-inch square baking pan. Combine sugars and cocoa and sprinkle over top of batter.
Pour coffee over top. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Serve with vanilla ice cream.

title: salmon au gratin
directions: Place toast in a greased 8 x 8-inch dish or pan.
Top with the salmon (drain all juice).
Put the salmon on the toast with your hands (works better).
Mix soup with cream or milk; add parsley and onion.
Spoon over salmon; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, until cheese melts and is bubbly.
Makes 4 big servings.

title: chicken surprise
directions: If stuffing mix is used, leave out seasoning.

title: scalloped ham and potatoes
directions: Put half of ham, potatoes and onion in a slow cooker.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper, then half of cheese.
Repeat layers.
Spread soup over top, completely covering potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken until done. Remove from broth and cool. Chop into bite-sized pieces and place in lightly greased 13 x 9 pan. Combine soup, sour cream and seasonings. Pour over chicken. Combine cracker crumbs and poppy seeds. Sprinkle over soup mixture and drizzle with margarine. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 10 to 12.

title: cheesecake
directions: Beat cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar.
Blend in vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust.
Chill until set, 4 hours.
Clean; slice strawberries and mix with glaze.
Serve on top of cheesecake.

title: brownies deluxe
directions: Melt margarine.
Beat in eggs.
Add sugar, flour, cocoa and baking powder.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: steak and kidney pudding
directions: Mix flour and suet with salt together with enough water to make a firm dough.
Roll out pastry on a floured cloth (large enough to hold ingredients).
The pastry should be 1/2-inch thick in center.
Place beef kidney and onion mixture; dust with flour and sprinkle with water.
Fold the pastry together to hold the meat mixture.
Gather the 4 corners of the cloth into 1 hand and tie with string, leaving about 1-inch leeway between the pudding and the tie.
Put into a saucepan, cover with cold water and boil slowly for about 3 hours.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs; add oil, sugar and zucchini.
Add in dry ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Pour mixture into greased and lightly floured loaf pans (2 large or 3 small). Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Cool on rack.
Turn out and cool thoroughly.

title: shoo-fly pies
directions: Mix flour, sugar and butter all together.
Mix molasses, hot water and baking soda all together.
Pour liquid in unbaked pie shell and then put crumbs over liquid.
Do not mix together.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 pies.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the peanut butter and oats, in saucepan.
Boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Pour mixture over oats and peanut butter.
Mix well.
Pour or drop in a buttered pan.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: good old georgia sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients at once and pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes or until knife comes out clean.

title: mud hen bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in 1 whole egg and 2 egg yolks.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°. Mix butter, sugar, brown sugar, vanilla and eggs in a large bowl. Then mix soda, salt and 1 1/4 cups of the flour. Stir in the rest of the flour, peanut butter and chocolate chips. Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of dough onto a large cookie sheet. Bake for 8 to 11 minutes.

title: egg and sausage casserole
directions: Saute sausage; drain well.
Mix eggs, milk and seasonings. Layer bread cubes, sausage and cheese in a greased casserole dish. Pour egg mixture over layered mixture.
Refrigerate overnight or 2 to 3 hours before baking.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: star-spangled parfaits(makes twelve 1-cup servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a 10 x 15-inch baking pan combine oats, cereal, peanuts and cinnamon.
In a small saucepan, combine butter, brown sugar, water and vanilla.
Stir over low heat until evenly blended.
Pour over oat mixture.
Stir to coat well.
Bake, stirring frequently for 30 minutes, or until lightly browned. Cool.
Stir in raisins. Store in an airtight container.

title: waldorf astoria cake(red velvet)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add color and eggs.
Sift flour 3 times.
Add vanilla, flour, salt, buttermilk and cocoa alternately.
Dissolve vinegar and soda together before folding into flour mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cherry delight
directions: Press graham crackers, butter and sugar into glass dish (9 x 13-inch).
Soften cream cheese and powdered sugar and fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over graham cracker mixture.
Pour over top of cherry pie filling.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Cut into squares and serve.

title: french dressing
directions: Combine all ingredients well with a mixer. Serve with vegetables or salad.

title: whipped cream cheese cake
directions: Let cream cheese, sour cream, butter and eggs stand at room temperature for approximately one hour.
Blend cream cheese, butter and sour cream together, then add the cornstarch, sugar, vanilla and lemon juice.
Beat on "whip" speed until very well blended. Beat in one egg at a time until the entire mixture is very smooth.

title: rhubarb upside-down cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put rhubarb, sugar, Jell-O and marshmallows over bottom of pan.
Mix cake mix as directed on package.
Pour cake batter over rhubarb and Jell-O mixture.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Invert cake on a tray.
When cool, serve with whipped topping or ice cream.

title: double-quick dinner buns
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in deep bowl; add sugar, salt and about half of flour.
Beat thoroughly two minutes.
Add egg and shortening and beat in remaining flour.
Let rise in bowl in warm place about 50 minutes.
Stir batter down and place in greased muffin pans.
Let rise 30 minutes and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 425°.
Makes 12.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream the margarine and shortening. Add eggs and sugar alternately.
Sift flour and baking powder.
Add alternately with milk.
Add the vanilla. Bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool and remove from pan.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Bake Jiffy mix as directed on box.
Crumble baked corn bread into bottom of pan or dish.
Pour beans on top of bread.
Slice onions, pepper and tomato on top of beans.
Mix mayonnaise and pickle juice together; pour on top.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Chill and serve.

title: jena's chili-mac
directions: Brown hamburger, pepper and onion.
Drain.
Add tomatoes and spices to taste (1/2 to 1 teaspoon).
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Cook macaroni separately.
Drain and add to hamburger.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes.
Top with your favorite cheese.
American cheese is delicious.
Serves 6.

title: party rounds
directions: Soften cream cheese and mix with Italian dressing and mayo. Chill.
Spread on party rounds.
Top with a slice of cucumber. Enjoy!

title: grape and turkey salad
directions: Combine turkey, celery, grapes and mayonnaise.
Season with salt and pepper.
Toss lightly.
Serve on salad greens.
Trim with additional grapes, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: french toast bake
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Add brown sugar and mix together.
Place 2 layers bread over sugar mixture.
Mix remaining ingredients together and pour over top of bread.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake uncovered at 375° for 35 minutes or until toasted on top.

title: nannan's brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease pan.
Melt cocoa and shortening in large saucepan over low heat.
Remove from heat, mix in sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: peggy smith's impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Grease
9-inch
pie
plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth.
Bake about 30 to 35 minutes at 350° until knife comes out clean.
Serve with fruit if desired.

title: "almost sugar-free" chocolate pudding
directions: In a 2-quart microwave dish, stir together cocoa, sugar, cornstarch, Sweet 'N Low and salt.
Gradually stir in milk.
Cook on High power 6 minutes or until thickened, stirring several times.
Stir in margarine and vanilla.
Pour into individual serving dishes; cover with plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Makes 5 (1/2-cup) servings.

title: fried cauliflower
directions: Break cauliflower into flowerets.
Boil until tender in salted water.
Mix eggs with flour and salt to taste until it forms a paste.
Add drained cauliflower.
Drop in hot oil and dry until brown, turning once.

title: date orange cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add soda and salt to buttermilk; then add alternately to creamed mixture with flour.
Add orange peel, nuts and dates.
Bake in 1-piece angel food cake pan (large), greased and floured well, 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: happy apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and 1 teaspoon salt together.
Cream eggs and sugar in mixer bowl until light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients, oil, apples, pecans and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch dish or pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes or until cake tests done.

title: baked blueberry pancakes
directions: Mix milk, egg and butter.
Add dry ingredients.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Arrange blueberries over all. Place a piece of sausage so that each slice has a sausage.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Test with toothpick.
Serve with syrup.

title: fruit salad
directions: Partially thaw strawberries.
Drain oranges and pineapple. Slice bananas.
Mix all ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Chill and serve.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Pour boiling water and gelatin in large mixing bowl; mix until gelatin dissolves.
Beat cranberry sauce and sour cream into gelatin mixture with eggbeater.
Drain oranges and fold into mixture with chopped nuts.
Spoon into 5-cup ring mold.
Chill in refrigerator until set.

title: homemade tomato soup
directions: Cream margarine and flour together until smooth.
I melt the margarine first.
Add cheese and milk.
Boil until bubbly.
Add tomato juice that is boiling in another pan.
Stir until completely
slowly mixed.
Season with salt and pepper.
Ready to serve with crackers.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: In mixing bowl, combine water, honey and yeast.
Let set until mixture bubbles.
Beat into yeast mixture 5 cups whole wheat flour.
Beat 5 minutes by hand or with an electric mixer.
Let set a few minutes.
Then mix in salt, oatmeal and 8 to 8 1/2 cups of flour.
Add chopped dates or raisins.
Knead 8 to 10 minutes. Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Divide dough into 4 balls.
Form into 4 loaves, making sure you work dough hard enough to get large air bubbles out.
Place in 4 medium sized SilverStone loaf pans or four medium loaf pans that have been sprayed with Pam.
Let rise about 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 4 medium loaves.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place potatoes on oven rack and bake for 60 to 75 minutes or until tender. Cut a thin lengthwise slice from each potato. Scoop out the inside, leaving a thin shell.

title: island energy bars
directions: Toast oats and sesame seed in skillet, stirring occasionally, for 3 minutes or until lightly browned.
Melt marshmallows, peanut butter and margarine over medium flame, stirring constantly.
Add oats, sesame seed and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool and cut into bars.
Yield: 48 bars.

title: calzone
directions: Let bread rise according to package directions.
Punch down and flatten out on a 9 x 13-inch shallow pan.
Heat the olive oil slowly.
Add garlic only to slightly brown.
Do not overcook. Pour garlic and oil over broccoli, olives and cheese and mix together.
Pour mixture onto bread dough and roll up, jelly roll fashion (2 rolls).
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Slice.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Saute beef; add onion, garlic and seasoning.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Add all but rice and simmer 30 minutes.
Add rice just before serving.
Put the following toppings in separate dishes for self-service:
cheese, tomatoes, lettuce, Fritos, avocado, ripe olives and taco sauce.

title: chili-cheese potatoes
directions: Combine potatoes and oil in a 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish; toss well.
Sprinkle potatoes with parsley, chili powder, salt and pepper.
Cover tightly with heavy-duty plastic wrap; fold back a small corner to wrap to allow steam to escape.
Microwave at High 9 to 10 minutes or until tender, stirring gently, every 3 minutes. Sprinkle potatoes with cheese and onion.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes.

title: gingerbread
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, brown sugar, cinnamon, ginger, baking powder and baking soda.
Add shortening, molasses, egg and 1/2 cup water.
Beat with an electric mixer on low to medium speed until combined.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes.

title: bacon-horseradish dip
directions: Serve with chips, crackers or veggies.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and seasonings well.
Mix all other ingredients and pour seasonings over.
Mix well.
Refrigerate 2 hours.

title: diet fruit salad
directions: Drain most of liquid off of fruit and mix all together.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Clean zucchini and mushrooms.
Melt butter in skillet and saute zucchini, mushrooms, onions and tomatoes until tender. Drain off excess liquid.

Using 2 qt. casserole, layer vegetable mixture, alternately with Mozzarella cheese, ending with cheese on top. Sprinkle with breadcrumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350°, covered the first 1/2 hour and uncovered the last 1/2 hour.

title: horseradish eggs
directions: Peel and cut eggs in half.
Mix together the sour cream, mayonnaise, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Gently mix in the egg yolks.
Fill egg whites with yolk mixture; sprinkle with paprika. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: coconut 3 day cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients; set aside. This is the filling. Mix cake as directed on the box.

Bake in two 8-inch round cake pans. When cooled, split the layers; put the filling between the layers. Reserve 1 cup of filling to add to the carton of Cool Whip for the frosting on top. Store in the refrigerator.
Best after 3 days in the refrigerator, if you can wait that long.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Combine egg product, evaporated milk, salt and black pepper in large bowl. Add potatoes, cheese, onion, bell pepper and ham; mix well.
Pour mixture into prepared baking dish.
Bake for 60 to 65 minutes or until set.
Makes 12 servings.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Mix flour together.
Cream butter and sugar and add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add flour mixture alternately with sour cream, ending with flour.
Add flavoring. Pour into a large tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and about 5 or 10 minutes.

title: fruit ball
directions: Drain and crush fruit; add cream cheese.
Work/mix together well.
Add dry pudding.
Mix.
Form into ball, roll in nuts. Refrigerate till time to serve.

title: pecan spread
directions: Place cream cheese in microwave for 30 to 45 seconds on High. Add milk, green pepper, garlic salt, pepper, onion flakes and sour cream; mix well.
Melt margarine. Stir in pecans and salt. Microwave on High for 1 minute. Sprinkle over cheese mixture in serving dish. Serve with crackers or crisp vegetables.

title: chicken-artichoke soup
directions: Place chicken and water in Dutch oven.
Bring to a boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes or until tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Cool slightly and shred.
Save the broth. Spray dutch oven with Pam.
Saute onion and celery until crisp-tender.
Add the broth from cooking, the canned broth, bay leaf, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat. Cover and simmer until thoroughly heated.
Top each serving equally with Parmesan cheese.

title: scarborough casserole
directions: Best if made in the AM to stand in refrigerator or overnight before cooking.

title: blueberry-coconut slush
directions: In a blender, combine pineapple sherbet or sorbet, blueberries, coconut milk and sweetened shredded coconut. Whirl until smooth and pour into a chilled tall glass. Makes 2 cups.

title: bar cheese
directions: Cube Velveeta and melt in microwave, stirring occasionally. Cook bacon until crisp and cut into small pieces.
When Velveeta has melted, stir in bacon, horseradish (including juice) and mayonnaise.
Quickly pour into refrigerator containers.
Chill for 4 hours.
Serve as a spread with crackers.

title: pineapple cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill in refrigerator for 2 hours.
Serve with low-fat or fat-free crackers.
Makes 16 servings.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Mix well all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Press into a 15 x 10-inch pan.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on peanut butter mixture.
Cool.
Cut into bars.
Keep in refrigerator or in freezer.

title: frozen cranberry salad
directions: In a medium bowl, blend cream cheese, mayo and sugar.
Fold in the Cool Whip and set aside.
In a
large mixing bowl, combine pineapple, nuts, coconut and cranberry sauce.
Add cranberries. Gently combine with cream cheese mixture.
Spread into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch glass baking dish.
Cover and freeze.
Remove from freezer 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Cut into squares or slices. Serve on lettuce leaves.
Makes 24 servings.

title: zucchini ziti casserole
directions: Cook ziti as directed.
Peel and julienne zucchini.
Saute zucchini until tender.
Season this with salt, pepper and Italian seasonings.
Grease (with Pam) a deep casserole dish.
Put cooked zucchini in and sprinkle with 1/2 Parmesan cheese.
Cook alfredo sauce using milk only.
Mix the cooled ziti, Ricotta cheese, Parmesan cheese and alfredo sauce, then pour on top of zucchini. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: aunt oing oing's carrot cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients.
Add eggs and oil until well blended. Fold in carrots and raisins.
Bake in greased Bundt pan for 1 hour at 300°.

title: yellow squash pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chicken pot pie
