directions: Thaw out the pie crusts and then mix all of the ingredients together, cooking the chicken first and dicing it up. Then pour into the pie crust. Take the second pie crust and flip over the top of the chicken mix; press the pie crust down over the edges. Poke holes in top with fork. Bake 30 minutes. Serve with bread and butter. Yummy!!

title: refried beans
directions: Grate the cheese.
Drain about half the juice from the beans. Mash with potato masher. Add cheeses and reheat.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Fill 3 1/2-quart crock-pot 7/8 full with apples.
Cook until mushy, approximately 1 hour on high.
Add remaining ingredients and boil on high for 8 or more hours, until desired thickness. Pour into jelly jars and refrigerate or freeze.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Mix all together.
This makes a very large batch.
I put them in 2 casserole dishes.
Freeze one.
Bake the other at 350 degrees for 40 minutes, till heated through and cheese melts.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and place in small jars for gifts or large jar for your own convenience.
Refrigerate.
Will keep indefinitely.

title: french toast with apple custard sauce
directions: Heat 1/2-inch oil in electric skillet to 325°.
Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs, cream and salt in medium bowl.
Dip each slice of bread, allowing it to soak up as much liquid as possible. Fry in hot oil until browned, turning only once.
Transfer to baking sheet and bake until puffed, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Arrange on heated platter; sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve immediately with Apple Custard Sauce on side.

title: pastors' wives' casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom of 2-quart glass casserole dish.
Wipe chicken with a damp paper towel (or use a sliced lemon) to clean.
Place chicken on the bottom of casserole dish.
Spread cream of chicken soup on top of chicken.
Pour wine over chicken and soup.
Sprinkle croutons generously on top.
Pour melted butter over croutons.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: clayville pioneer sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine, sugars, eggs, oil and vanilla together.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Refrigerate overnight.
Form small balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet. Dip a glass in sugar and flatten each cookie.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: quick coconut cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 2 (9-inch) pans.
Cool; slice each layer into 2 layers with split sides up.
Mix sugar and sour cream together.
Add 3/4 package coconut to mixture; fold in Cool Whip. Add vanilla.
Spread on layers, top and sides.
Sprinkle remainder of coconut over cake.
Let stand for several hours before serving. Keep in refrigerator.

title: buttermilk pound cake 2
directions: Cream sugar and butter until smooth; add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Mix soda and hot water; add to buttermilk. Add flour and milk alternately, a little at a time to sugar, butter and eggs.
Add flavors and beat 5 minutes.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake until cake leaves sides of pan (about 45 minutes) at 350°.

title: back country venison
directions: Combine all ingredients in crock-pot.
The dried apples will cook to a thick gravy.
Let cook on low 8 or 9 hours.
Serve with boiled small potatoes or mashed, cole slaw or tossed salad.

title: quick snack time pizza
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees. Remove biscuits from can and flatten. Place onto, (vegetable sprayed), cookie sheet. Top each biscuit with 1 tablespoon pizza sauce. Place pepperoni and sausage on top of sauce. Top each with cheese. Bake 8--10 minutes or until biscuits are done and cheese melted.

title: pink stuff
directions: Mix together. Drain cottage cheese. Drain crushed pineapple. Dry jello mixed together until cottage cheese turns pink. Then fold in Cool Whip and nuts.
Keep in refrigerator until served.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch pie plate. Set aside.
Toss spaghetti with olive oil or butter.
Combine eggs and 1/2 cup shredded Parmesan.
Stir into spaghetti.
Pour mixture into prepared pie plate.
Form into a "crust".

title: homemade yeast
directions: Cook potatoes until soft in boiling water.
Mash in liquid. There should be one quart.
Add sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Blend yeast and lukewarm water.
Add to potato mixture.
Put in glass jar.
Keep at room temperature for 24 hours.
Then cover with lid, refrigerate.

title: squash rolls
directions: Mix ingredients as for any rolls.
Knead until smooth.
Let rise once.
Punch down.
Shape into rolls.
Let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 400° about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine 3/4 cup sugar, flour, cocoa and milk (enough to dampen); stir well.
Add rest of milk, 1 cup water, beaten egg yolks and dash of salt. Place in a 2-quart pan; heat over medium heat, stirring constantly.
When thick enough to stand, remove from heat and add 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Pour into pie crust.

title: western mac
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese. Brown meat and onions. Cook until tender. Stir in corn, tomato paste, water, salt and pepper. Add macaroni and mix well. Pour into 2-quart casserole; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: white brownies
directions: Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Makes 32 squares.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Add other ingredients and simmer for 30 minutes.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir into sauce.
Put 1/2 of mixture in long pan and top with cheese.
Spread remaining mixture on top and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: beets polynesian
directions: In saucepan combine brown sugar, flour and salt.
Stir in vinegar and 1/4 cup plus 2 tablespoons water.
Add undrained pineapple, raisins and butter.
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Stir in cooked fresh or drained canned beets; heat through.
Makes 5 servings.

title: boston creams
directions: Put sugar, cream, butter and syrup in a large skillet or pan. Cook until it makes a soft ball.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla, nuts or coconut and soda.
Beat until cream cools and pour in pan. Cut in pieces when cool.

title: chewy spice cookies
directions: In a bowl, combine brown sugar, applesauce, molasses and egg substitute until well blended.
Combine flour, baking soda and spices; stir into molasses mixture.
Drop by teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto baking sheets that have been lightly coated with nonstick cooking spray.
Sprinkle with sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Yield: About 3 1/2 dozen.
Nutritional Analysis: One cookie equals 56 calories, 15 mg sodium, trace cholesterol, 12 gm carbohydrate, 1 gm protein and trace fat.

title: pierres' pasta with blue cheese and asparagus
directions: Saute asparagus (cut on bias).
Add salt and pepper to taste. Add garlic and tomatoes.
Cook pasta.
Add pasta and 1/4 pound Blue cheese (diced) to pan and toss with 1/2 cup fresh basil and Parmesan.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Skin chicken; wash and pat dry.
Place in crock-pot.
Pour on barbecue sauce.
Turn crock-pot on low; baste now and then if you're home.

title: pizza burger
directions: Brown hamburger meat, drain and let cool.
Gradually add cheese and Spam, then add Ragu and oregano.
Put on hamburger buns.
Cook at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: clams casino
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
In bacon grease, place peppers, onions and celery which have been ground up.
Simmer until all are tender. Add crushed Ritz crackers.
Split open clams and place mixture on top of clams.
Broil until brown.
These are the best-wonderful flavor!

title: guacamole dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Cover and chill 1 hour. Serve with sliced raw vegetables and corn chips.
Makes 2 cups.

title: holiday jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with boiling water.
Stir until dissolved, about 2 minutes.
Add cold water; let set until soft, then add all other ingredients.
This is great served with turkey or ham.

title: pina colada cake
directions: Bake yellow cake mix in greased and floured sheet pan.
Leave in pan.
Cool.
Punch holes with fork.
Mix milk and creme of coconut pina colada and pour over cake.
Mix frozen coconut and Cool Whip and top cake.
Chill.
tags: creme of coconut pina colada mix

title: chewy bars
directions: Mix sugar and margarine.
Add eggs.
Stir in flour, vanilla and pecans.
Spread into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan. Bake at 325° for about 40 minutes.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter and cheese; stir in mushroom soup.
Combine rice, broccoli and onion.
Mix together and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, onion, raisins and water chestnuts in a serving bowl.
In a small bowl, combine mayo, sugar, vinegar and oil, blending well.
Pour over salad mixture.
Toss to blend. Cover and refrigerate several hours or overnight.
Sprinkle bacon over top before serving.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: creamy banana pie with lemon
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch and gelatin. Gradually stir in milk and egg yolks.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a full boil.
Stir in margarine, vanilla and lemon peel until margarine is melted.
Pour filling into large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate until thick. Place 2 tablespoons lemon juice in small bowl and dip 3 sliced bananas into lemon juice.
Beat whipping cream until stiff.
Fold bananas and whipped cream into pudding mixture.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate 5 hours.
Before serving, stir together apple jelly and 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Cook over low heat until melted.
Arrange banana slices on pie.
Drizzle jelly over bananas.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook rice.
Rice should be flaky, not gummy.
Set aside.
In electric skillet, put a chopped up head of cabbage with 1/2 cup sugar and small amount of vegetable oil.
Cover.
Makes own steam, and before done, add chopped up onions, green bell pepper and celery.
Stir.
Don't overcook.
Shut off.
Can use green onions, if you would rather.

title: microwave corn-on-cob
directions: Shuck corn down to last layer of shucks.
Chop on silk end of corn.
Rinse corn to dampen.
Wrap in plastic or waxed wrap. Microwave 2 minutes per ear, turning over once.

title: chicken divan
directions: Cook chicken.
Cool;
skin
and
cut into chunks.
Cook broccoli just until tender and drain and cool on paper towels. Mix remaining ingredients
except for bread crumbs and cheese. Layer in an 8 x
11-inch	baking	dish
the broccoli, chicken, then sauce.
Top with
bread
crumbs
mixed with melted butter and then cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Store in airtight container.
Mix 1 to 2 teaspoons with hot water.

title: yorkshire puddings
directions: Mix flour, salt and eggs with milk and water.
Beat until smooth batter.
Preheat cupcake pan on 450° with 1 teaspoon oil per cup.
When pan is hot, add mixture to 1/2 full.
Bake in oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for another 10 minutes. Serve with roast beef and gravy.
Pour gravy over Yorkshire Puddings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Heat first 3 ingredients in a saucepan over low heat, until sugar dissolves.
Cool to lukewarm.
Stir in eggs; add pecans and vanilla.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Simmer ingredients, except cinnamon sticks, for 20 minutes. Pour through strainer.
Pour cider into warmed cups and add cinnamon stick.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes.
Whip potatoes with oleo and add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: orange cinnamon coffee
directions: Combine the orange slices, cinnamon sticks and coffee in basket of coffee pot.
Fill to 6 cups and brew according to regular directions.
Place an orange rind twist and a cinnamon stick in each cup and fill with coffee.
Serve hot.

title: cold bread pudding
directions: Crumble up biscuits.
Add remaining ingredients; stir well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: lunch meat
directions: Mix all together and let stand for 24 hours.
Roll in aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Roll like summer sausage.

title: inflation corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal, soda, salt, eggs, milk, drippings and corn together; set aside.
Saute ground beef; drain off fat.
Grease large iron skillet.
Pour 1/2 of the batter into the pan.
Spread meat over batter in pan for next layer, then onion, peppers, cheese and pimentos.
Pour remaining batter on top; bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: frosted orange salad
directions: In a bowl, dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Stir cold water, bananas, marshmallows and pineapple into gelatin.
Pour into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch dish coated with non-stick cooking spray;
refrigerate until firm.

title: low-fat chocolate walnut brownies
directions: Cream the margarine.
Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating well at medium speed on an electric mixer.
Add egg substitute, evaporated milk and vanilla; beat well.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Add to creamed mixture; mix well.
Stir in walnuts.
Spoon into an 8-inch square pan coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes, or until a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool on a wire rack; cut into squares.
Yields 16 servings.

title: texas pecan pie
directions: Combine all and pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 450°, then reduce to 350° and bake 40 minutes more.

title: cola cake
directions: In large bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Set aside.
In medium saucepan, combine margarine, cola and cocoa.
Heat to boiling and pour over flour mixture.
Beat until well mixed.
Add buttermilk, eggs, baking soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Beat well and pour into greased and floured pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet pickle sticks
directions: Wash cucumbers; cut into sticks.
Pour boiling water over them and let stand for 4 to 5 hours.
Drain and pack solidly into jars. Make a solution of remaining ingredients.
Boil 5 minutes.
Pour boiling hot mixture over cucumbers.
Water bath for 5 minutes.

title: polly's potato soup
directions: Brown in large pot the onion and margarine.
Stir in flour. Add salt, potatoes and hot water.
Cook until potatoes are tender. Add milk and ham.
Sprinkle with parsley before serving.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all dry ingredients.
Add Crisco, beaten egg and milk; mix well.
Add a little water if batter seems stiff.
Pour into hot, well-greased pan and bake for 25 to 30 minutes in preheated 435° to 450° oven.
Makes 8 or more servings.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and bell pepper.
Drain off grease. Add corn, tomatoes, tomato sauce, salt, pepper and garlic powder. Simmer until warmed through.
Add grated cheese and heat until melted.

title: taco soup
directions: Combine all ingredients including liquid from cans.
Cook on low heat for at least 1 hour or more.
Add water if needed.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Line baking dish with foil.
Heat butter in pan until melted.
Mix Bisquick, paprika, salt and pepper. Coat chicken.
Place skin sides down in pan.
Bake uncovered 35 minutes.
Turn and bake until done, about 15 minutes.

title: sunshine punch
directions: Freeze in a Bundt pan the juices and fruit. Put frozen ring in punch bowl. Add sherbet, then add pop.

title: pineapple bread pudding
directions: Drain pineapple well; reserve 1/2 cup of juice.
Tear or cut bread into 1-inch cubes.
Place in baking pan.
Drizzle with melted margarine and pineapple juice.
Moisten evenly.
Sprinkle pineapple and raisins over bread and mix lightly.
Beat eggs with brown sugar and spices.
Stir in milk.
Pour evenly over bread mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is set.
Serve with Vanilla Custard Sauce.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Combine first eight ingredients and 1/4 cup cheese.
Put into 1-quart baking dish and bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and bake 5 minutes.

title: spiced orange tea
directions: Mix 1 teaspoon in 1 cup hot water.

title: mexicali casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 2-quart baking dish with nonstick spray.
Spread cooked noodles evenly over bottom of dish.
In a bowl, mix chili, beans and chili powder.
Spread over noodles. Sprinkle cheese evenly over mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is browned.
Makes approximately 6 to 8 servings.

title: salmon patties
directions: Place salmon into mixing bowl.
Remove bones, reserving liquid in bowl.
Break salmon apart with a fork.
Add slightly beaten egg, lemon juice, onion, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add flour until mixture can be spooned into a frying pan.
Heat cooking oil in pan and spoon mixture into pan.
Cook each side until brown. Drain on paper towel.

title: brownies
directions: Mix well. Bake in greased pan at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: chicken croquettes
directions: Mix butter in saucepan over low heat.
Stir in flour.
Add stock slowly.
Then add salt and pepper; cook over low heat.
Stir until thick and creamy.
Add the chicken and parsley; blend. Remove from heat.
Beat 1 egg and add to the chicken mixture. Cook for 1 minute longer.
Cool and shape into croquettes. Combine remaining egg with milk.
Roll croquettes in this, then in cracker crumbs.
Deep fry at 375° for about 2 minutes on each side.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except bread, together in bowl.
Cut a hole in the middle of bread and place in the hole.
Cut up bread from hole and the additional loaf to dip into mixture.

title: beef roast
directions: Place roast on heavy aluminum foil in a shallow pan.
Slice vegetables around.
Add seasoning and soups.
Wrap securely and bake at 450° for 15 minutes; then bake at 250° for 3 1/2 hours. Serves 8.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Crush pretzels.
Mix together pretzels, 1/2 cup sugar and butter.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Beat together Cool Whip, cream cheese and 1 cup sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Add boiling water to jello.
When jello is thoroughly mixed, add strawberries.
Place jello in refrigerator until partially set.
Place on top of salad.
Refrigerate, covered.

title: spaetzle
directions: Combine flour, salt and nutmeg.
Add eggs and milk and mix well, then add to flour mixture.
In large pan bring broth or water to boil.
Drop batter by 1/2 teaspoons into boiling broth. Boil spaetzle until they come to the top.
Remove to ice water. Drain well.
In skillet, heat butter and add spaetzle; brown lightly.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 2.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Combine sugar, water and cornstarch; cook until clear.
Add Jell-O.
Cool; add about 1 quart of fresh strawberries.
Put in pie shell.
Chill.
Top with Cool Whip before serving.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Beat 3 minutes, until creamy.
Pour batter into greased and floured 9-inch round pans or a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes, or until done.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
In skillet, cook beef, onion and green pepper until meat is brown and vegetables tender; drain off fat. Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Melt butter.
Add raw macaroni.
Stir well to coat macaroni. Add milk, salt, pepper and the cheese.
Bake for 2 1/2 to 3 hours at 250°.

title: macaroni corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix the macaroni, whole kernel corn and cream-style corn in a baking dish.
Microwave the butter or margarine and cheese in a microwave-safe dish until melted.
Add to the corn mixture.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: zesty salad
directions: Use any amounts of ingredients; place in a large bowl.
Pour the dressing over and mix.
Chill until ready to use.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: grape-nuts muffins
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Add cereal.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to dry ingredients, just to dampen.
Put into muffin cups.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute celery and onions in margarine. Add pimentos and chicken. Add chicken broth, soup and Velveeta and stir until melted. Add cooked spaghetti. Put in sprayed casserole dish. Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate angel food cake
directions: Sift flour, cocoa and salt together.
Add cream of tartar to egg whites and beat until they will hold peaks.
Add vanilla, then sugar.
Gradually beat well after each addition, then fold in flour mixture.
Put in ungreased tube pan.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes in 350° to 375° oven.
Cool cake upside down, then loosen from sides and remove.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Mix flour and sugar together and add to eggs. Add melted butter and beat well.
Stir in buttermilk and vanilla. Pour mixture into pie crust.
Bake at 325° until firm in center, about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: chili cheddar cheese casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish and preheat oven to 350°.
Cut veins and seeds from chilies and slice.
Alternate layers of chilies and cheese in casserole dish.
Add flour to beaten eggs and mix thoroughly.
Add milk and mix thoroughly.
Pour mixture over chilies and cheese.
Bake for approximately 40 minutes or until golden brown and fluffy.

title: pizzelles
directions: Mix margarine and beaten eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat in flour and baking powder.
Drop by teaspoon onto hot pizzelle iron.
Squeeze handles together to flatten batter and cook for 15 to 20 seconds.
Lift off with a fork.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar when cool.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients by hand.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: grandma's special cake
directions: Cream sugar,
butter
and eggs.
Dissolve soda in milk. Add to creamed
mixture.
Add
the sifted flour and beat until smooth. Bake in moderate oven.

title: delicious peach cobbler
directions: Put peaches in bottom of large baking dish, 9 x 13-inch. Sprinkle with cake mix.
Top with butter slices.
Bake at 375° until brown on top.
This is also good with other pie filling.

title: oreo cookie freeze
directions: Crush Oreos and mix with margarine.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.
Soften ice cream and spread on top of crust; refreeze.
Boil for 1 minute, sugar, evaporated milk, vanilla, chocolate and margarine.
Cool; pour over ice cream and refreeze. Mix Cool Whip with nuts and spread over chocolate.
Keep frozen until ready to serve.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: roma's frozen fruit salad
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put in freezer.
Take out 2 hours before serving.

title: rotten cake
directions: Bake yellow cake; split each layer to make 4 layers.
Spread between layers (combined) sour cream and 8 ounces whipped topping. Spread this on top and sides of cake.
Sprinkle with coconut. Refrigerate in tightly covered container for 3 days.

title: chocolate pudding cake
directions: For first layer, mix flour, margarine and nuts together. In a 13 x 9-inch pan, pat down the flour mixture and bake in 350° oven 20 minutes. Cool. For second layer, cream the cream cheese and confectioners sugar and fold in the whipped topping. Spread on top of the first layer. For third layer, mix chocolate pudding and milk together. Place in refrigerator to thicken. Then spread on top of second layer. Finish with the fourth layer by spreading the remainder of the whipped topping on top of the third layer and sprinkle with chopped nuts. Place in refrigerator. Serves 18.

title: deep dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine ingredients in a large mixing bowl. Add remaining ingredients (except boiling water).
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Remove from mixer.
Stir in boiling water.
(Batter will be thin.)
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans or one 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes for layers and 35 to 40 minutes for 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool completely before removing from pan.

title: lemon cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together except powdered sugar.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into powdered sugar and roll into balls until covered with sugar.
Place balls on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.
Cool a few minutes before removing from pan, then place on cooling rack.
May be glazed with an icing mixture from powdered sugar and lemon juice.
Other flavors of cake mix may be substituted to change flavor of cookies.

title: streusel coffee cake
directions: Mix together with mixer.

title: bacon quiche
directions: Combine eggs, Pet milk, salt and nutmeg in a bowl. Beat on medium speed of mixer.
Fry bacon. Saute onion and green pepper in some of the bacon oil. Crumble in bacon. Add salt, pepper and cheese.
Mix well. Pour in pie crust.
Sprinkle parsley flakes. Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes.
Let set 20 minutes before cutting.

title: peanut butter fudge cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Then open jar of peanut butter.
If oil and peanut butter have separated, stir together well.
Pour jar into bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Roll into balls and crisscross with sugar coated fork.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes.
After removing from oven, let sit on pan for 8 minutes before removing. Place on rack to cool completely!
Delicious!!

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Mix hot rice with Cheez Whiz.
Layer mixture, beginning and ending with rice.
Pour soup over all.
Bake until bubbly.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon.
Take out small bones.
Flake salmon with a fork.
Add all ingredients.
Bake in 1 1/2-quart loaf pan for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Saute the onion and garlic in the oil in a 1-quart nonstick saucepan for 3 minutes.
Add the celery, tomatillos, chicken broth and cilantro.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Shred the chicken breasts and add with the yogurt to the tomatillo sauce.

Lay a tortilla flat and place 1/2 cup of the chicken mixture along the center. Fold over the ends to cover the mixture and place, seam side down, in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch casserole that has a thin layer of enchilada sauce on the bottom.
Repeat with the remaining tortillas.
Cover with enchilada sauce.
Sprinkle with shredded Mozzarella cheese and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
To serve, garnish with the yogurt mixture topped with chopped green onions. Serves 4. Two enchiladas equals one serving.

title: quick 'n easy corn relish
directions: In bowl, combine drained corn and cooking oil.
In a small saucepan, combine sugar, vinegar, minced onion, salt and celery seed.
Cover and bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes.
Add to corn mixture; cover and cool.
Refrigerate several hours or until thoroughly chilled.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking soda and sugar; add Crisco oil, eggs and milk.
Mix well with mixer.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
By hand, mix poppy seed through mixture.
Put in greased Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until cake test is done.
When cake is cool, turn onto dish and sprinkle generously with powdered sugar.

title: taco dip(appetizer)
directions: Brown meat in heavy skillet.
Drain.
Mix cream cheese with sour cream and 1/2 package of taco seasoning.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Extract the juice from the oranges and grind the rind of 1/2 orange.
Mix the rind, sugar and cranberries together and let stand.

title: company pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet.
Drain. Mix onion and chili sauce.
Place pork chops in oiled baking dish.
Spread onion and chili sauce over them.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: mrs. margaret long's applesauce drop cookies
directions: Grease pans lightly. Bake in middle of oven at 350°.
Makes about 90 small cookies.

title: corn souffle
directions: Put aside 1/4 cup of the Cheddar cheese for the top of the casserole.
Mix all other ingredients together and pour into greased casserole dish.
Sprinkle the remaining cheese over the top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: french wafers
directions: Grease pan; set oven on 350°.
Shape mixture; bake for 20 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar.

title: mounds
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients and form into small balls.
Melt bark in top of double boiler.
Dip balls in until covered.
Place on foil to cool.
This makes a large amount.
I make some dark and some white.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Mix ingredients well.
Use 2 1/2 heaping teaspoonfuls for 1 cup hot water.

title: children's hour brownies
directions: Mix cocoa and sugar together.
Put in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in flour.
Pour into 9 x 11-inch pan that has been greased.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together; spread in bottom of 8 x 8-inch dish.
Top with shredded lettuce, tomato, olives, etc. Then pour taco sauce over top.
Chill and serve with nacho chips.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Mix and spread in a buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Rinse, dry and dice apples. Place in a deep bowl and sprinkle with lemon juice, a tad of sugar, a tad of salt and vinegar. Stir and mix. Add raisins, pecans, celery and mayonnaise; stir. Shredded coconut may be substituted for nuts.

title: hot mustard sauce
directions: Sift ingredients together; add 2 tablespoons water and mix well.
Cover and set 1 hour, then, with 1/2 cup vinegar, cook until clear.
Do not let the mixture get too thick.
Chill and serve.
Great with ham or turkey.

title: sweet dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Beat margarine and sugar together until fluffy.
Stir in eggs, yeast, lukewarm milk, flour and salt and beat with wooden spoon until smooth.
Cover and let rise 30 minutes.
Punch down and let rise 30 minutes longer.
Let rise 20 minutes and bake in a 400° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli and chicken(quick and easy)
directions: Cook chicken in 1 tablespoon margarine. Remove. In the other tablespoon margarine, cook vegetables. Stir in soup, milk and black pepper. Heat to boil. Return chicken and simmer. Total cooking time: 20 minutes.

title: pickle relish
directions: Mix veggies together.
Let stand in salted water for 30 minutes.
Drain.
Rinse salt off.
Add remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Boil for 10 to 15 minutes, stirring constantly. Seal in sterilized jars.

title: mama's frozen fruit cake
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
Add to scalded milk.
Cook over boiling water until smooth, stirring constantly.
Add eggs and cook 2 more minutes.
Add vanilla, cookies, cherries and nuts. Fold in whipped cream.
Freeze in an oblong pan.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Break cauliflower and broccoli into small pieces. Wash and drain thoroughly.
Mix mayonnaise, sugar and vinegar to make a dressing.
Pour over vegetables.
Marinate overnight, turning several times to coat well.

title: mom's au gratin potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender; let cool, then slice.
Melt oleo, flour, salt, pepper, Milnot, water and Velveeta together.
In a casserole dish, layer sliced potatoes, small amount of chopped onions and peppers.
Repeat.
Pour the cheese mixture over the potatoes.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: best ever corn bread
directions: Melt butter and set aside.
In large bowl, whisk together flour, corn meal, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Combine eggs and milk and melted butter.
Pour into flour mixture.
Blend with wooden spoon.
Batter should be moist but not runny.
With spatula, spread into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Bake in center rack of oven at 350° until toothpick tested in center comes out clean. Allow to cool 20 minutes.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Mash bananas and everything together, except nuts.
Mix well with mixer, then add pecans.
Use a greased and floured Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Put fruit and nuts together.
Mix the butter and honey together.
Add the flavoring and pour over the fruit.
Let stand 2 hours.
Mix the crackers and spices together and the salt.
Mix all the ingredients together and pack in a greased, lined pan and cover.
Put in the refrigerator until you use it.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Sift all dry ingredients into large bowl.
Add eggs, vanilla and Wesson oil.
Beat well, either by hand or with mixer.
Add nuts.
Pour into an oiled 9 x 9-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean when testing.
They should be soft and moist.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients with thawed broccoli.
Bake in greased pan at 350° for about 45 minutes.
(Can be made in Bundt pan.)

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each egg is added.
Add sour cream to which baking soda has been added, alternating with the flour until all sour cream and flour is mixed in well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan and bake at 300° to 325° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until done. Remove from pan and place on rack to cool.
Can frost if you like.

title: we three sherbet
directions: Squeeze out pulp and juice of oranges and lemons.
Mash bananas fine.
Cook sugar and water together and, when cool, add oranges, lemons and bananas; freeze.

title: peach or berry custard pie
directions: Mix fruit and flour well and pour into unbaked deep pie crust. Mix together egg, sugar, milk, salt and vanilla and pour over fruit. Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower parmesan
directions: Boil cauliflower until tender.
Place in glass baking dish, flower side up.
Cover with pats of butter.
Cover with Parmesan cheese.
Place under broiler for 3 minutes or until golden brown and cheese melts.

title: snickerdoodle cookies
directions: Stir together flour, soda, cream of tartar and salt. Beat butter for 30 seconds. Add sugar and beat until fluffy. Add eggs, milk, vanilla and beat well. Add dry ingredients to beaten mixture, beating until well combined. Form dough into 1-inch balls. Roll in mixture of cinnamon and sugar. Place balls 2-inches apart on a cookie sheet (greased) and flatten each ball with bottom of a glass slightly. Bake at 375° for about 8 minutes until light golden.

title: chicken soup irish-style
directions: Bring water, salt and chicken parts to a boil in a large saucepan; cover and simmer 1 hour.
Add celery, leek, carrot and potatoes; simmer for 20 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth and add peas.
Simmer 8 minutes.
Remove scum from soup.
Lightly beat egg yolks; stir in yogurt.
Remove soup from heat and stir in yogurt mixture.
Adjust seasonings.
Garnish with lettuce.
Serve at once.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix well and chill.
Serve with strawberries, pineapple chunks, bananas, apples, peaches, etc.

title: the black-eyed peas' baked squash
directions: Cut off tips of squash and cut each into 3 or 4 pieces.
Place in boiling water, making sure it is totally covered.
Return water to a boil; reduce heat and cook until tender.
Drain in colander; mash.
Combine squash with beaten eggs, bread crumbs, butter, sugar, salt, pepper and onions.
Turn all ingredients into a 3-quart casserole that has been lightly greased or sprayed.
Cover with a layer of bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned, approximately 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter chip brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar, corn syrup and vanilla until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating until well blended.
In separate bowl, stir together the flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually blend into butter mixture.
Stir in peanut butter chips.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies just begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool completely in pan on wire rack.
Cut into bars.
Makes about 36 brownies.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Thoroughly mix together sugar, oil and eggs.
Sift together the dry ingredients and add to the sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Add pumpkin, nuts and raisins.
Pour into a standard bread pan and bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from the pan and cool on a rack.

title: champagne salad
directions: Mix together softened cream cheese and sugar, then add strawberries and juice, bananas, pineapple, pecans and La Creme. Pour into 10 x 13-inch cake pan.
Place in freezer.
Let this salad sit out a while before serving and return unused portion to freezer.
This is a delicious and refreshing salad.

title: cashew salad
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and chill.
Fry bacon, drain and measure out 1/3 cup - adding salad oil if necessary.
Return to pan with vinegar, sugar and pepper and stir; when warm,
pour over lettuce.
Garnish with parmesan cheese.

title: buster bar dessert
directions: Crush 1 pound Oreo cookies and mix with 1/2 cup melted butter. Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Lay on 1 1/2 cups chopped peanuts, then put on 1/2 gallon vanilla ice cream and freeze.

title: garbanzo spread(appetizer)
directions: Put all in food processor and grind to a fine paste.
Serve with crackers or Spoon-Size Shredded Wheat.

title: meat 7-layer casserole
directions: In a covered casserole, layer ingredients in this order: rice, corn, salt and pepper, tomato sauce, water, onion, green pepper, ground beef, more salt and pepper and garlic powder.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes longer.

title: apple crisp
directions: Butter dish size you think will hold ingredients.
Mix all ingredients thoroughly and put in pan.
Pour melted margarine over top.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: drop doughnuts
directions: Stir mixture well and drop by teaspoon in hot fat like doughnuts.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill overnight.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: potato soup
directions: Barely cover potatoes, onion and celery with water; cook until tender.
Mash with potato masher.
Add milk, butter, salt and pepper.
Serve topped with finely chopped parsley.
Serves 4.

title: hamburg barbecue
directions: Brown hamburg and onions; drain the fat.
Add your ingredients in bowl; mix well.
When hamburg is brown, add ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil, then add flour, cinnamon, salt, baking soda and baking powder.
Mix, then add zucchini and vanilla and mix again.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes in 2 greased and floured pans.

title: pineapple cheesecake squares
directions: Mix all ingredients in medium bowl with fork until crumbly. Press firmly and evenly in bottom of ungreased 13 x 9 inch rectangular pan.
Bake until set, 15-20 minutes at 350°.

title: flour icing
directions: Bring to a boil the flour and milk until it thickens.
Cool. Then cream together the butter, sugar and vanilla.
Add the cooled paste and beat 7 minutes.
It is very important to beat this icing the whole time.

title: cheese sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Add flour to milk and shake so there are no lumps visible.
Add to butter and cook until thick and smooth. Add salt, pepper and paprika.
Add cheese.
Stir until the cheese is melted and well blended.

title: jam cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, 1 at a time.
Beat soda into buttermilk; add to shortening mixture.
Add jam.
Sift 2 cups of flour with spices; add to batter, slowly.
Mix nuts and raisins with remaining cup of flour; add to mixture and beat.

title: homemade chili
directions: Brown beef in heavy large skillet.
Add juice, salt, onion, sugar, pepper, beans and sauce.
Stir; simmer for 30 to 40 minutes on low heat.

title: quick chicken soup
directions: Place cut chicken breasts in medium saucepan.
Pour chicken broth over chicken.
Cover and cook over medium-low heat for 20 to 25 minutes, until tender.
Stir in vegetables with rice and chicken; cook, stirring twice, until heated through.
Add spices (parsley, basil, etc.).
Serves 4 to 6.
